Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling west on a three-lane, divided roadway.  V1 was traveling in lane three.  V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted the bridge (event 1).  V1 re-entered the road and departed the road to the right.  V1 came to rest partially on the roadway.  V2 and V3 were traveling in lane one.  V2 began to rotate clockwise.  V3 departed the road to the right and the right of V3 contacted the bridge (event 2).  V3 began to rotate counterclockwise.and re-entered the road.  The front of V3 contacted the bridge (event 3).  The left of V2 contacted the left of V3 (event 4).  Both vehicles continued to rotate and the back of V2 contacted the left of V3 (event 5).    The right of V2 then contacted the left of V1 (event 6).  All three vehicle came to rest near their final events.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane roadway not divided by a positive barrier, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #3 was legally parked facing south. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 departed the lane and roadway on the left side and contacted the front on a wall. V1 overturned on the right side and contacted the top on a pole.  V2 rotated clockwise and the left side contacted the left side of V3. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing south on the passenger side. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing north. V3 came to rest off the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane three of a five lane, two way undivided roadway turning left approaching a highway entrance. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane one of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 2 contacted the right of Vehicle 1. V1 rotated counterclockwise and the front of Vehicle 1 then contacted a guardrail. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing south, Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane three of a five lane roadway not divided by a positive barrier turning left at an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane one of a five lane roadway not divided by a positive barrier approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right of V1. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane three of a six lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one of a six lane, two way physically divided roadway without a positive barrier approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east on the north leg of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to final rest within the intersection facing west.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2-lane, one-way on ramp. Its left front then left rear tires contacted a police spike strip placed on the roadway. V2 was traveling north in lane 3 on the adjoining 5-lane divided roadway. After contacting the spikes, V1 entered the 5-lane roadway where its left side contacted the back of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the left road edge where its back plane contacted a concrete barrier. V1 continued its rotation and the front contacted the barrier. V1 came to rest on the paved shoulder facing north. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the left road edge where its front plane contacted the concrete barrier. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest on the paved shoulder facing southwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southwest in lane one of an intersecting two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 began to turn left at the intersection.  The left of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 came to rest partially on the roadway facing northeast.  V2 came to rest on the roadway facing south near impact.

V1 was exiting a parking lot to turn onto the southbound lane. V2 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four-lane, undivided roadway. V3 was parked in the parking lot V1 was exiting. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. V2 was then redirected forward and to the right. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V2 impacted the front of V3. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact facing generally north. V2 and V3 came to final rest at the point of impact. V2 was facing generally south while V3 was facing in its original direction of west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane roadway with a positive barrier.  V1 departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a guardrail end.  The guardrail deformed and the left plane of V1 contacted the guardrail face.  V1 came to rest facing south off the road to the right.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left to avoid a deer in the road. V1 then departed the left side of the roadway impacting a guardrail end with its frontal plane causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated counter clockwise traveling down an embankment coming to final rest at the bottom of the embankment facing north.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, two-way, non-divided roadway, and was approaching a stop sign at an intersection. The vehicle did not stop at the stop sign and crossed over a two lane, two-way roadway. The vehicle then departed the roadway and its front plane contacted an embankment. The vehicle then came to final rest with its front plane against the embankment.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane one, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, attempting to crossover the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicle rotated where the right plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 continues rotating clockwise, striking an unknown object with its left plane. V2 continued off the roadway down an embankment and over a small culvert where the undercarriage impacted the embankment on the opposite side of the culvert before before coming to final rest off the roadway facing southeast. V2 continued forward coming to a final rest on the paved shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane one, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, attempting to crossover the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right plane of V1 was contacted by the front plane of V2. V1 began rotating striking V2's right side with the right plane of V1. V1 continued forward coming to a final rest off the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction and came to a final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling North on a non-physically divided, two-way roadway, approaching a four-legged intersection. V1 turned right on the intersection and departed the roadway. The front of V1 contacted a tree and came to final rest there.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching a light controlled intersection. V2 was travelling westbound on a three lane, divided roadway in lane two. During the intersection the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest inside the intersection facing northeast. V2 came to rest inside the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a three lane, divided roadway in lane two. A deer was crossing the roadway and the front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to a controlled rest on the shoulder facing northbound.
V1 was traveling north in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a grass median. A deer entered the roadway and was contacted by V1's frontal plane.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge and reentered the roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed left road edge in a clockwise yaw. V1's left plane contacted a tree twice before coming to final rest off the left road edge.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a traffic light. V1 was traveling in lane two. V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway traveling on a two-lane roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. V1 was making a left turn to head eastbound when the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway. V1 was facing east and V2 was facing northwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. V1 lost control and began to rotate clockwise and departed the right road edge. V1 continued off of the roadway where the undercarriage of V1 impacted a water pipe. V1 continued and began to roll left six quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its roof facing a southeasterly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one stopped at a stop sign at an intersection, waiting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling south on a three lane undivided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. V3 was traveling north on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V1 attempted to make a left turn and the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. After impact, V1 began to rotate counter clockwise into the northbound lanes and off of the east road edge where the rear of V1 impacted an embankment. As V1 came to rest, the front of V3 impacted the left side of V1. V1 came to rest on the east shoulder facing a westerly. V2 came to rest on the east shoulder facing a northwesterly direction. V3 came to rest on the east shoulder facing a northerly direction.

V1 and V2 were traveling northwest in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane divided trafficway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise while departing the roadway to the left where the right side of V1 impacted a guardrail. V2, after the impact with V1, departed the roadway to the right where the front of V2 impacted a fence. V1, after the impact with the guardrail, continued to rotate counter-clockwise and came to rest facing northerly on the west shoulder. V2 came to rest facing easterly off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway. V2 was parked facing south on the west shoulder. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 then rolled over onto its left side. V1 came to rest facing southeast on its roof, south of V2. V2 came to rest facing southwesterly on the west shoulder.

V1 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 5 lane divided highway. Lane #1 became an off ramp and a gore point formed. V1 continued in the now #1 lane of a 4 lane highway traveling north. V1 departed the roadway to the right in the gore point. The front of V1 impacted an impact attenuator. V1 came to rest facing north east with the front of V1 against the impact attenuator.

V1 was traveling east in the #1 lane of a 4 lane roadway. V2 was stopped at an intersection facing north. V1 crossed through the intersection. V2 traveled north attempting to turn left and head west. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest facing east in the middle of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing north in the middle of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a divided traffic way (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the road on the left and was returned to the road from the left. V1 then crossed both northbound lanes and departed the road on the right, where its front end contacted a fence and continued forward. V1 then traveled into a dry creek bed and its front end contacted the bottom of the creek bed. V1's undercarriage then contacted the slope of the creek bed. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction in the open desert east of the traffic way.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 4-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped facing east in lane 3 on a 3-lane divided roadway at the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the southwest curb edge where its left front tire contacted the curb. V1 came to rest on the sidewalk facing southwest. V2 rotated clockwise and the front of V2 contacted the front of V3. V2 and V3 came to rest in the area of impact.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left shoulder and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer in the road. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, five lane lane, embankment divided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, contacting a tree with its frontal plane. V1 then began to roll left side leading two quarter turns where it came to final rest off of the roadway on its roof.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both westbound on a three-lane divided highway. Vehicle 1 was in lane two and Vehicle 2 was in lane three. Vehicle 1 moved into lane three where the front of Vehicle 2 struck the back of Vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was following V2 eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 slowed for other vehicles in the travel lane as the frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2 causing damage. V1 and V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, non-physically undivided roadway in the number 2 lane approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 2 lane, non-physically undivided roadway in the number 1 lane approaching the same 4 way intersection. V3 was stopped at a traffic signal at the 4 way intersection traveling south in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane non-physically undivided roadway. V4 was also stopped at the traffic signal traveling south next to V3 in lane 1. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The right plane of V1 collided with the front plane of V2. Due to impact V1 and V2 rotated away from each other causing the right plane of V1 to collide with the left side of V2. V1 traveled westward, departed the roadway left side, traveled down a ditch and entered a roll making 2 quarter turns coming to rest on its roof facing south west.. At the same time, V2 also traveled westerly rotating in a counter clockwise rotation. The rear plane of V2 collide with the front plane of V3

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a four-lane undivided roadway approaching a three leg intersection. Vehicle 1 was in the designated left turn lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane No. 1 of an undivided three-lane roadway, approaching the same intersection. The driver of Vehicle 1 initiated a left turn as the front of Vehicle 1 impacted the left side plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to rest within the intersection and facing north. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in lane No. 1 and facing west.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 1 of a 2 way undivided roadway attempting to crossover an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound in lane 1 of a 2 way undivided roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection.  Within the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the left of V1.  V1 was deflected towards the Southwest corner of the intersection, departing the roadway where its front contacted a low retaining block wall before coming to rest facing Southwest.  V2 stayed in its original lane of traffic and came to final rest shortly after impact, facing West.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a four lane undivided roadway approaching a four way intersection.  V2 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  V2 attempted to make a right turn at the intersection as V1 was passing through the intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  V1 rotated counterclockwise to final rest in the intersection facing southeast.  V2 rotated clockwise to final rest in the intersection facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) road, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 turned left into the southbound lanes of traffic. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and moved north into the southbound lanes. V1 came to rest at the west curb of the southbound lanes, facing southeast. V2 rolled onto its left side and slid to final rest. V2 came to final rest in lane one, laying on its left side, facing east.

V1 was traveling south in lane 3 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching a three way intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 3 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 was passing through the intersection, it departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Continuing forward, V1 crossed over a raised median and re-entered its original travel lane before coming to final rest on the roadway, facing south. V2 came to final rest near impact facing north.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer crossed the path of V1 contacting its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 departed the roadway north of the intersection, and the front of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were all southbound in the same lane of a seven-lane divided highway. V2, V3, and V4 were all stopped ahead of V1. The front of V1 struck the back of V2 (event 1), followed by the front of V2 striking the back of V3 (event 2) and the front of V3 striking the back of V4 (event 3). Finally, the right side of V1 swiped the left side of V3 (event 4). All the vehicles came to final rest on the highway.

Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling west on a physically undivided, two lane roadway in lane one. Vehicle 2 attempted to pass Vehicle 1 as Vehicle 1 attempted to make a left turn into a driveway. The left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both Vehicles departed the roadway on the left. The front of Vehicle 2 contacted a utility pole. Both vehicles came to final rest off the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was traveling southeast bound on an undivided 4 lane roadway, in lane 2 and approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south west bound on a 2 lane, undivided, roadway and approaching the same intersection. With in the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 3 lane roadway, in lane 3 and approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a 4 lane roadway, in lane 2 and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided two way road in lane one. Due to windy conditions, a tree branch fell from above the road and impacted the top of V1. V1 came to rest in lane one facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a divided six lane highway, in lane one, approaching an intersection to make a right turn. V1 attempted to negotiate the turn and traveled off the south road edge where the front of V1 impacted a wooden sign, the wooden sign then impacted the top of V1. V1 continued in a southwest direction, and the front of V1 impacted an embankment. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southwest direction.

V1 was traveling west in the third of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east in the fourth of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway roadway entering the same intersection as V1 attempting to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the back of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 departed the road on the northwest corner and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to rest partially off the road and caught fire. V2 came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, two way crossover. V2 was traveling south in lane two on a four lane, divided roadway and was negotiating a left curve. At the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. After impact, V2 continued forward and began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction. The vehicle then departed the roadway on the left side before coming to final rest. V2 came to final rest off of the roadway facing east, with the right rear tire on the roadway. V1 came to final rest in lane one of the four lane roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 hauling a trailer was traveling west, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection as V1. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated in a clockwise direction while V2 rotated in a counter clockwise direction. The left side of V1 made contact with the right side of V2. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and made contact with the right side of V2 a second time. V2 continue forward in a counter clockwise rotation and departed the west side of the southbound roadway. The trailer being hauled by V2 jackknifed causing damage to rear plane of V2. V1 continued forward and departed the west side of the southbound roadway. Both vehicles came to a final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a physically divided roadway with three lanes traveling westbound, V1 was in lane one. V2 was traveling westbound on the mentioned divided roadway with three lanes traveling eastbound, V2 was in lane three attempting a left turn to head southbound. In the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 then continue off the roadway on the southeast corner, with V2 rotating in a counterclockwise manner. During the roadway departure the front plane of V1 contacted a utility marker, a utility pole with the left plane, and contacted the front of V2 again with its front plane. V2 contacted the curb on the right plane, a utility marker and V2 on the front plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing westbound, V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling directly in front of V1, attempting to turn right. V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane two, on a four lane, two-way roadway controlled by a traffic light at a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway passing through the mentioned intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. After initial impact with V2, V1 continued northwest, where it departed the left side roadway and struck a light pole base with it's front plane, before coming to final rest facing westbound off roadway. V2 came to final rest at intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a non-physically divided roadway with two lanes traveling west and two lanes traveling east. V1 departed its lane to the left side and continued into oncoming traffic lanes where it departed the roadway to the left. The front plane of V1 then struck a guardrail end while continuing off the roadway. After impact with the guardrail the left plane of V1 contacted a utility pole while airborne, when V1 landed the undercarriage struck a rock. V1 continued off the road down a small embankment where the right front wheel struck a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing northwest.
V1 was traveling north west on a two lane, one way, highway entering an off ramp. V1 lost control and its frontal plane contacted a guardrail. V1 came to final rest on the off ramp.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling southeast in lane three on a four-lane divided roadway. V3 was ahead of V2 and V2 was ahead of V1. V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic when the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed into V3 and its front plane contacted the back of V3. All vehicles came to rest at impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane three of a five-lane undivided roadway, attempting a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane not physically divided roadway, passing through the same intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway close to impact.

V1 was traveling northest on the right gravel shoulder of a two lane roadway. The right shoulder was used as a school pick up/drop off lane. V1's right wheels went off the edge of the shoulder. V1 then fell over to the right and rolled four quarter turns down an embankment off the shoulder. V1 came to rest up on its wheels at the bottom of the embankment off the right road edge.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, positively divided median barrier roadway. Vehicle one departed the left side of the roadway contacted a guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and overturned five quarter turns before coming to final rest on its right side.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left. An animal was in the roadway and V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's left side contacted a guy wire before its front contacted a fence. V1 continued forward and its right side contacted a tree and its front contacted another tree. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling  southbound on a two lane, one-way roadway in lane two passing through the same intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. After initial impact with V2, V1 rotated counter clockwise, and departed the left side roadway where it contacted a pole with its back plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway. V2 came to final rest in the roadway, south of the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and contacted a group of small trees with its front, right and left side planes. V1 continued forward contacting two large trees with its right side and front planes. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was parked facing east along the south curb. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway ahead facing east. V2 came to rest near the point of impact facing east.

V1 was entering the roadway, traveling west on a two way, two lane driveway. V2 was traveling north on the two way, two lane intersecting roadway. V3 was traveling south on the same two way, two lane intersecting roadway. As V1 entered the roadway, it impacted the front of V2 with its frontal plane. The impact pushed the front of V1 into the left side of V3. V1 came to final rest in the southbound lane, facing north. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing north. V3 came to final rest on the southbound shoulder and roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a three lane median divided roadway in the lane 2 position with the intent to turn left at an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane median divided roadway in the lane 1 position with the intent to pass through the same intersection.  As both vehicles entered the intersection the front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southeast near the middle of the intersection shortly after impact.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing roughly southeast in the lower center portion of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way uncontrolled intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The right front side of V1 contacted the front corner of V2. After impact, V2 departed roadway right side and came to rest on a residential lawn facing southwest. V1 came to rest on the roadway also facing southwest at the southwest corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a single lane one way roadway approaching an intersection to pass through.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching the same intersection to pass through.  After stopping Vehicle 1 began to enter the intersection.  The front plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2 who had also entered the same intersection.  After initial contact, V1 rotated counter clockwise coming to final rest facing north in the middle of the intersection.  V2 came to final rest shortly after contact facing north near the top of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 3 lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position. V2 was also traveling west on the same roadway in lane 3 position. V1 departed lane of travel left side. The left side of V1 contacted the left front side of V2. after impact both vehicles connected again the left side of V1 contacted the left rear passenger door of V2. Both vehicles came to rest still facing west in lane 3 position.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane roadway. V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane line on the left. V2 partially departed the roadway on the right. V1's front contacted V2's left side. V1 and V2 both came to rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-lane two-way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling behind vehicle 1 on the same roadway, going to same direction. Vehicle 3 was traveling ahead of vehicle 1 on the same roadway, going the same direction. Vehicle's 1 and 3 stopped in traffic, and the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the back plane of vehicle 1. The front plane of vehicle 1 then contacted the back plane of vehicle 3. Vehicle 1 departed the road to the right, and the right plane of V1 contacted a guardrail. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the shoulder facing north. Vehicles 2 and 3 came to final rest on the road, facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane two on a two-lane divided roadway approaching a four-leg roundabout. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane two, on a two-lane divided roadway approaching the same four-leg roundabout. Both vehicles entered the roundabout and the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the left plane of vehicle 1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the right plane of V1 contacted the base of a long traffic divider. V1 tripped, rolling two quarter turns to the right and came to final rest on its roof, on the shoulder facing south. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the road facing north.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. While V1 was negotiating a curve to the right, a deer entered the roadway where V1 impacted the animal with its frontal plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and departed the roadway to the right. V1 traveled down a large ditch, and impacted the field side of the ditch with its rear plane. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway in the ditch.

V1 was traveling in a southern direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where the V1s frontal plane impacted an embankment and a utility pole. The utility pole sheered off, and part of it impacted the top of V1.  V1 continued in a southern direction, where it again impacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a tree with its left plane. V1 impacted a large rock with its right plane. V1 impacted another tree with its frontal plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and impacted an unknown object with its rear plane. V1 came to final rest facing in a northern direction off the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane three of a three lane roadway divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle #2 was traveling in lane two of a three lane roadway divided by a positive barrier. V1 departed the lane on the right side and contacted the right side on the left side of V2. V2 then departed the lane and roadway on the right side and contacted the front on a guard rail. V2 then contacted the front on a ditch and tree. V2 rotated on the left side three quarter turns. V2 came to rest on its right side off the roadway facing south. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a two lane, two way roadway. V2 and V3 were slowing to a stop ahead of V1 also traveling south in the same lane. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V3. All three vehicles came to final rest shortly after impact, remaining in the same lane, facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane two of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane, two way roadway divided by a median approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one of a five lane, two way undivided roadway with two way left turn lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane two of the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the original lane of travel on the left. The left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. The left side of Vehicle 1 then contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-lane two-way roadway approaching a three leg intersection with a stop sign. Before the intersection vehicle 1 departed the lane on the left side and the undercarriage contacted a raised concrete median. Vehicle 1 continued forward and the undercarriage contacted another raised concrete median. Vehicle 1 then departed the roadway on the north side, contacted an embankment and overturned three quarter turns before coming to final rest off the roadway on its left side facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-lane two-way roadway approaching a three leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling on the same roadway, in the same direction, in front of vehicle 1. Vehicle 3 was traveling on the same roadway, in the same direction, in front of vehicle 2. Vehicles 2 was decelerating behind V3. V3 was stopped at the intersection. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the rear plane of vehicle 2. The front plane of vehicle 2 then contacted the rear plane of vehicle 3. Upon impact all three vehicles came to final rest on the roadway, in their original lane of travel, facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in front of V2, stopped at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise slightly and came to rest facing southeast near the intersection, V1 continued forward where it departed the road edge, crossed a driveway and its front plane contacted a metal post. V1 continued forward where it entered the the intersecting road then departed the left road edge where its front plane contacted a pole. V1 rotated counter-clockwise on the grass roadside then tripped and rolled right 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top facing south.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two way, two lane, non-divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and entered a ditch. As V1 exited the ditch it rotated counter clockwise, and rolled right side leading four quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the roadway in the upright position.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane road passing through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2, causing V1 to rotate clockwise several times before coming to rest, facing west. V1 then caught on fire at final rest. V2 went airborne and departed the road to the left where its left plane impacted a tree and its front plane impacted a row of low lying shrubs and came to rest heading south.

V1 was traveling south in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling south in the same lane behind V1. V2 departed the lane on the left side attempting to pass V1 in the oncoming travel lane. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 departed the southeast corner and the right side of V1 contacted a pole. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the road. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east negotiating a slight curve to the right on a two lane, one way non-physically divided roadway traveling on the right shoulder area. V1 then entered lane 1, exited lane 1, entered lane 2, then exited roadway left side into a landscaped median. V1 traveled across the median and entered the west bound roadway. V1 then traveled across the west bound roadway lanes 1 and 2 and departed roadway on the left side. V1's front left corner contacted a guardrail face. V1 continued east while maintaining contact with the guardrail. V1 then traveled on top of the guardrail making contact with its undercarriage. V1 then entered into an end over end roll making 4 quarter turns while traveling down a hill before coming to rest on its tires at the bottom of the hill facing east. V1 then became engulfed in flames.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  After stopping at the intersection Vehicle 1 entered into the middle of the intersection to pass across the roadway.  Vehicle 2 was attempting to pass through the intersection.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 spun clockwise through the intersection departing the roadway at the southwest corner of the intersection.  It continued its spin off road striking a stop sign post.  It came to rest off the roadway facing east.  Vehicle 2 also spun clockwise 90 degrees departing the roadway at the same southwest corner coming to final rest facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and contacted a guard rail end with it's left side. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise across both lanes departing the roadway on the right side. V1's rear then contacted a guard rail face. V1 then rotated clockwise contacting the face of the guardrail again with it's rear plane. V1 then continued back across both lanes of traffic and partially departed the roadway on the left side before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, four lane roadway, in the left lane of travel. V2 was traveling east on the same two way, four lane roadway in the right lane. As V1 was attempting to turn left into a driveway, the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to final rest on the side of the roadway, in the driveway, facing west. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 departed the lane on the left and V2 departed the roadway on the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left and impacted the left of V2 with its front plane. V1 re-entered the roadway and exited the roadway to the right where its front plane contacted a ditch. V1 came to rest in the ditch facing northeast. V2 came to final rest right after impact off of the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway right where the front plane contacted a guardrail. V1 re-entered the roadway crossing both lane and departed the roadway left in a clockwise yaw where the left plane of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 then rapidly rotated counterclockwise, becoming airborne and the frontal plane contacted the embankment, coming to final rest off the roadway facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a three-lane, two-way road in lane 1. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane 2 of the same road, towing a flat-bed trailer. V2 turned left into a driveway and came to a stop with its trailer partially on the road. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2's trailer. V1 departed the road to the right, and the right plane of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to rest off-road to the east. V2 came to rest on the driveway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two-way, two-lane road. Vehicle #2 was traveling south on an intersection two-way, two-lane road. Both vehicles entered the intersection, and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, and V2 rotated clockwise. The right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles departed the road to the southwest. The front plane of V1 contacted a guard rail face. The left plane of V2 contacted a guard rail face. Both vehicles came to rest off-road to the southwest.

Vehicle #1, Vehicle #2, and Vehicle #3 were traveling in lane one of a three lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The front of V2 contacted the back of V3. V1, V2, and V3 came to rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered into the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2. The right of V1 then contacted the left of V2. After contact Vehicle 1 made a circular movement coming to final rest facing north at the northeast corner of the intersection.  Vehicle traveled through the intersection coming to final rest facing southeast near the southeast corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction on a two lane non divided roadway, approaching a T intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left. V2 was traveling in a northern direction on a two lane, non-divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 was passing through the intersection at the same time as V1. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's left plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and slid off the eastern side of the roadway, where it came to final rest. V2 continued in a northern direction, rotating counter clockwise at the time. V2 departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted an embankment. V2 continued to rotate where its rear plane impacted the embankment. V2 then rolled one quarter turn onto its left side, where it came to final rest in the south bound lane of travel.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle #2 was legally parked facing west. A second vehicle was legally parked in front of V2, facing west. V1 departed the its lane on the right and the front of V1 contacted a curb. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the second parked vehicle in front of it. V1 then rotated counterclockwise and departed the roadway. The right side of V1 then contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing southeast. V2 and the second parked vehicle came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two of a four lane, divided trafficway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane two of a three lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier, approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection proceeding straight and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing east. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling north in lane three of a three lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail face. V1 returned on the roadway on the left side. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane two of a five lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier approaching the intersection. Vehicle #3 was traveling east in lane one of five lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier, approaching the intersection. V1, V2, and V3 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V3. V3 rotated counterclockwise and the right of V3 contacted the left side of V2. V3 traveled southeast and departed the south road edge. The front of V3 contacted a curb and traveled into a grassy area.  V1 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing east. V3 came to rest off the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way roadway. While negotiating a curve to the left, V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted a utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 then reentered the roadway and initiated a quarter turn roll to the left. V1 came to final rest on its left side, in the roadway, facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was following V1 on the same roadway. V1 stopped in the road way and began to move in reverse. The rear plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

V1 was following V2, traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1's frontal plane came into contact with V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway partially in original travel lane.

V1 was traveling south on a six lane, two-way roadway attempting to make a left turn at a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 5 lane non-divided roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right of V1. The impacted caused V1 to rotate counter-clockwise and contact V2 in the right rear with its front. Both vehicle came to rest within the intersection.

V2 was traveling south east on a two-way, two lane, median divided roadway, approaching a cross walk. V1 was traveling behind V2 in the same lane. V2 stopped at the crosswalk and the front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on the roadway just east of the area of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east, exiting a parking lot. Vehicle #2 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road, approaching the parking lot exit. V1 began to turn left. The front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The vehicle then reentered the roadway and began to skid clockwise while crossing the roadway and exiting to the left. V1 then impacted a tree with its front left bumper corner. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and contact two more trees with its left plane. V1 came to final rest against the trees facing northeast.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-lane, two-way road. A deer entered the road from the right side of the road. The front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road heading northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right. A deer entered the road from the right side of the road and impacted the front plane of V1. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road heading southwest.

Vehicles 1, 2, and 3 are all traveling westbound on a 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 2 position at the time of impact.  Vehicle 1 was attempting a lane change from the lane 3 position to the lane 2 position.  Vehicle 2 was slowing for stopped traffic and Vehicle 3 had already come to a stopped position.  As Vehicle 1 was making the lane change, the front plane of the vehicle made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2.  This caused a chain reaction as the front plane of Vehicle 2 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 3.  All three vehicles came to final rest at impact facing west at the east side of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection with the intent to pass through. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 was then launched in to the south east corner of the intersection where it departed the roadway and contacted a building with its front coming to rest facing south east. V1 after impact left the scene.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1. Vehicle 2 was stopped in the roadway un-occupied facing west in lane 1. V1 departed lane of travel left side. The front left of V1 contacted the front left of V2. V2 came to rest at impact facing west. V1 came to rest just after impact still facing east.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling southwest in lane two of a two lane roadway, not divided by a physical barrier. Vehicle #3 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway, not divided by a physical barrier. The front of V1 contacted the Back of V2. V1 departed the lane on the right side and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V3. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing east. V3 came to rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling in south eastern direction on a one lane roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling in a southern direction on a three lane roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 and V2 passed through the intersection the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated in a clockwise direction coming to rest in the intersection facing north west. V2 rotated clockwise, and also came to rest in the intersection facing north west.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the western roads edge into a ditch. V1 rolled primarily to the right and came to final rest off the road way on its roof.

V1 was traveling south west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway following V2. V2 was stopped to turn left. V1's frontal plane contacted the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway. V1 departed original travel lane to the left and continued on its path to depart the left roadway. V1's front plane came into contact first with a utility pole guy-wire and then struck the utility pole. The guy-wire broke free and contact the hood and windshield of V1. V1 came to rest in the grass yard facing north..

V1 was traveling east bound in lane 1 of a 2 way non-divided roadway approaching an intersection with a 2 way non-divided roadway.  V2 was traveling south bound in lane 1 of a 2 way non-divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The left plane of V1 came into contact with the front plane of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing south in the southbound lane of the north/south roadway.  V2 came to rest shortly after impact facing south partially in both lanes of travel.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 attempted to make a right turn but departed the left side of the roadway being turned onto.V1 departed the southwest corner of the intersection in a clockwise yaw, traveled down into a ditch in a left side rotation impacting the left plane and frontal plane causing damage. As V1 fell into the ditch it rotated one quarter turn then righted itself onto its wheels. V1 came to final rest on its wheels off the road facing southwest.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the road facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a undivided two lane road in lane one, V2 was traveling east on a undivided two lane road in lane one. For an unknown reason V1 traveling onto the eastbound lanes and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After the impact, V1 and V2 began to spin clockwise, where V1 came to rest within the eastbound lanes facing a northerly direction. V2 came to rest within the eastbound lanes facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane divided highway in lane one, negotiating a curve. For unknown reasons, V1 lost control and began rotating clockwise and the front of V1 impacted a guardrail. After impact, V1 began rotating clockwise and the driver was ejected out of the driver side door. V1 came to rest on an off ramp facing a southeasterly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway divided by a jersey barrier in lane one. For unknown reasons, V1 departed the roadway to the right and traveled down an embankment where the front of V1 impacted a fence. After impacting the fence, V1 began to roll along the fence left side leading and completed three quarter turns before coming to rest on its left side facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling to the left of V2. V1 departed the lane to the right where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the lane to the left and began to rotate counter-clockwise, then departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise, coming to rest facing easterly in the number 4 lane. V2, after the impact with V1, continued forward and crossed into the number 3 lane, coming to rest facing easterly.

V1 was traveling west across a highway intersection. V2 was traveling south on a three lane undivided highway in lane two approaching the intersection. As V1 passed through the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 continued traveling west and came to rest a half mile west from the collision. V2 came to rest on the west shoulder south of the intersection.

V1 was travelling east in lane 3 of a 5 lane non divided roadway. V1 was turning left onto a 3 lane non divided roadway.  V2 was travelling west in lane 2 of a 5 lane non divided roadway. Within the intersection the right plane of V1 was impacted by the front plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane two of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing east.
V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a sign pole. V1 came to final rest near its point of impact.

Vehicle 1 traveling eastbound in the right turn lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway attempting to turn right at an intersection.  Vehicle 2 traveling southbound in lane 2 of a 3 lane median divided roadway attempting to cross over the same intersection.   V1 departed its lane left where the front contacted the right plane of V2, in lane 3 of southbound leg.   Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise where it contacted a median curb initiating a rollover.   Vehicle 2 continued rolling, coming to final rest approximately 100m from initial contact with V1.  After initial contact, vehicle 1 veered to the right coming to rest in the roadway along the southbound curb.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a deer with its frontal plane that crossed in front of V1 from the east. V1 came to rest headed south on the edge of the southbound lane.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane two, stopped, waiting to make a left turn. V2 was stopped behind V1. V3 was traveling behind V2. The front of V3 impacted the rear of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V1. All three vehicles came to rest in lane two facing south.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching left curve. V1 departed the roadway to right. V1 then impacted a raised curb, and a breakaway sign pole with its front. V1 came to rest south of the curve facing south.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1 and stopped for traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to rest in lane two facing westbound. V2 came to rest in lane one facing westbound.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane, grass median divided, roadway approaching an interchange ramp on its right. As V1 proceeded to travel past the exit interchange, the front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. After the initial impact the deer moved countercockwise and impacted the left side of V1 as V1 steered to its left. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast in lane five on a six-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling southeast in lane one on a five-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 turned left and V2 continued straight, the eight side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and rolled left one quarter turn. V1 came to rest on its left side in the roadway facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east in the first of five lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail. V1 continued off the road and the front of V1 contacted two trees. Vehicle 1 came to rest off the road.
V1 was southbound on a one way roadway in the first of two lanes. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a cement bridge support pillar and came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the first of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling west in the same lane ahead of V1. V2 slowed for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was eastbound on a non physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was west bound on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 made a left turn the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact, both vehicles came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, four lane, guardrail divided interchange negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway and approaching a stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling west on two way, four lane, guardrail divided roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 stopped at the stop sign and while attempting to make a left hand turn entered the intersection. V2 entered the intersection at the same time as V1, and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was heading northwest on a six lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading southeast on the same roadway approaching same intersection. V1 entered the intersection to pass through. V2 entered the intersection to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked facing east on the same roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the right of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 began to rotate counter clockwise and started a left leading roll. V1 complete one quarter turn and came to final rest near the point of impact

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling on the same road in the opposite direction. V1 made a left turn into a private drive. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest heading east, halfway into the driveway. V2 came to rest in the road heading north.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road approaching a cul-de-sac. V1 departed the road to the left and impacted a curb with its left front wheel and then impacted a large shrub with its front plane.   V1 came to rest off of the road facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway negotiating a left curve, approaching an intersection. V1 drove through the intersection and departed the road to the southeast corner of the intersection. The front wheels of V1 impacted a raised curb. The front of V1 impacted the pole of a traffic light. V1 rotated clockwise around the pole and came to rest at the pole facing south. A fire started in the engine compartment of V1, burning the interior of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling north in lane four of a four lane divided (with positive barrier) major highway, negotiating a left curve. V2 and V3 were in the same lane, ahead of V1, stopped for traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward and impacted the rear of V3 with its front. All vehicles came to rest in lane four, facing north.

V2 was westbound, stopped at a three leg intersection waiting to make a left turn. V1 was westbound behind V2 approaching the same intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2 causing damage. V1 and V2 both came to final rest in the westbound lane facing west.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching a three leg intersection to make a left turn. V2 was southbound on a one lane, two way divided roadway with a right turn lane approaching the same intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1 causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated counterclockwise coming to final rest in the intersection facing south. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a bird.  The front of V1 then contacted a mailbox.  V1 continued forward and the front of V1 contacted a driveway culvert.  V1 crossed over the driveway.  Entering the ditch on the other side, the undercarriage of V1 contacted the ground.  V1 continued off road and came to rest in a cornfield.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two of a three-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north in northbound lane one of the same roadway.  V2 steered left to avoid a non-contact vehicle and departed it's lane to the left.  The front of V2 contacted the left of V1.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of three lanes). V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in lane 1, north of V1. V3 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in lane 2, north of V1. V1 departed its lane on the right, and its front end contacted the back of V2. V1 then entered lane 2, where its front end contacted the back end of V3. V1 rotated counterclockwise, continued in a northerly direction where it came to rest on its wheels facing a westerly direction in lanes 3 and 2. V2 and V3 were driven to the right shoulder and parked.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a physically divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 1 (of three lanes) with V1 behind V2. In lane 1, the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 then departed the road on the right and came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction on the roadside. V2 was driven to the right shoulder and parked.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided trafficway. V5 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane. V1 was traveling behind a non-collision vehicle. The non-collision vehicle was traveling behind V2. V2 was traveling behind V3. V4 was traveling behind V1. V5 was traveling behind V4. V2 and V3 came to a stop for traffic ahead. The non-collision vehicle changed lanes to the left. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. This pushed V2 forward where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3. V1 traveled to the left after the impact with V2. The front of V4 then impacted the rear of V2. This pushed V2 forward and to the right where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3 a second time. V3, after the impact with V4, departed the road to the right where the front of V3 impacted a tree. After the impact with the tree V3 re-entered the roadway coming to rest facing north.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 3 lane roadway. V2 was traveling north east in the #3 lane of a 4 lane roadway. Both vehicles entered an intersection. V2 turned left to travel north. V1 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane roadway with an unprotected median, in lane 1. Within the roadway, the front of V1 contacted a deer. V1 came to rest on the shoulder of the roadway, facing northbound.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided three lane road in lane two, waiting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling north on the same non-physically divided three lane road in lane one. V1 was traveling north west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the left road side. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a guardrail end. V1 drove over the guardrail and came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 continued forward striking a tree with its left side plane and came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane roadway. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 continued forward and northerly where V1 departed the roadway to the left. V2 was pushed forward and to the right, departed the roadway to the right and coming to rest facing southeast on the south curb.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway, and was negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound on lane 3 of a 4 lane, one way roadway with both left and right  turn lanes, approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching a curve in the roadway to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was making a left turn from a one lane, one way, crossing roadway passing through the intersection with a six lane median divided roadway. V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching a T intersection. V1 skidded across the intersecting roadway, departed the south side of the roadway, and struck a fence with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest off the roadway, south of the fence, heading south.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway and struck a bridge edge with its undercarriage. V1 came to rest partially off the east side of the roadway heading east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest in lane one, on a two-lane, two-way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front plane contacted a guardrail end. Upon impact vehicle 1 continued forward and came to final rest on the shoulder facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided two lane roadway exiting an off ramp, negotiating a left curve. V1 was traveling north on a two lane one way road in lane one behind V2. Due to traffic ahead, V2 stopped and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane one facing north.

V1 and V2 were approaching an intersection while traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road with V2 leading V1. V2 came to rest on the eastern leg of the intersection heading east.
V1 and V2 were traveling south on the exit ramp from the interstate. V2 stopped for traffic. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north bound on a two lane, non-divided roadway when V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1's undercarriage impacted the ground. V1 entered a ditch, where its right plane impacted a mail box post. V1 crossed over a driveway, where its frontal plane impacted the ditch and a second mailbox post. V1 then crossed a second driveway, where it impacted an ornamental fence with its right plane, and a second ornamental fence with its frontal plane before coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a western direction, negotiating a curve to the right on a two lane, non-divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted an embankment. V1 traveled up the embankment, where it rolled one quarter turn onto its right side. V1 came to final rest on its right side on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V2 came to rest facing northwest in the westbound travel lane.

V1 was traveling south in lane 4 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and its front plane contacted a guardrail face. V2 came to rest against the guardrail facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right.  V1 tripped and rolled over two quarter-turns to the right.  V1 came to rest on its roof, off the road to the right, facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted 11 trees.  V1 came to rest off the road to the left, facing west near the final tree impact..

V1 was travelling on a 2 lane, non-physically undivided roadway heading east. V1 was stopped at a 4 way intersection with intent to turn left into the northbound lane. V1 entered the intersection. V1 came to final rest facing a northeasterly direction against the pole.

V1 was traveling southwest in 1 on a 4-lane two-way roadway. V1 contacted an unknown object with an unknown plane of vehicle. V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the road on the right side. The back of V1 contacted a metal fence and came to rest off the road facing east.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection making a left turn. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of V1 causing damage. V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the road facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the roadway. V1 moved to its right, and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a north eastern direction on a two lane roadway negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it's frontal plane impacted a utility pole and a tree, and its left plane impacted a second utility pole. V1 came to final rest off from the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest in a residential area on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway in lane one. Vehicles 2 and 3 were legally parked along the right side of the roadway. As Vehicle 1 continued to rotate it struck the left side of Vehicle 3. Vehicle 1 then tripped and rolled left 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top facing south. V2 and V3 came to rest at impact area.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, two way, non-divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree with its right side plane. V1 continued forward and contacted seven more trees with its front plane before coming to final rest, off of the roadway, to the right.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway before returning to the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 then departed the left side of the road impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then overturned right side leading three quarter turns onto its left side before rolling back onto its top coming to final rest in the ditch facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two-way undivided roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 2 and vehicle 3 were on the same roadway stopped in lane number 2 ahead of vehicle 1. The front of vehicle 1 made contact with the back of vehicle 2. The front of vehicle 2 then contacted the back of vehicle 3. All vehicles came to final rest in lane number 2 facing east.

V1 & V2 were both traveling south in lane three of a four lane, positively divided roadway. V2 then slowed due to traffic ahead, and V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. V1 then departed the left side of the roadway and came to final rest in the grass median. V2 came to final rest in lane three.

V1 was traveling south on a undivided two lane road in lane one. V1 began to drift off the west edge of the road and the driver overcorrected by steering left. V1 began to travel across the northbound lanes and departed the east road edge. The front of V1 impacted a block wall and gate. V1 continued south and the front of V1 impacted another block wall/gate post. V1 came to rest in front of a driveway facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling north traveling the wrong way on a one way, one lane roadway, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling west following a one way, one lane roadway, approaching the same four way intersection. V3 was approaching the same intersection, traveling south, following a two way, two lane road.
