V1 was traveling north in lane one of a four-lane, positively divided roadway, and was passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane four on the same roadway, and was making a left turn at the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the northwest corner of the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane two on a four lane, two way, median divided roadway. V1 was trailing V2. V2 began to slow to turn left into a paved median crossover. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 came to a final rest on the roadway. V2 came to a final rest on the paved median crossover.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, attempting to crossover the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 rotated in a counter clockwise direction and came to a final rest on the paved shoulder of the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction. V2 departed the right side of the roadway and struck a ditch with its front plane. V2 came to a final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in the first of two travel lanes of a four lane grass median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a guardrail end with its frontal plane. V1 rode up the guardrail and flipped into a left side leading rollover.  V1 came to rest on its left side on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest on a two-way, two-lane divided highway in lane two. Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast on the other side of the same highway in lane one. Vehicle #3 was traveling southeast on the same highway in lane two. V1 departed its lane to the left and crossed the grassy median before entering the other side of the highway. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. The front plane of V3 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 departed the road to the west. The front plane of V1 contacted a guardrail. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the road to the west. The back plane of V2 contacted the guardrail, then the left plane of V2 contacted the guard rail. V1 and V2 came to rest off road to the west. V3 crossed the grassy median and came to rest on the other side of the highway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles enter the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and came to rest on the grass roadside facing northeast. V2 came to rest in the northeast corner of the intersection facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was north on a 4 lane divided interstate highway with a dirt median, concrete barrier, in lane 4. Vehicle 1 lost control on the wet road and slid off the roadway rotating counter-clockwise where the front of vehicle 1 contacted the concrete barrier. Vehicle 1 then tripped over and rolled to the right 2 quarter turns coming to rest on its roof, facing west straddling the median and number 4 lane.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling in lane 1 of a 4 lane physically divided roadway. All vehicles were within an interchange area. V2 had forward momentum and and V3 was stopped. V1's front contacted the back of V2. V2's front then contacted V3's back. All vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a five lane, two way roadway in lane one. V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two way roadway. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest in the intersection after impact. V2 came to final rest facing northeast of roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane 3 on a three lane, one-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 on a two lane, one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the southwest corner of the intersection and the its front contacted a metal fence. V1 came to rest against the fence facing southwest. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane non-physically divided roadway traveling in the lane 1 position approaching a sign controlled intersection to make a left turn.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway negotiating a left hand curve passing through.  After stopping, Vehicle 1 entered the intersection initiating a left turn.  The left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  After impact Vehicle 2 passed through the intersection coming to final rest facing west. Vehicle 1 began to spin counter clockwise departing the roadway coming to final rest facing west after striking a chain link fence.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection with the intent of passing through.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection with the intent of passing through.  After stopping, Vehicle 1 began to enter the intersection at the same time Vehicle 2 was passing through.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise after impact coming to final rest in the middle of the intersection facing southeast.  Vehicle 2 passed through the intersection after impact and came to final rest facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 2 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the right front side of V2, due to impact both vehicles rotated in away from each other and the left side of V1 contacted the right rear side of V2. V1 and V2 both  came to rest facing north west at the northwest corner of the intersection.

V1 was pulling a trailer and traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 swerved left, crossing the center line, to avoid a animal in the roadway. V1 then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 then swerved right back onto the roadway, crossing back over the center line and departed the right side of the roadway. V1 then swerved back onto the roadway and crossed the center line and then departed the left side of the roadway striking a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest heading southeast, with the trailer still attached.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V1 struck the frontal plane of V2. V1 came to rest heading southeast in the northbound lane. V2 came to rest heading north in the northbound lane.

V1 was traveling in a north eastern direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional dirt road. V1 was negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the road to the right, where its frontal plane impacted two trees. V1 came to final rest off the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a undivided two lane road in lane one, negotiating a left curve. For an unknown reason V1 drifted towards the east road edge and and back towards the roadway, where V1 began to lose control. V1 then swerved off the east roadway and the front of V1 impacted a rock wall/embankment. After the impact V1 began to roll left four quarter turns and came to rest on its wheels, within the eastbound lanes facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway. V3 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway behind V2. For unknown reasons, V1 crossed into the northbound lane where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. After the impact with V2, V1 continued in the northbound lane where the front of V1 impacted the front of V3. V3 continued off of the roadway backwards where the rear of V3 impacted a tree. V1 came to rest in the northbound lane facing south. V2 came to rest in the northbound lane facing south. V3 came to rest off of the roadway against a tree facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane divided highway in lane one, behind V2. V2 was stopped in lane one of a two lane divided highway in front of V1. V1 was unable to stop and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 and V2 both came to rest in lane one facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway. V2 was also traveling in lane 1 on the same roadway when the front end of V1 contacted the rear end of V2. Both vehicles remained in lane 1 when reaching their final rest points facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, non-divided roadway entering a sign controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles rotated side slapping in the intersection. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2 lane undivided private driveway, preparing to turn left. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 5 lane undivided roadway, approaching the private driveway. V1 began to turn left when the left side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V2 continued forward and V1 rolled right 2-quarter turns and came to rest on the roadway on its top facing northwest. V2 continued east uncontrolled and departed the lane to the right and then departed the roadway to the right where the front of V2 impacted a tree. V2 came to rest facing east off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane, curbed divided roadway, approaching an intersection.V2 was traveling west on a three lane, curb divided roadway, approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1 and slowed to turn at an intersection. V1 departed it's lane to the left to pass V2. During the intersection the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 departed the roadway to the southwest of the intersection. The front right tire impacted a metal pipe culvert and V1 came to rest facing southwest. V2 also departed the roadway to the southwest of the intersection and came to rest facing west.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane, grass median divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, private driveway. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching the private driveway. In the roadway, the left of V1 contacted the front of V2 as V1 attempted to exit the driveway and turn left. Then the left of V1 contacted the right of V2 as the vehicles both moved southwest. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a T intersection.  V2 was traveling east on the intersecting roadway approaching the same intersection.  As V1 turned right at the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.  V1 rotated clockwise to final rest off the south road edge facing southeast.  V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway entering a right hand curve, crossing over into the oncoming travel lane. Vehicle 1 attempted to return into its travel lane and departed the roadway to the right contacting a tree road with its front plane. V1 rotated clockwise and its left side contacted an unknown object where V1 came to rest facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing northwest. V2 continued straight and came to rest facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north west on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching a 3 way intersection with the intent to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front right corner of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 coming to rest in the intersection facing north. After impact V2 departed roadway left side coming to rest facing north east.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way roadway, passing through a four leg intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. The impact caused V2 to rotate counterclockwise, V1's left plane contacted V2's right plane. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing southbound. V2 came to final rest off roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling westbound, on a three lane, two way roadway crossing through the intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound, making a left turn attempting to travel northeast through the same intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound, in lane one, of a three lane roadway with a two way left turn lane. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 began to go down an embankment where it tripped over and began to roll to the left. During the rollover, V1 contacted a fence with its left side, where it came to final rest.

V2 was traveling east on an undivided two way roadway attempting to crossover an intersection. V1 was traveling north on a one way roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the east leg of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same two lane, two way roadway. While V1 attempted to turn left into a driveway, the right plane of V1 impacted the front of V2. After impact, V1 rolled one quarter turn to the left and came to final rest on its left side in the roadway, facing north. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided left curved roadway.  A deer ran out in front of V1 from the south side of the road.  V1 steered right to avoid the deer and departed the roadway on the right. The front of V1 impacted a ditch and then the right front tire impacted a rock. V1 continued forward, reentering the roadway, coming to final rest in the west bound lane facing southwest.

V1 was traveling in a north eastern direction on a two lane roadway negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a ditch, and its left plane impacted debris/fallen branch. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the third of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the second lane of the same roadway. V1 departed its lane on the right side and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and came to rest. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in in lane 3 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the left and entered the grass median. The right side of V1 contacted a tree two separate times. The front of V1 contacted a tree and the left side of V1 contacted a tree. V1 returned to the roadway at the intersection. V1 then departed the intersection on the northeast corner where its left front tire contacted the curb then the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to rest partially off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 continued and the frontal plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was heading south west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection crossing paths with V2. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane two of a two lane roadway with median. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the left. The right side of Vehicle 1 contacted a tree, rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the southbound roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a three-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the same lane on the same roadway in front of Vehicle 1. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear of Vehicle 2. Vehicle did not stop. Vehicle 2 came to final rest within the intersection facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, positively divided highway, in the south bound lane. A deer entered the roadway from the left. The front of V1 impacted the deer before coming to final rest on the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling eastbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane 2 of a 3 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in lane 3 of an 4 lane roadway. V1 entered the southbound roadway attempting a left turn. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. In an attempt to avoid an unknown object in the roadway, V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 struck a fence with its front plane and continued forward along the fence striking it with its left, right, and top side plane. V1 continued forward and came to a final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the right. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left, attempting to overtake a non-contacted vehicle. V1 lost control on the curve and began to skid longitudinally departing the roadway to the left. The left side of V1 impacted a sign. Continuing forward, V1 began to reenter the roadway, it went into a roll with its left side leading. V1 rolled a total of 4 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its wheels, on the shoulder, facing south.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 failed to negotiate a left curve departing the right side of the road impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then fell further into the ditch impacting the rear plane causing damage and coming to final rest in the ditch at the initial point of impact facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 departed its left lane line as V2 departed its left lane line and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 then continued off the north side of the roadway coming to final rest facing northwest. V2 continued eastward crossing over the left side of the travel lane then the north side of the road coming to final rest on the north roadside facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south on a curved left, two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a utility pole, this sheered the pole off and the pole contacted the left windshield and windshield header. V1 rotated counterclockwise and rolled over 5 quarter turns before coming to rest on its right side.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching a sign controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection as V1. In the intersection the left side of V1 made contact with the front of V2. V1 rotated in a clockwise direction and came to a final rest in the roadway facing west. V2 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and came to a final rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. As the vehicles passed each other, left plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 continued forward and its front made contact with the left side of V2. V1 came to a final rest on the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a counter clockwise direction and came to a final rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a six lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and V2 rotated counter-clockwise. V1 rolled right 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top in the north bound lane facing southeast. During the rollover, the right side of V2 contacted the undercarriage of V1. V2 came to rest in the northbound lane facing south.

V1,V2, and V3 were traveling southbound on a two lane, positively divided roadway in lane two. V3 was traveling ahead of V1, and V2 was traveling behind V1. V3 slowed due to traffic ahead, and the front of V1 impacted the back of V3. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V1. V1 and V3 departed the roadway to the left and came to rest in the grassy median facing southbound. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest partially in lane one and lane two, facing southeast.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northeast on a five-lane road. V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one ahead of V1. V1 attempted to pass the traffic in its lane by entering lane one. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right shoulder. The right of V1 contacted left of V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the right where its lower front bumper contacted a cement driveway the contacted an embankment of a yard. V1 came to rest in the yard facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west in lane three of a three-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane three of the same roadway, ahead of V1. V2 began to decelerate due to traffic ahead. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to impact.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, attempting a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection with the intention to turn right. V1 departed it's travel lane to the left and V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest close to impact on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a divided roadway with two lanes going west and one lane going east, in lane two of two, passing by an entrance to a shopping mall. V2 was traveling east in lane two of  a three-lane, two-way road. V2 turned left across the path of V1 and the front of V1 impacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right. A deer entered the road from the left and impacted the left plane of V1 and the windshield area before being thrown over the vehicle. V1 came to rest on the southbound shoulder facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, grass median divided roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the right, then departed the roadway to the right. V1 returned to the roadway and then departed the roadway to the left.  V1 continued off the roadway, and the front contacted an embankment. V1 Then rolled end over end and landing back on its wheels, before V1 came to final rest off the roadway and caught fire.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane business drive intending to turn left at a 2-lane intersecting roadway. V1 turned left at the intersection then departed the right road edge where its front plane then undercarriage contacted a ditch. V1 came to rest in the ditch facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of an undivided two-lane roadway, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the roadway to the left. V1 entered a ditch and its front plane contacted a culvert. V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest partially on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a undivided two-lane roadway, crossing over an intersection with a stop sign in the median break. V2 was negotiating a right curve while in lane two of a five-lane divided roadway, approaching the intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to impact on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1's right wheels departed the right road edge. The driver over steered left and went into a counter clockwise rotation. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1 tripped and rolled right four quarter turns and came to rest on its wheels off the left road edge.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane roadway, in lane two, and approaching a private driveway. V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway, in lane two and approaching the same private driveway. V1 initiated a left turn. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to final rest within the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both in an interchange area, headed westbound, while negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was stopped in the roadway. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Then the right of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 proceeded off the roadway to the north west section of the intersection, and the front of V1 contacted a guywire. V1 came to final rest off the roadway, and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a three lane, roadway in lane three approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a three lane, roadway in lane two. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. In the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and the right front tire impacted the raised curb. V1 departed the roadway to the left and impacted a road sign with its front. V1 then impacted a tree with its left side and came to rest against the tree facing south. V2 rotated clockwise and impacted a raised curb with its left rear tire. V2 came to rest against the curb facing west.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the lane line to the left and continued off the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued forward across the sidewalk where the front of V1 impacted a second curb. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a pole. The pole was severed from the ground and the front V1 impacted a fire hydrant. V1 came to rest facing westerly against the fire hydrant off the south roadway.

V2 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way non-divided roadway approaching a sign controlled 3-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north on a five-lane (with center turn lane), two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection and attempted to turn left. In the intersection, the Front of V2 contacted the left rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on an undivided two-way road in lane one, V1 veered to the northbound lane and off the east road edge, impacting a ditch and rolling over right side leading, two quarter turns before coming to rest on its roof facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one, negotiating a curve. V1 was unable to navigate the curve and lost control, rotating in a clockwise direction. V1 departed the south road edge and continued along an embankment where V1 began to roll left. While rolling, the undercarriage of V1 impacted a fence then the top of V1 impacted a fence. After completing 6 quarter turns, V1 came to rest on it's roof in a horse corral facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a one lane highway negotiating a left curve. V1 was unable to navigate the curve and departed the west road edge where the front right of V1 impacted a utility marker. V1 continued off the roadway and up an embankment where the rear undercarriage impacted the embankment. V1 continued off the roadway and the front right impacted a freeway sign post. V1 then rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder and the front plane of V1 contacted the animal in the roadway. V1 traveled a short distance where it came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 2 of a 4 lane roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in lane 2 of the 4 lane roadway. V1 turned and started to make a U-turn. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.  V1 then rolled over two quarter turns to the left, coming to rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two-way, two lane road approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling southeast on a two-way, two lane road approaching the same four way intersection. In the middle of the mentioned intersection, the right of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise while V2 continued forward. While rotating, the right of V1 then impacted the left of V2. V2 departed the roadway to the right and impacted a non-fixed sign with it's frontal plane. Portions of the sign then impacted the right plane of V2. V2 re-entered the southern leg of the intersection from the right and departed this roadway on the left. V2 came to final rest facing west in a marsh. V1 continued traveling east along the edge of the roadway. V1 came to final rest at the edge of the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the middle of the intersection facing west. V2 traveled west out of the intersection coming to final rest facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 5 lane, two-way not physically divided roadway in lane number 3, intending to turn left into a private drive. Vehicle 2 was traveling south [on the same road] in lane number 1. Vehicle 3 was facing east in the private drive in lane number 1. Vehicle 1 began to turn left, and the right side of vehicle 1 and vehicle 2's front made contact with each other. After initial contact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and vehicle 1's left side made contact with vehicle 3's front. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing northwest in the private drive. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing northeast in between lanes and number 1 and 2. Vehicle 3 came to final rest facing east.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane, one-way exit lane, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a stop sign. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a wrong way sign. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a bridge rail. V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a three lane roadway attempting a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast negotiating a right curve in lane two of a six lane roadway approaching the intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and its front plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south. Vehicle #2 was traveling west on an intersecting roadway. V1 began to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 then rolled over 8 quarter turns right side leading. V1 came to rest in the construction area facing west.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two way undivided traffic way. V1 departed right lane and continued to depart roadway on the right side. V1 struck an embankment at the base of a tree and rolled one quarter turn onto it's right plane. V1 partially skid down the shoulder and partially down southbound travel lane before making a reverse quarter turn back onto its wheels. The vehicle came to final rest partially in original travel lane and partially off the roadway.

Vehicles 2 and 4 were traveling west on a 4 lane, two way non-physically divided roadway. V2 in lane 1 pulling a flatbed trailer. V4 in lane 2. V2 was just ahead of V4. Vehicles 1 and 3 were traveling east on the same roadway, Vehicle 1 in lane 1 of the west bound lanes and Vehicle 3 in lane 2. Vehicle 2 then changed to lane 2. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2's trailer. Due to impact V2's trailer became disconnected and entered the east bound lane 2. The front of V3 contacted the left side of V2's disconnected trailer. V3 came to final rest facing south east in both east bound lanes. V2 continued west after impact and pulled off the roadway in a nearby parking lot.   After impact with the trailer V1 continued east rotating clockwise. The left front side of V1 contacted the front right of V4. Due to impact with V4, V1 quickly yawed clockwise doing 2 360 degree turns coming to rest facing south in lane 1 of the west bound lanes. V4 came to rest in lane 2 of east and west bound lanes facing west.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 3 lane, physically divided, roadway and in lane 1. V1 departed its lane to the right and then the roadway to the right.V1's front contacted a guardrail end. V1 then rotated clockwise and came to rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north and crossing through a four leg intersection from a stopped position on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, passing through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the right side plane of the towed unit of V1. Upon impact V2 rotated clockwise and struck the right side plane of the towed unit again with its frontal plane. V2 came to rest in the intersection heading north.  V1 came to final rest north of the intersection on the shoulder of the northbound lane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane two of a five lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way physically undivided roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right. V1 began a clockwise rotation, before vehicle 1 began to rollover on the left side leading. The top of Vehicle 1 contacted a utility pole during the roll event. Vehicle 1 completed 3 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its right side facing east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two of a three lane roadway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north lane three of a four lane, undivided roadway turning left at an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest.

All 3 vehicles were traveling south in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V3 stopped at the intersection. V2 stopped behind V3. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 pushing the front of V2 into the back of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the area of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane 3 on a 4 lane roadway approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 5 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time and as V1 began to turn left, the front of V1contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing northeast. V2 continued forward and came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was entering into a 4 lane physically divided roadway from the west.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound in the same 4 lane physically divided roadway in the left hand turn lane which was lane position 3.  Vehicles 3 and 4 were in same physically divided roadway stopped for a traffic light in the lane 2 position.  As Vehicle 1 traveled east into the intersection it crossed two lanes of traffic making impact with the right rear plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise after impact coming to final rest facing southeast.  Vehicle 2 continued traveling south bouncing slightly off the median curb and was deflected into Vehicle 3 stopped in traffic.  The right front plane of Vehicle 2 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 3.  Vehicle 2 continued in its path of travel coming to final rest at impact with Vehicle 4's rear plane.  It was the front plane of V2 making contact with the rear plane of V4 facing south at final rest.  Vehicle 3 was pushed slightly forward into the rear plane of Vehicle

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 5 lane, two- way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided private drive approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on the east side on the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a fence with its frontal plane. V1 continued south, becoming entangled with the fence, and received wrap-around type damage to the right and left sides.  V1 came to rest facing northwest.

V1 was heading east on a two-lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading south on an intersecting three-lane undivided roadway. V1 entered the intersection to turn left. V2 entered the intersection to continue on its initial path of travel. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. Impact forces redirected the rear of V2 to the left. During this redirection, V2 completed one quarter turn and came to final rest on its left side near the initial point of impact. V1 came to rest near impact as well.

V1 was traveling south and negotiating a left curve on a rural roadway. V2 was traveling north and negotiating a right curve on the same rural roadway. V1 front made contact with V2 front, V1 then departed the right side of the roadway striking a tree with its frontal plane. V2 continued on, and did not stop. V1 came to final rest near the impact with the tree heading south.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 4-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 4-lane, one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southwest. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south bound on a two lane, non-divided roadway. V2 was legally parked on the west side of the same roadway facing south. V3 was traveling north bound on the same roadway approaching V1 and V2. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted the rear plane of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise, returned to the roadway, crossing into the north bound lane, where its right plane impacted the left side of V3. V1 came to final rest in the south bound lane, facing northeast. V2 came to final rest partially blocking the south bound lane. V3 came to final rest in the north bound lane.
V1 was traveling south bound on a two lane divided roadway, when a deer entered the lane of travel. V1's frontal plane impacted the animal. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling South-east negotiating a left curve in lane 1 of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling North-west in lane 1 of the same roadway. V1 departed its lane left where the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise coming to final rest in the roadway facing north. V2 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane divided roadway in lane three. V1 departed two travel lanes to the left and then the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier. V1 was redirected to its right where it came to final rest in lane two facing generally southeast.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right hand (west) side of the roadway, and V1 struck the animal in the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a interstate on-ramp, merging into the roadway. V2 was traveling east in lane three of the interstate. V1 merged onto the interstate and then changed lanes into lane three. V1's left plane contacted V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to final rest just past impact on the roadway.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the left side of the travel lane, then departed the left side of the roadway impacting a utility marker then a utility pole with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then rotated clockwise sliding down a ditch coming to final rest facing south.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling in a ditch and overturned right side leading one quarter turn coming to final rest on the right side in the ditch facing west.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction, on a winding, two lane, non divided roadway with a positive grade. The roadway is bordered on the right side by a steep positive grade embankment, and to the left side by a small creek. A large rock fell down the embankment from the right. V1 traveled over the rock where the rock contacted the undercarriage. The undercarriage of the trailer also contacted the rock. A portion of the trailer then contacted the back of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway a short distance from impact.

V1 was traveling in a north western direction on a two lane, non-divided roadway while negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right,where it struck a tree with its frontal plane, and its right plane. V1 continued forward, where it struck a tree with its left plane causing the vehicle to rotate counter clockwise. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway, facing west bound.
V1 was eastbound on a four lane, two way, roadway divided by a grass median. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the south side of the roadway facing east.

V1 was westbound on a four lane, two way, roadway divided by a grass median. The front of V1 contacted a tire in the road causing damage to the front end. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the road facing west.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern roadside and in an attempt to avoid the deer in the roadway V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway. V1 then contacted a rock wall with its frontal plane. V1 continued off of the roadway contacting an unknown object with its frontal plane before contacting the rock wall again with its right side plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway when it approached a group of cows in the road. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a cow. Subsequently, the cow struck the left side of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 made a left turn at the intersection to make a u-turn.  V1 re-entered the roadway and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling in lane two of a five-lane roadway, non-divided roadway entering a light controlled four-legged intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane three of a five lane roadway, non-divided roadway attempting to turn left at the intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road that curved slightly to the left with a negative grade. V1 departed the right side of the road where its left front tire impacted a curb and then drove up and over a driveway. The undercarriage of V1 then impacted an embankment and its left side impacted a small pole. V1 reentered the roadway and crossed both lanes before departing the left side of the road and impacting a tree with its front plane. V1 came to rest at the point of final impact, heading west.

V2 was leading V1 while traveling east in lane two on a divided roadway with three lanes going east and three lanes going west. V2 stopped at the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at point of impact heading east.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact, still facing east.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane three of a four-lane divided interstate. V2 was ahead of V1. V2 began to slow for traffic ahead when the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in their original lane facing east.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane two. V1 began changing lanes from lane one to lane two, while changing lanes the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 then rotated counter-clockwise and rolled right 3-quarter turns and came to rest on its left side facing northwest on the road.  V2 rotated counter-clockwise as it departed the left road edge into the grass median where it rolled right 8-quarter turns and came to rest on it wheels facing northwest in the median.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane two-way roadway. V2 was turning left out of a two-way alley access. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northwest. V2 came to final rest in across the roadway facing south.

V1 was travelling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V2 was stopped in traffic due to a controlled intersection ahead facing east in the same lane as V1. The front left corner of V1 collided with the right rear corner of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the eastbound lane facing east.

V1 was traveling on an on-ramp on a three lane divided highway. V2 was traveling on an on-ramp on a three lane divided highway in front of V1. Due to traffic ahead, the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued across the northbound lanes and came to rest in the center median facing a northwesterly direction. V2 came to rest on the east shoulder facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane undivided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one stopped at a stop sign. V1 drove into the westbound lane to pass a vehicle in front and then drove back into lane two as it entered the intersection. As V2 entered the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. After impact, the right side of V1 impacted the left rear of V2. V1 came to rest in the middle of the intersection in lane one of the westbound lanes facing north. V2 came to rest on the north side of the intersection in lane one of the northbound lane facing north.

V1 was traveling east on an undivided two lane road in lane one. Due to a pig on the road, the front of V1 impacted the pig. V1 began to lose control and departed the south road edge. V1 began to roll right nine quarter turns, before impacting a cable fence. V1 came to rest on the passenger side facing a easterly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway. A non-contact vehicle was overtaking V1 on the left. V1 steered right, departed the right curb edge and its front plane contacted a wooden utility pole. V1 came to rest partially off the road facing west.

V1 was traveling west in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. The roadway became a divided roadway with a center median as V1 traveled forward. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 traveled in a southerly direction where the front of V1 impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter-clockwise after impacting the tree and came to rest facing southerly on the center median, against the tree.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. V1 continued straight into the intersection. V2 was turning left in the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 continued traveling and never stopped at the scene. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing northerly.

V1 was traveling east on a one way trafficway in lane 1 (of one lane). V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway ahead of V1 in lane 1. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2, and V1 caught fire. V2 then departed the road on the right and descended an embankment where its front end contacted a tree. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction on the right shoulder. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing an easterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of five lanes). V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in lane 2 (of five lanes). V1 departed its lane on the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 continued in a southerly direction and began to rotate clockwise until it departed the roadway on the right and its front end contacted a guardrail. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northwesterly direction across lanes 1 and 2. V2 was driven to lane 4 and stopped.

V2 and V1 were traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road that curved slightly to the right. V2 stopped for traffic and the front of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact heading south.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane two of a four-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling south in lane two of the same road. V3 was waiting in a driveway heading east waiting to enter traffic from a driveway. V1 turned left, across the path of V2. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V2 rotated clockwise and  came to rest in the southbound lanes facing west. V1 rotated clockwise and its left plane impacted the front of V3. V1 came to rest in the south bound lanes facing north. V3 came to rest at points of impact facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 continued straight through the intersection, V2 turned left and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, non-divided roadway and drifted to the right side of the roadway prior to the driver steering to the left as a corrective measure. V1 initiated a counter-clockwise yaw and traversed the centerlines. The frontal plane impacted a rock retaining wall (Event 1) The right rear rim gouged the roadway surface (Event 2) just prior to its front plane impacting a fence (Event 3). The right side plane impacted and fractured a utility pole (Event 4) as the right rear tire impacted the curb (Event 5). V1 initiated a two-quarter turn rollover sequence (Event 6), leading with its right side. During the rollover, the frontal plane impacted a small tree (Event 7). V1 came to rest on its roof and facing southwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a undivided six lane road in lane two, V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 was stopped and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane two facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 lost control and departed the right hand (south) side of the roadway contacting a mailbox post with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward making contact with an embankment and a utility pole with its front plane. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction overturning, with its left side leading, two quarter turns before coming to a final rest partially off of the roadway on its top plane.

V1 was traveling east on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching a stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling north, on a median divided roadway, with two lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right side plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 continued forward with V1 rotating in a counter clockwise direction and V2 rotating in a clockwise direction. Both V1 and V2 came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway in lane one.  V2 was legally parked against the right curb facing north on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  Both vehicles moved north to final rest off the right road edge facing northeast.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling in the westbound lane of a two lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was stopped in the travel lane due to road construction. The front plane of vehicle 1 contacted the back plane of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was north on a 3 lane, interstate highway with a positive barrier.  V1 was in lane one as it came over an overpass.  On the decline side, V1 ran over a large, rolled up tarp that dropped across the travel lane. This caused damage to the front and right front tire. V1 came to rest in the right emergency lane.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane roadway approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane intersecting roadway.  V3 was stopped at the same intersection facing southwest.  V1 and V2 both entered the intersection. The front of V1 struck the left side of V2. Subsequently, V2 continued off the roadway at the east corner and struck a road sign with its right plane.  V2 reentered the roadway and struck its left side struck the left of V3. All three vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the road to the left. V1's front plane contacted a tree and V1 rotated clockwise. V1's left plane contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off the road to the south.

V1 was traveling northeast bound, on a 3 lane and physically divided roadway, in lane one. V1 went off of the roadway to the right. V1's front contacted an embankment. V1 then entered the access road where it tripped over and rolled to the right 5 times before coming to final rest, partially on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southbound on a 2 lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left.  V1 departed it's lane line to the left. V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane roadway in the southbound lane.  V1 decelerated and intitiated a left turn attempting to enter into a private driveway.  V2 was traveling south on the same roadway behind V1 in the southbound lane and struck V1 with the front plane.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.  V1 driver was ejected.

V1 was traveling south bound on a two lane, non-divided roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the road to the left to avoid an animal. V1 returned the road, crossing both lanes of travel, where it departed the road to the right. V1's frontal plane impacted the the embankment on the right, V1 traveled up the embankment, and rolled left side leaning two quarter turns, coming to final rest on its roof on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway.  V1 departed the left road edge and impacted an embankment with its left front corner.  V1 re-entered the roadway then traveled back into the center median where V1 rotated counter-clockwise then tripped and rolled right 4-quarter turns and came to rest in the median facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching a curve. V1 was unable to navigate the curve and departed the east road edge where the front of V1 impacted an embankment. V1 continued up and along the embankment where the left side of V1 impacted the ground, then continued down the embankment where the right side of V1 impacted the embankment. V1 re-entered the roadway where the front of V1 impacted the ground then rotated counter clockwise where V1 came to rest in between both lanes facing a northeasterly direction.

V1 was travelling South East in Lane 1 of a 2 way, undivided roadway.  V1 left the right side of the roadway.  The front plane of V1 contacted a roadside reflector.  V1 reentered the roadway before crossing both lanes of travel and leaving the left side of the road.  The front plane of V1 struck the dirt embankment parallel to the roadway.  V1 began to rollover leading with its right side.  V1 completed 4 quarter rotations before coming to final rest on its wheels facing North East.

V1 and V2 were heading east while traveling on a one-lane, one-way on ramp that curved to the right. V2  was traveling ahead of V1 and slowed to initiate merging with traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest heading east on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south west on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway. An animal entered the roadway, V1 swerved to miss the animal and departed the right road edge. V1 went into a ditch and rolled to the left. V1 came to final rest off the roadway on its roof.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a physically divided two way road. V1 was traveling in lane one and V2 was traveling in lane two. V2 was attempting to change lanes, and left their original travel lane over the right hand side, causing V2's right plane to contact V1's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a three lane, two way roadway, approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two of a three lane, two way roadway approaching the same four leg intersection. While V1 was attempting a left turn in the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the intersection facing south. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the intersection facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on the intersecting 2-lane roadway. As V1 began to turn right at the intersection, its front plane contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the area of impact..

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a 4 lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 intended to continue straight through the intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left front side of V2. The Right of V1 then contacted the left of V2. V1  and V2 came to rest after impact in the intersection facing north west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contact a light pole.  V1 came to rest near impact, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, passing through a four leg intersection. V2 was proceeding south, from a stopped position, in the southbound lane, of the same four leg intersection. V1 swerved right into the southbound lane of the south side of the intersection, still heading east. Just south of the intersection the frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. V1 departed the southeast corner of the intersection in a counterclockwise yaw. V1 rolled, right side leading, one quarter turn, then rolled left side leading back onto its wheels after the roll was interrupted by an embankment. V1 came to final rest on its wheels heading northeast. V2 came to a controlled stop on the shoulder of the northbound lane, south of the intersection, heading south.

V1 was approaching a four leg intersection, traveling west, on a two way, six lane road with a right turn lane, and a center two way turn lane, in lane two. V1 departed its travel lane to the right and struck a light pole with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest at the point of impact heading west.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, positively divided roadway. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and its front plane contacted an embankment. After the initial impact, V1 then rotated in a counter-clockwise direction and its right side plane contacted the embankment. The vehicle then re-entered the roadway and came to final rest on the right shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a three lane, two-way roadway, and was negotiating a right curve in the road. V1 then departed its lane, crossed over the oncoming travel lane and turn lane, and departed the roadway on the left side. After departing the roadway, V1's front plane contacted a ditch, continued forward and then contacted a tree with its front plane. This contact caused the vehicle to tilt to the right, and the vehicle contacted another tree with its left undercarriage. V1 then then struck another tree with its right side plane and came to final rest with its right side plane against/into the last tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane three of an undivided, five lane roadway turning left at an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane one of a three lane, divided trafficway approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling north in lane two of a three lane roadway physically divided by a concrete barrier. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and the rear then the right side contacted the concrete barrier before coming to final rest facing northwest. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway to the right and rolled left 4-quarter turns. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on its wheels facing southeast after the left side contacted a fence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two of a five lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing south. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane, two way physically undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane one of a one lane driveway. Vehicle 2 entered the roadway; the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the roadway facing south. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V1 was negotiating a left curve of the roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, went down a ditch where the front plane collided with the opposite embankment of the ditch. V1 came to final rest facing westerly on its wheels in the ditch.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 stopped at a stop sign and began to turn left at the intersection to travel southbound. V2 entered the intersection. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing southeast in the intersection. V2 continued forward and to the right, coming to rest on the east curb line, north of the intersection, facing in a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling southeast on a five lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a concrete wall. V1 rotated clockwise and rolled rearward back onto the roadway. V1 came to final rest facing west in the intersection.

V2 traveling southbound in lane 2 of a 6 lane roadway.  V1 was traveling northbound in lane 5, the left turn lane, of this 7 lane roadway.   V1 attempted to turn left at this intersection. Vehicle 1 departed the lane and roadway on the left. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the curb. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the median facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, rural roadway. V1 departed the left travel lane and then the left roadway in a counterclockwise yaw. V1 then struck a culvert and a sign post with its right plane. V1 continued traveling off the roadway and rolled, right side leading, one quarter turn,striking a tree with the top plane during the roll.  V1 rotated counter clockwise and contacted a utility marker, and a utility pole, before coming to rest on its right side plane, partially in the eastbound lane and partially off the roadway, facing northeast.
