V1's left plane impacted V2's right plane. V1 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway in a driveway. V2 continued east bound to a safe place to turn around, and returned to the scene.

V1 was traveling in a south eastern direction on a two lane, non-divided roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right where its frontal plane impacted a guardrail. The left side of V1 then impacted the separating guardrail.  V1 then rolled passenger side leading 8 quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels.

V1 was traveling west following a two way, six lane roadway, in the third lane of traffic, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling east following a two way, six lane road, in the second lane, approaching the same intersection. As V1 was turning left in the mentioned intersection, the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway, V1 facing southwest and V2 facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same two way, two lane, undivided roadway as V1.  Both vehicles approached the same intersection where V1 attempted to make a left hand turn at the intersection and the right side plane of V1 contacted the front side plane of V2. V1 began to rotate in a clockwise direction and the front plane of V1 contacted and unknown plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane, then the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a culvert.  V1 tripped over and rolled 8 quarter-turns, right side leading, before coming to rest on its wheels in a ditch.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane two on a two-lane, divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left.  V1 re-entered the roadway and began to rotate clockwise.  V1 departed the roadway to the right.  V1 tripped and rolled left 3 quarter-turns.  During the rollover, the top of V1 contacted a wire fence.  V1 came to rest on its right side facing southwest, just south of the fence line.

V1 was traveling north east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway that was recently paved. V2 was in front of V1 traveling north east on the same roadway approaching in intersection. There were two vehicles that were not involved in the accident between V1 and V2. V1 attempted to pass all three vehicles. At that time V2 was making a left turn at the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V2 spun clockwise and came to final rest on the roadway. V1 continued departing the roadway to the left rotating 90 degrees clockwise. V1 contacted a utility pole with the left plane and came to final rest off the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 6 lane, two-way non physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 2 was stopped for traffic ahead of vehicle 1. The front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway in there original lanes.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway negotiating a curve to the right. Vehicle 1 departed the lane then the roadway on the left side. Vehicle 1 traveled down a ditch and the front plane struck a rock. The right rear undercarriage of V1 then impacted the embankment. Vehicle 1 continued forward and the front of V1 contacted a second rock. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing north in a field.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane three on a six lane, two way, physically divided trafficway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left. The left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the cable barrier and the front plane contacted a sign post. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was traveling north in lane No. 1 of an undivided two-lane roadway. V1 initiated a clockwise yaw as it departed the right side of the roadway. The left side plane impacted a tree, increasing its clockwise rotation. Vehicle 1 came to rest straddling the northeast road edge and facing northwest.

Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling NW on a two-lane divided road in lane two. V2 slowed for traffic ahead at an intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V1 came to rest on the road V2 came to rest on the left shoulder.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, undivided (two way traffic) roadway in lane one approaching a two way stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, undivided (two way traffic) roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest inside the intersection facing southeast. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest inside the intersection facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east on a undivided seven lane road in lane two. V2 was traveling on the same undivided seven lane road in lane one. As V2 was changing lanes to lane two, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 began to spin counter-clockwise towards the left turn lanes of the westbound lane, where it came to rest facing a westerly direction. V1 continued towards the westbound left turn lanes where it came to rest facing an easterly direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 1 lane median divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1 turned left and and departed the roadway to the left and vehicle 1's front made contact with a fence. After initial contact, V1 continued forward and came to final rest in the pool.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of an undivided, two-lane roadway. V1 drifted to the left, traversing the westbound lane before departing the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole guy wire (Event 1). The guy wire impact caused continuous contact damage along the left side plane and top surface of the trunk lid. V1 continued forward as its left side plane impacted the utility pole (Event 2). As the vehicle rotated counterclockwise, its right rear bumper corner contacted the roadway surface (Event 3). V1 came to rest upright, facing north and perpendicular in the westbound travel lane.

Vehicle 1 was south on a 4 lane, undivided roadway in lane 2 and approaching an intersection with a stop sign. Vehicle 2 was west on a 2 lane, undivided roadway in lane 1 and approaching the same the intersection. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection and the front of Vehicle 1 impacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to rest just south of the intersection on the west edge of the roadway, facing south. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and rolled to the left one quarter turn, coming to rest on its left side, facing east.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a three lane non-physically divided roadway. Both vehicles were traveling in lane onw towards an intersection. V2 began slowing down as they approached the intersection. The front plane of V1 to contacted the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 3-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in the same lane and stopped at the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest near the impact area.

V1 was traveling east in the third of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the fourth lane of the same roadway. V3 was traveling west in the third of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway. V1 attempted to change lanes to the left and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 began a counterclockwise yaw and contacted a raised curb with the right front wheel before crossing over the median, entering into the westbound lanes of travel. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V3 in the westbound lanes. V1 and V3 came to rest in the westbound lanes. V2 came to rest in the eastbound lanes.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling west, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection as V1. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated in a clockwise direction while V2 rotated in a counter clockwise direction. The left side of V1 made contact with the right side of V2. V1 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and departed the south side of the westbound roadway contacting a ditch with its front plane. V2 continue forward in a counter clockwise rotation and departed the south side of the westbound roadway contacting a ditch with its rear plane.  Both vehicles came to a final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling northbound, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection as V1 with a stop sign. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, undivided, roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the left and started a counter-clockwise yaw. Then right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 continued off the roadway to the left and the left side contacted a fire hydrant. V1 came to final rest off  the roadway and V2 on the roadway.

V1 was traveling Southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and continued off the road, V1 front plane contacted a culvert. V1 rotated clockwise, and came to rest, facing Northwest after impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of a five-lane divided roadway, passing through the same intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 continued west and came to final rest on the roadway. V2 departed the roadway to the right and came to final rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a embankment and V1 went airborne. V1 landed on its undercarriage then the front plane contacted a chain link fence were it came to rest.

V1 was negotiating a left curve traveling south in the first of four lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a fire hydrant. V1 continued south across an intersecting road and began to rotate clockwise. V1 rolled left six quarter turns coming to rest off the roadway on its roof.

V1 was traveling west on a 2 lane roadway stopped at a stop sign at an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 2 on a 4 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left as V2 was traveling straight and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing north. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 4 position approaching an intersection to make a left hand turn.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a 7 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 2 position approaching the same intersection to pass through.  Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The right side plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and Vehicle 2 rotated slightly counter clockwise.  The right rear plane of Vehicle 1 then made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east at the southeast corner of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest also facing east at the southeast corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an uncontrolled intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way, non- physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest facing southeast in the south east corner of the intersection. Due to impact V2 slid just south of the intersection. The rear of V2 contacted a mailbox before coming to rest facing south east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west bound in lane one of a three lane divided highway with a positive barrier. V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the right side rotating in a clockwise direction. The back of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane three of a five-lane non-divided road, approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane one of the same road approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 3 was stopped at the intersection, facing north in lane one of an undivided two lane street. V1 initiated a left turn a left turn in the intersection and the front of V2 contacted its right side. Subsequently, the left of V1 contacted the left side of V3. V3 rotated clockwise and its front contacted a street sign. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing southeast. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing southeast. V3 came to rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a guy wire. V1 then returned to the roadway where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling in a south eastern direction on a two lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway, with a negative grade, and a left curve. The road conditions at the time were ice/frost. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it impacted a road sign with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest down a small embankment on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, with a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest off the roadway heading west.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane roadway and approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing northeast. V2 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and its front plane contacted a curb. V2 came to rest partially on the sidewalk facing north.

V1 was traveling north following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, impacting a curb with both right side wheels.  V1 continued forward to reenter the roadway, coming to final rest in the left lane facing northwest.

V2 was heading east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway making a right turn onto a driveway. V1 and an unknown vehicle were following V2 on the same roadway. The unknown vehicle slowed while V2 was making the right turn. V1 swerved to the right to avoid the unknown vehicle. V1 departed the southern road edge and continued on. V2 entered the driveway and its frontal plane contacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on the driveway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 experienced a mechanical failure and the vehicle pulled to the right. V1 departed the right side of the road where its front plane impacted a utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest against the utility pole heading east.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the right while traveling northwest on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was a legally parked vehicle on the right side of the road heading northwest. V1 lost control due to snow covered roads and departed the lane to the left. V1 returned to its lane of travel and departed the right side of the road while rotating clockwise. The front undercarriage of V1 impacted an embankment and its left side impacted the rear of V2 twice. V1 came to rest partially off of the right side of the road heading northeast. V2 came to rest on the right side of the road heading northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 3 lane median divided roadway in lane number 2 approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 3 lane median divided intersection in lane number 2. Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's left side made contact with each other in the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling northwest in lane one of a three-lane roadway, with V2 ahead of V1. V2 stopped for traffic and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at impact.

V1 was traveling Northwest in Lane 2 on a 5-Lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling Southeast in Lane 3 began to make a left turn at the intersection, its right plane contacted the front plane of V2. Both V1 & V2 rotated counterclockwise, V1 facing Northwest, V2 facing East and came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling west on two lane, grass median divided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, three lane road. V1 departed the roadway to the right, striking an impact attenuator with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest at impact, on the side of the roadway, facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south west on a three lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching an intersection with the intent to pass through. Vehicle 2 was traveling north west on a two lane, one way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 stopped at the traffic light.  Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest just after impact still facing west in the intersection. Vehicle 2 after impact yawed 180 degrees in a clockwise rotation coming to rest in the same lane of travel facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection to make a left turn.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position with the intent of passing through the intersection.  Vehicle 3 was stopped in the left hand turn lane facing north.  As V1 made its turn, the right plane made contact with the front plane of V2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing south at the southern portion of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise after impact making contact front plane to front plane of Vehicle 3.  Final rest for V2 and V3 was at impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 at an intersection stopped at a stop sign with the intention to make a left turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling south west on a five lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection with the intent to pass through. Both vehicles entered the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 yawed counter- clockwise approximately 110 degrees coming to rest facing mostly north in lane 2 of the north/east bound lanes. V1 came to rest facing east straddling both north/east bound lanes.

V1 and V2 were both traveling westbound, in lane two, of a three lane roadway. Both vehicles were approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at the intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. V2 was shoved forward into the intersection, where it came to final rest. V1 then crossed all intersecting lanes before leaving the roadway. V1's front then contacted a bridge pillar, where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound while negotiating a curve to the right, in lane one, of a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling in the same direction, but stopped in the roadway, waiting to turn left into a private driveway. V3 was traveling westbound on the same roadway while negotiating a curve to the left. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. V2's left side then contacted V3's left side. V1 came to rest on the South shoulder. V2 came to rest on the north shoulder. V3 came to rest within the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in lane four of a four-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and entered the median.  The front of V1 contacted a snow drift in the median.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane, divided highway in lane three. V1 departed the roadway to the left where contacted a cable guardrail. V1 returned back the the roadway where it came to rest on the right shoulder.

Vehicle one was traveling west on a 1-lane divided roadway, stopped at an intersection. Vehicle two was traveling north in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway, approaching the same intersection. V1 turned left at the intersection as V2 continued straight and the left plane of V1 was contacted by the front plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as V2 continued forward and the left side of V1 was contacted by the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing west. V2 came to rest off road to the west.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 attempted to pass another vehicle before traveling off the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 impacted a tree causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated clockwise traveling down an embankment striking three more small trees with the left plane. V1 came to final rest near impact 2 & 3  and resting against point of impact 4 facing south.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane undivided (two-way traffic) road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one of the same road. V3 was stopped in lane two, waiting to turn left at the intersection. V1 changed lanes to the right. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 continued to drive and tried to move back into lane two. The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V3. All vehicles came to rest facing north. V1 was partially in lane one and two, V2 and V3 stayed in their original lanes of travel.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching a left  curve. V1 departed the right road edge where the front of V1 impacted a large boulder used as a traffic barrier. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest next to boulder facing a westerly direction.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling west in lane 2 on a 3-lane, divided roadway.  The front of  V2 contacted the back of V1's cargo unit.  V2 came to rest near impact, facing west. V1 was unaware of the impact and continued driving then returned after being flagged down.

V1 was traveling west on a five lane divided road with three west bound lanes and two east bound lanes in lane three, passing through an intersection. V1 departed the road to the left, traveled onto a median and impacted a concrete planter with its front plane. V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing north in the west bound lane.

V1 was traveling south on a undivided two way road in lane one. V1 drove of the right road edge and the front of V1 impacted a descending embankment. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction.

V1 was parked facing east on the south shoulder. V2 was traveling west in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 entered the roadway to make a u-turn. V1 began to make its turn left where the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing southwest in the eastbound lane. V2 continued forward and came to rest facing west in the westbound lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, median divided roadway in the second lane. Vehicle 2 and vehicle 3 were on the same roadway, stopped in the second lane ahead of vehicle 1. The front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. After initial contact, vehicle 2's front contacted the back of vehicle 3. All vehicles came to rest in there original lane.

V1 was traveling westbound in the third lane of a four lane divided highway. V1 departed the right side of the road and its front end struck a sign (events 1 and 2) .V1 continued to travel off the road where its left side struck two unknown objects (events 3 and 4). V1 came to final rest on a grass roadside.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 started to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right. The left side of V2 then impacted a barbed wire fence. V2 came to rest against the fence facing south. V1 came to a controlled rest east of the intersection facing east.

V1 and V2 were both were traveling northeast on a two lane, non-positively divided, roadway. V1 was in lane one and V2 was in lane two, when V1 departed its lane on the left side. V1's left side plane then contacted V2's front plane. This contact caused both vehicles to rotate in a counter-clockwise direction and depart the roadway on the left side. V1's front plane then contacted a tree, and V2's front plane contacted V1's back plane. V2's front plane then went under V1 and struck the back undercarriage of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest off of the roadway and in the median. V2 then caught on fire under the back of V1.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling southeast, on a median divided trafficway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. V1 entered the intersection while V2 was attempting a left hand turn. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1. V1 rotated in a counter clockwise direction and came to a final rest in the non-paved median of the roadway. V2 continued forward rotating in a clockwise direction and began a left side leading roll-over. V2 completed 4 quarter turns and landed on its wheels coming to a final rest in the non-paved median of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Both vehicles came to a final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway. V1 departed the right curb edge and its front plane contacted a wooden utility pole. V1 was re-directed left and its front plane contacted a metal railroad crossing pole and came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided, straight, level road approaching a four-way intersection.  V1 turned left at the intersection and headed north.  V1 partially departed the east road edge causing the front right corner to contact a guy wire.  V1 rotated clockwise and rolled over one quarter turn coming to final rest on the left plane facing east mostly in lane one.

V1 was traveling south on a five lane, one way, roadway approaching an intersection. V2  was traveling west on a three lane, divided, roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Then the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was northbound on the same roadway. V1 departed the travel lane to the left impacting the left side of V2 with its left side causing damage. V1 then continued south rotating counter clockwise and departed the left side of the road traveling down an embankment and overturned right side leading four quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels facing northeast. V2 continued northward coming to final rest on the right side of the road facing north.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the road traveling east before returning to the road. V1 crossed both travel lanes to depart the right side of the road in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 then overturned in a ditch right side leading three quarter turns coming to final rest on its left side facing north.

Vehicle 1 was north on a 5 lane, undivided highway in lane one. Vehicle 1 was traveling uphill when the front of the vehicle contacted a deer in the travel lane. Vehicle 1 came to rest at the next intersection on the east side of the road, facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a three lane divided roadway, and was negotiating a right curve on a roadway exit ramp. V1 departed the roadway on the left side, crossed over an island median, and traveled over another roadway exit ramp. V1 then struck an exit ramp curb with its left front tire (event 1), and then struck a guardrail face with its front plane (event 2). The vehicle then crossed over the top of the guardrail, and traveled over a roadway on-ramp. V1 then struck a second guardrail with its front plane (event 3) and also crossed over the top of the second guardrail. The vehicle then traveled approximately 35 meters down an embankment and struck an unknown object with its right side (event 4). Finally, V1's left side struck a culvert (event 5) before it came it final rest in wooded area.

V1 was traveling south in lane three, on a three lane, non-positively divided roadway, and had stopped at a traffic light to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two on a three lane, divided roadway, and was passing through the intersection. As V1 began to turn left at the intersection, V2's front plane contacted V1's right side plane. This impact caused V1 to rotate in a clockwise direction approximately 180 degrees, and the vehicle came to final rest in a parking lot entrance, facing north. After the impact, V2 came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 lost control and departed the right hand side of the roadway. V1 continued forward striking a tree with its front plane. V1 continued forward striking another tree with its front and came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway and continued forward down an embankment striking shrubbery with its front plane. V1 continued forward contacting the ground with its undercarriage and striking another tree with its front. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling South in lane 3 of 4 on a two-way, physically divided without positive barrier approaching an intersection, with a right turn lane. V2 was traveling East in lane 1 of 2,two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously with V1's front plane contacting V2's left plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise while V2 rotated clockwise. V1's right plane then contacted an unknown plane on V2. V1 departed the roadway to the left and came to final rest facing south in the northbound lane of the roadway. V2 came to final rest in the the southbound lanes of travel.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on  two lane, undivided, roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was slowing to make a left turn at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left, then departed the roadway to the left. V1's front plane contacted two trees before coming to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to cross over an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one of a six lane  divided roadway attempt to cross over the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 departed its left road edge and came to rest. V2 departed its right road edge and the right plane contacted a sign. V2 came to rest off the right road edge near impact with the sign.
V1 and V2 were traveling northwest negotiating a left curve in lane one of a two lane roadway with V2 ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southeast in lane one of the same roadway, behind V1. V1 pulled off the roadway to the right side and then reentered the roadway as V2 was passing. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 & V2 then sideslapped, with the left plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 departed the roadway to the left, into a parking lot, and the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V3 (a parked, unoccupied vehicle). The front plane of V1 contacted a pole. V1, V2, and V3 came to final rest off the roadway.

Both vehicles were traveling in the westbound travel lane of a two lane undivided roadway, vehicle 2 stopped in the travel lane waiting to make a left turn into a parking area. Vehicle 2 was contacted on its back plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 1, both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.
