V1 was traveling east on a three lane, physically divided roadway in lane one. V1 departed the right side roadway, where it struck a sign, then continued to strike a utility pole with it's frontal plane, before coming to final rest off roadway facing south east.

V1 was traveling eastbound in a two lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V2 and V3 were stopped facing eastbound, in lane one in the mentioned roadway due to traffic. V1's front plane contacted V2's back plane. After initial impact with V1, V2's front plane contacted V3's back plane. V1, V2 and V3 came to final rest in the roadway at point of impact facing eastbound.

V1 was stopped facing south in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling south in the same lane behind V1. The front of V2 contacted the back of V1. After the initial impact, V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the roadway. V1 came to final rest in the roadway at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in the fourth of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway approaching a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was stopped facing west in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the lane near the point of impact.

V1 was pulling a trailer while traveling east in lane 1 on a 3-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 3-lane roadway approaching the same intersection making a left turn. V3 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 3-lane roadway stopped at the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued forward while rotating counter-clockwise and the trailer contacted the back of V1. V1 departed the left road edge and its front plane contacted the concrete base of a breakaway pole. V1 came to rest at the pole facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise and its front plane contacted the front of V3. V2 departed the left road edge and came to rest facing east. V2 then was entirely engulfed in flames. V3 came to rest near its area of impact.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. The roadway was bordered on the eastern side by a guardrail, and on the western side by a large ditch, with a steep embankment and rock cuts. A deer entered the path of V1. V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 entered the ditch, where its frontal plane impacted the embankment. V1 continued in a northern direction and impacted the embankment a second time with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a large boulder with its frontal plane. This final impact caused V1 to rotate counter clockwise, coming to final rest in the ditch on the western side of the road.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, non-divided roadway, approaching a four-way intersection, which was controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, non-divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was northbound in a right turn lane of a three lane roadway at the same intersection, which was also controlled by a stop sign. V1 attempted to cross through the intersection as V2 was traveling through the intersection. V1's right plane impacted V2's frontal plane (event 1). V1 rotated counter clockwise, where V1's right plane impacted V2's left plane (event 2). V1 then departed the roadway to the northeast side of the intersection, where it came to final rest off the roadway. V2's right plane impacted V3's frontal plane (event 3). V2 departed the road to the southeast side of the intersection. V3 came to final rest at the point of impact in lane one of the roadway.

Vehicles 1,2, 3, and 4 were traveling south on a four lane, two way roadway physically divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle 1 was traveling in lane four, Vehicle 2 was traveling in lane one, and Vehicles 3 and 4 were in lane two. V1 changed lanes from lane four to lane one.  The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 departed the lane on the left and the front of Vehicle 3 contacted the back of Vehicle 1. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 4's trailer. Vehicle 3 departed the roadway to the right and the right side contacted a guardrail; coming to final rest facing south on the shoulder. Vehicle 1, 2, and four came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane roadway. V1 departed the lane of the right and departed the roadway on the right. V1 contacted the front on a ditch. V1 then rolled to the left side six quarter turns. V1 came to rest off the roadway on the roof facing east.

V1 was traveling east in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. Both vehicles entered an intersection. V1 turned left to head north. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise while continuing east. V2 was pushed backwards and started rotating clockwise. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 rolled over onto its right side. V1 came to rest on its right side facing south. V2 came to rest facing north against the north east curb.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when control over V1 was lost and it began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 departed the road on the left and overturned. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in the median.

V1 was traveling south on a undivided two way road in lane one. Due to an unknown reason V1 drove of the west road edge and the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest on it's wheels partially on the roadway facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane one. V1 departed its left lane line and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing east. V2 rotated counter-clockwise where it departed the eastbound road into a ditch and contacted the ditch side with its back plane. V1 continued to rotate and contacted the ditch side with its right side. V1 then contacted a tree stump with its left top plane. V1 came to rest in the ditch facing north.

V1 was southbound exiting a private driveway. V2 was traveling west, negotiating a curve, on a two-lane road approaching the driveway. V1 initiated a left turn in the road and its left side was struck by the front of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing south and V2 traveled a short distance before coming to final rest off the roadway facing west.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating the same curve. V1 departed the left side of its travel lane impacting the front end of V2 with its right side plane causing damage. V2 came to final rest in the middle of the curve facing  west. V1 departed the left side of the road coming to final rest off the road facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder, and V1 contacted the deer with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward a short distance before coming to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a curb with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then continued forward impacting another curb with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then overturned right side leading three quarter turns onto its left side before rolling back left side leading onto its roof. V1 came to final rest on its roof facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane highway in lane one behind V2. V2 was traveling south on a three lane highway in lane one in front of V1. As V1 entered an off-ramp the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2, which was at a stop on the off-ramp. V1 came to rest in lane one facing south. V2 came to rest in lane one facing south.

V1 was backing into the road from a front yard area. V2 were traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest near impact facing north. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact also facing in a northern direction.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling south in lane one of a two lane, grass median divided roadway.  The front of Vehicle 2 contacted the back of Vehicle 1.  Both vehicles came to rest forward of impact, still in lane one, facing south.

V1 & V2 were both traveling west in lane one, on a two lane, positively divided roadway. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. As a result of this contact, V1 departed the roadway to the left and contacted a guardrail end cap with its front plane, continued traveling forward and then contacted a tree, before coming to final rest off of the roadway, perpendicular to the roadway. V2 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a guardrail face with its front plane. V2 then began a left leading, four quarter rollover contacting the guardrail face with its left side plane, its top plane, and right side plane. V2 came to final rest, on its tires, behind the guardrail, facing east.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway and was negotiating a left curve in the roadway. The vehicle then veered to the right to avoid an animal in the road. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and contacted a guardrail face with its front plane. V1 then began to rotate in a clockwise direction and contacted the guardrail face again with its left side plane. The vehicle then re-entered the roadway, and came to final rest in a perpendicular position to the roadway. At final rest, the vehicle's front wheels were in lane 1 of the roadway, and the rear wheels were off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a two-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 rotated clockwise, departed the roadway on the southwest corner and the left side of V1 contacted a utility marker. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing north. V2 rotated clockwise, departed the eastbound roadway and came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway negotiating a curve to the left. Vehicle 1 departed the road on the right side and the front plane contacted a utility pole. Vehicle 1 then continued forward and the front of V1 contacted a stump and drove over some debris. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two way divided roadway with grass median.  V1 departed the roadway to the left, rotated clockwise and rolled 1 quarter turn coming to final rest on the right plane.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching a four-way intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a two lane one-way roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeding straight through the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  V1 rotated counterclockwise to final rest in the intersection facing northeast. V2 rotated clockwise to final rest facing northeast in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south in lane two on a three lane median divided roadway. V2 was also traveling south on the same roadway in lane three behind V1. While attempting to turn left to travel north bound on the same median divided roadway, V1 crossed the left lane line and its left side plane made contact with the front plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 continued forward and came to a final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south, on a median divided trafficway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was ahead of V1 in the same lane stopped at the traffic signal controlled intersection that V1 was approaching. The front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front contacted a fence. V1 proceeded off the roadway and the front contacted shrubbery/saplings. V1 finally contacted a tree with the front, and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge and its front plane contacted a fence. V1 then continued traveling northeast and it front plane contacted a ditch. V1 came to rest in the ditch at near impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and then departed the roadway to the left. V1's front plane contacted a tree and then its left plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway against the trees.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a six lane roadway attempting to pass through an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two of a six lane roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane. V1 continued through the intersection and parked off the roadway. V2 came to rest in the intersection near impact.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was turning right out of a driveway to proceed northeast in lane one of the same roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 continued traveling and departed its travel lane to the left, then the roadway to the left. V1's front plane contacted an embankment and came to final rest off the roadway close to impact 2. V2 rotated as it traveled off the roadway on the right side and came to final rest off the roadway facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound and turning right from a two lane undivided roadway, within the intersection onto a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was stopped on a two lane undivided roadway at the same intersection and was contacted on its frontal plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 3 on a 3- lane divided roadway, and was turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway and was passing through the same intersection. In the intersection, the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing north. V2 rotated clockwise as it continued forward and came to rest in the intersection facing northwest.

V1 was traveling south bound on a four lane, physically divided roadway, in the number one lane, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 left the roadway to the left, rotating counter clockwise in doing so, V1's frontal plane impacted a culvert, causing V1 to rotate further counter clockwise. V1's right plane then impacted a road sign. V1 came to final rest off the left side of the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling north in the second of five lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the first lane on the same roadway. V1 changed lanes to the right and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the second of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling south in the first lane on the same roadway as V1. V1 attempted to change lanes to the right and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 lost directional control of the vehicle, began to rotate clockwise, crossed through all the lanes and departed the road on the left side. V2 rolled over from left to top for four quarter turns before coming to rest off the left side of the road. V1 left scene of crash.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway and in an attempt to avoid the deer, V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway striking a guardrail face with an unknown plane. V1 continued forward partially off the roadway and then returned to the roadway. V1 then crossed the left hand lane line and departed the left hand side of the roadway striking a tree with its front plane. V1 continued forward coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, traveled down an embankment and contacted two trees with its front plane. V1 came to a final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane three of a four lane divided roadway (no positive barrier), approaching a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1, V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing north. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest within the intersection, facing south.

V1 and V2 were negotiating and exiting a right curve on a two lane divided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to its right as the roadway began to curve left and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a four lane divided roadway. V2 was also traveling west in lane 2. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The left of V1 contacted right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 lost control and departed the right road edge and rolled right side leading two quarter turns. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the southbound lane of a two lane undivided roadway and departed the roadway to the right. Vehicle 1 impacted a ditch with its frontal plane off the roadway and then entered into a roll-over event coming to rest on its left side off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection controlled by a stop sign in the north and south directions. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway and V3 was traveling west. Both V2 and V3 were approaching the intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. V2 then departed its lane to the left side and entered the west bound lane. The front of V2 contacted the front of V3 further east of the impact with V1. V1 came to final rest facing southeast in the roadway, V2 came to final rest off the roadway to the north facing south, and V3 came to final rest on the west bound shoulder facing west.

V1 was eastbound in lane 4 of 4 on a one-way roadway.  V2 was northbound on a 1 lane divided roadway attempting to turn right on to the same roadway. After turning right V2 was traveling when the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the second of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in the fifth of six lanes on a divided two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1  attempting to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Vehicle 1 came to rest within the intersection. Vehicle 2 departed the road on the southwest corner before coming to final.

V1 was westbound on a 5 lane, with middle turn lane, roadway in lane 3 approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was eastbound in lane 1 on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 turned left at the intersection and V2 proceeded east the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and its right rear wheel contacted the curb. The front of V1 then contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise the rolled left onto the roadway one-quarter turn. V1 came to rest on its left side on the road facing south. The driver was ejected during the rollover sequence..

V1 was traveling north following a two way, two lane road. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole. Continuing forward, the front impacted a guy wire before coming to final rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road with a slight curve to the left. A non contact vehicle, traveling in the opposite direction, departed its travel lane to the left, entering V1's travel lane. Attempting to avoid contact, V1 steered right and departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a wood pile and then a tree. V1 then rolled right 2-quarter turns and came to rest on its top.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the Lane 1 position.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway right side making contact with the front plane to a mailbox, 2 landscaping rocks, and a tree before coming to final rest facing northwest lodged against a building.

Vehicles 1 and 2 we both traveling southeast on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was stopped in traffic facing southeast. V1 was behind V2. As Vehicle 1 approached the intersection, the front plane made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing southeast shortly after impact. Vehicle 2 was at rest facing southeast at the time of impact.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a tree. V1 rotated counter clockwise, and rolled right side leading two quarter turns coming to final rest on its roof.

V1 was south bound on a two lane, non divided roadway. V2 was north bound on the same roadway approaching V1. V1's left rear wheel came off from the vehicle, and rolled into the front of V2. V2s frontal plane impacted the wheel. V1 came to final rest on the west side of the roadway, and V2 came to rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west exiting a parking lot and entering a 3-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of a 5-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection facing northwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast on a two lane divided roadway with a positive barrier. V1 departed the roadway on the right side while rotating clockwise. V1 rolled with its left side leading  four quarter turns before coming to rest off the road on its wheels facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane two of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest facing southwest.

Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane two of a four lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane, undivided roadway. V1 turned left and the front of V2 contacted the right of V1. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing southeast. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast.

Vehicle1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non- physically divided roadway in lane 1, approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles then contacted each other in a side slap manner with the right side of V1 contacting the left side of V2.  V2 contacted a curb with the left front tire before it came to rest south of the intersection on the side walk, facing south.  V1 departed the roadway on the south east corner of the intersection. The front of V1 contacted a stop sign then contacted a tree before coming to rest facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction. V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway, struck an embankment with its front plane, and began to rotate in a clockwise direction in a field while off the roadway. V1 continued forward overturning with its left side leading eight-quarter turns before coming to a final rest off the roadway on its wheels.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound, on a two way, two lane undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right of V1 made contact with the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to a final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south through a four leg intersection, on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, V2 was traveling west through the same four leg intersection, on a two lane, two way, undivided road. The frontal plane of V1 struck the right side plane of V2. V1 then rotated clockwise and its rear plane was struck by the right side plane of V2. V1 came to rest on the northwest corner of the intersection heading south. V2 came to a controlled stop in its original travel lane heading west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a culvert with its frontal plane. V1 then went airborne over a driveway and contacted the culvert bank with its frontal plane as it came down. The rear undercarriage of V1 then contacted the culvert pipe on the opposite side of the driveway. V1 continued north coming to rest in the ditch facing north.

V1 was traveling west on the eastbound lanes in lane 2. V1 departed the roadway to the left in a yaw. V1 contacted the curb with the left front tire (event 1). V1 continued on its path crossing the sidewalk. The front of V1 contacted the steps (event 2). V1 exited the steps and the undercarriage of the rear of V1 contacted the sidewalk (event 3).  V1 was then redirected to the right where it came to final rest facing northwest.
V1 and V2 were heading west on a four lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane roadway while negotiating a curve to the right. V1 crossed the lane line to the left and then went off of the roadway on the left side. V1 went into a ditch where its front contacted a wall and then fell over to the right. V1 rolled 4 quarter turns before re-entering the shoulder, where vehicle came to final rest on its wheels.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west in lane 2 on a 4-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 stopped in the roadway to turn left. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left while traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road when its front plane impacted a metal utility pole. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the right while traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted a mailbox and a utility pole with its front plane. V1 came to final rest off of the right side of the road at the second point of impact.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway with icy conditions. V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway at point of impact.

V1 was traveling east on a one-way exit ramp. V2, a tractor-trailer, was parked on the paved shoulder of the exit ramp facing east. V1 departed the roadway to the left, returned to the roadway then departed the roadway to the right and its front plane contacted the back plane of V2's trailer. V2 was pushed forward and came to rest near impact. V1 rotated clockwise and bounce back and came to rest on the left shoulder facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway making a left turn into a driveway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 crossed paths of V2. V2 applied brakes and steered to the right to avoid V1. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the front plane of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest off the roadway, on the driveway.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a stop sign at the same intersection as V1. V2 stopped at the stop sign. V1 made a right turn and slid laterally to the left due to the slush on the road. The front plane of V1 contacted an unknown plane of V2. V2 left the scene. V1 continued on and struck an unknown object on the road edge. V1 came to final rest on the roads edge.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then the left side of the road. V1 traveled off the road before impacting a concrete pole with the front end causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated clockwise coming to final rest facing northeast.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway following V2. V1 attempted to pass V2 as V2 made a left turn into a driveway. The left side of V2 impacted the right side of V1 causing damage. Upon impact V1 continued eastward traveling into a ditch then out of the ditch impacted the road edge with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the road facing east. V2 came to final rest in the driveway facing east.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling northbound on a four lane, undivided roadway in lane two. V3 was traveling ahead of V2 and V1 was traveling behind V2. V3 stopped in the roadway due to another vehicle was stopped. V2 stopped behind V3, the front of V1 then impacted the back of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V3. All vehicles came to rest in lane two facing northbound.

V1 was traveling south in lane two on a three lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane one on a three lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2 in a side slap manner. V1 came to rest in the southwest corner of the intersection facing southwest. V2 departed the southwest corner of the intersection and came to rest in an asphalt area facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north on an intersecting two-lane, undivided roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  After impact, V1 began to rotate clockwise and rolled over one quarter-turn to the left.  V1 came to rest on it's left side, east of the intersection.  V2 came to rest on the edge of the intersection, facing east.

V1 and V2 were traveling north west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 came to a stop due to traffic ahead behind a non collision vehicle. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the #1 lane facing north west.

V1 was on the southbound lanes in a physically divided three lane highway, stopped between lanes three and two, facing a easterly direction. V2 was traveling south on the same physically divided three lane highway in lane two. As V1 was stopped in the middle of the road, V2 traveling south braked and steered left, but the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 then spun clockwise in a westerly direction across the southbound lanes and came to rest in the right road edge shoulder on it's wheels facing a northeasterly direction. V2 continued towards the median and came to rest on it's wheels within the intersection facing a easterly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one in front of V1. As V2 came to a stop, the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued towards the east bound lane where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in between the east and west bound lanes facing west. V2 came to rest in lane one facing west.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection to turn left. V2 was traveling east on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. V3 was traveling north in lane two on a three lane non-physically divided roadway stopped at the same intersection. V1 began to make a left turn as V2 was passing through the intersection and the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 then rotated counter-clockwise and rolled left one quarter turn where the undercarriage of V1 impacted the front right of V3. V1 came to rest on its driver side in lane two of the northbound lanes in the intersection facing a southeasterly direction. V2 came to rest in lane one of the eastbound lanes in the intersection facing an easterly direction. V3 came to rest in lane two of the northbound lanes facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 was stopped facing southerly due to traffic in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V3 was traveling southerly in the number 1 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and into the number 1 lane where the left side of V1 impacted the front of V3. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and came to rest south of V2 and V3, facing northerly, between the number 1 and number 2 lanes. V2 came to rest facing southerly, north of V1, in the number 2 lane. V3 came to rest facing southerly, north of V1, in the number 1 lane.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane undivided intersection, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise while V2 rotated counter-clockwise. The left side of V1 impacted the right side V2. V1 continued southerly and came to rest facing southwest on the southwest corner of the intersection. V2 continued southerly and came to rest facing south on the south roadway.

V1 was traveling south through an intersection in lane 2 (of two lanes). V2 was traveling east to north (making a left turn) through the same intersection from lane two of a two-lane, one-way off ramp. In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction south of the intersection in lanes 1 and 2. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a northeasterly direction in the intersection, northeast of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane two of a two-lane, divided roadway with a barrier.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a guardrail face.  V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and the right of V1 contacted the guardrail face.  V1 came to rest in contact with the guardrail, facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west, on a 5 lane, two-way physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 2 and vehicle 3 were heading west, on a 5 lane, two-way physically divided roadway, stopped in lane number 1. Vehicle 1's front made contact with vehicle 2's rear end. After initial contact, vehicle 2's front made contact with vehicle 3's rear end. Vehicle 1 and 2 came to final rest in their original lane. Vehicle 3 left the scene.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a four lane, two-way not physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1's front made contact with a deer that had jumped the guardrail that was on the south side of the road. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the original lane and the deer took off and left after it was hit.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 4 lane median divided intersection in lane number 2 approaching the intersection. Vehicle 1 continued through the intersection and swerved to the left then right to miss a vehicle that was turning left to go west. After missing the vehicle in the intersection, vehicle 1's front made contact with a pole on the SE median. After the impact with the pole, it broke and fell onto the truck bed.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the median facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right hand (south) side of the roadway and contacted a stone garden border with its front plane. V1 then proceeded forward a short distance before contacting a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane, median divided, roadway. V1 was in lane 1 and V2 was in lane 2. V1 changed lanes to the left and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles contacted again with the left side of V1 contacting the right side of V2.   Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a three lane undivided (two-way traffic) straight roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a seven lane undivided (two-way traffic) straight roadway, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the northeast corner of the intersection. The left side of V1 impacted two utility poles in separate impacts. V1 also impacted the guy wire of the second pole with its left side. V1 came to rest in the northeast corner of the intersection, facing southeast. After the impact, V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest within the intersection, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. V1 began to lose control and departed the left lane line, continued to slide forward departing a second left lane line, and then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 then stuck a rock wall with its frontal plane where it came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on an undivided two-way road in lane one approaching a sign controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east on an undivided two-way road in lane one entering the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest within the intersection facing a southeast direction and V2 came to rest within the intersection facing a easterly direction.

V1 was turning right out a driveway, and was in lane 3 while crossing 3 lanes of a 5 lane roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 4 of the same five lane roadway and was changing lanes from lane 4 to lane 3. V1's front plane then contacted V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a three lane, two way roadway, and was turning right to travel south on another three lane roadway. V2 was traveling north in lane two on a three lane, two way roadway, and was approaching a traffic signal in the left turn lane. As V1 was completing the right turn, the vehicle departed it's lane on the left side. V1's front plane then contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on lane 1 of a 3 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in lane 1 of a 3 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 right plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane one facing westbound in lane one.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane undivided roadway while negotiating a left curve in lane 2. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway in lane 2. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2, then V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane in a side slap type impact. Both vehicles came to final rest off the roadway to the west side. The driver of V1 was ejected from the vehicle during the crash sequence
V1 was traveling south on a four lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted an utility pole. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and contacted an embankment with its right side plane. V1 continued forward contacting another portion of the embankment with its right side plane. V1 then contacted a pole, a culvert pipe, and an additional portion of the embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then attempted to exit the embankment and began to roll, right side leading. V1 rolled four quarter turns before it came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the southern shoulder, and in a attempt to avoid the deer in the roadway, V1 departed the right hand (north) side of the roadway. V1 then struck two trees with its frontal plane. V1 then proceeded to rotate in a clockwise direction where it came to a stop and then became completely engulfed in flames. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north. Vehicle #2 was traveling south.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling west in the same lane.  The back of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V2 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed the road to the right.  V1 tripped and rolled over 1 quarter-turn to the left.  V1 came to rest off the road to the north on its left plane, facing east.  Vehicle #2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. V2, V3, and V4 were all stopped on the same two lane, two way roadway facing east, in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 causing the front of V2 to impact the rear of V3. The front of V3 then impacted the rear of V4. All vehicles came to final rest shortly after impact in the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling west following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 rolled a total of four quarter turns before coming to final rest on right side of the roadway, facing west.

V1 was traveling east following a two way, six lane roadway, in the fourth lane of travel. V1 was approaching a four way intersection, attempting to turn left. As V1 was negotiating the turn, it departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a curb and then a sign post before coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway, on the south leg of the intersection. V1 was facing south at final rest.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to make a left turn to the east as V2 attempted to make a right turn to the north. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 causing damage. V1 and V2 came to final rest at the point of impact with V1 facing southeast and V2 facing northwest.

V2 was pulling a trailer westbound on a four lane, two way traffic divided by a grass median followed by V1. V1 impacted the trailer of V2 with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then continued off the left side of the roadway coming to final rest in the median facing south. V1 continued west coming to final rest on the right side of the road facing west.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, undivided (two way traffic) roadway traveling in lane one. V1 saw a deer in the roadway and swerved left, V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 then returned to the roadway and departed the roadway to right. V1 then rolled over, left side leading, and the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 then impacted tree limbs with it's right side and came to rest on it's wheels facing north.

V1 was traveling southwest on a one-way roadway approaching a 4 way intersection attempting to turn left to travel east.  V2 was traveling west in lane two of the intersecting roadway, going straight at the intersection.  As V1 turned left the front of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.  V1 rotated counterclockwise to final rest facing east in the intersection. V2 came to final rest in the intersection facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a four lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection.As V1 made a left turn in the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 was traveling south on a two lane, median divided, roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the right side contacted a tree, then the front contacted another tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast, turning left out of a driveway. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching the driveway. Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane 3 on a 4- lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the first of two southbound travel lanes of a four lane median divided trafficway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a guardrail end with its frontal plane, coming to rest off of the roadway.

V1, V2, and V3 were all southbound in lane two of a six-lane undivided road. V2 and V3 were both stopped ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Subsequently, the front of V2 contacted the back of V3. V1, V2, and V3 came to rest in the roadway facing south.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a cow that was in its travel lane. V1 came to rest heading north on the northbound shoulder.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, while negotiating a left curve and attempting to turn right (south) onto a two lane, two way, undivided roadway at a three leg intersection. V1 struck a stop sign, that is placed for the northbound lane that ends at the T intersection, with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact heading southeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of an undivided, seven lane trafficway without a positive barrier. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and contacted a sign with its front end. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north.
V1 was entering onto the roadway from a driveway. V2 was heading east on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Both vehicle came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, with an up hill grade. Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a 4 lane, two way, non physically divided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2.  As Vehicle 1 continued past V2, the right plane made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest just after impact facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching the same intersection attempting to make a right hand turn.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  After impact Vehicle 2 was pushed laterally striking a curb with the right rear wheel.  Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise after the curb strike. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southeast.  Vehicle 1 deflected to the south eventually making contact with Vehicle 3 with an unknown plane to the left side of Vehicle 3.  Vehicle 3 came to rest straddling the curb facing north.  Vehicle 1 continued south eventually departing the roadway on the left side traveling across a business landscape.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 then made contact with a building coming to rest at im

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling south on a two-lane, divided roadway.  V1 was in lane one.   V2 was in lane 2.  V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed its lane to the left.  The left of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V2 came to rest in lane 2 facing south.  V1 departed the road to the left and came to rest facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane two of a two-lane, divided roadway.  V1 began to change lanes into lane one and began to rotate clockwise.  V1 departed the road to the right and rolled over four quarter-turns to the left.  V1 came to rest off the road to the north, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling south, on a median divided trafficway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching a traffic signal controlled intersection. V2 was ahead of V1 in the same lane stopped at the traffic signal controlled intersection that V1 was approaching. The front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a curved left, two-lane, two-way roadway. While negotiating the curve, V1 departed the roadway to the right.  V1 began a counterclockwise yaw. V1's right tires impacted a small gravel hill and V1 rolled to the right. V1 rolled seven-quarter turns coming to rest on its left side. The driver of V1 was ejected out of the vehicle during the roll sequence.

V1 and V2 were traveling southwest on a 3 lane, physically divided roadway, in lane 3. V3 was on the same roadway, in lane 2. V2 started to accelerate and steer left. V3 was stopped in the roadway. V1's front contacted V2's rear. V1's left side then contacted a concrete barrier. V2 then went over the lane line to the right. V2's front contacted V3's left. All 3 vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was heading south in lane three of a three-lane divided trafficway without a positive barrier. V2 was heading north on the same trafficway in lane two stopped for traffic ahead. The front of V1 contacted the front of V3 (event 1). V3 was redirected to the right. The rear of V2 contacted the front of V3 (event 2). V1 came to final rest in its initial travel lane near its point of impact. V2 came to final rest at its point of impact. V3 continued on its path of travel.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 6 lane two way roadway, approaching a four leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in the fourth lane of a six lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the front plane of vehicle 1. Upon impact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast. Vehicle 2 continued forward and came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane two on a three lane two way roadway approaching a three leg intersection with a red traffic signal. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the same direction behind vehicle 1 on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 stopped for the red light and the front plane of vehicle 2 contacted the back plane of vehicle1. Both vehicles came to final rest in their lane of travel before the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in the second of two southbound lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling south in the first of two lanes on the same roadway. V3 was traveling south in the second of two lanes on the same roadway. V4 was traveling south in the second of two lanes on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact V2 then moved to its right and the front of V2 contacted a concrete barrier. V2 continued forward and the right side of V2 contacted the same barrier. The front of V1 then contacted the front of V3 as it continued to travel north. And finally, the front of V1 contacted the front of V4. All four vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 and V2 were southbound on a 4 lane freeway with V1 behind V2. V2 stopped for workers on the roadway and V1 departed the roadway to the right to attempt to avoid V2. The front of V1 then contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 then traveled southeast away from the barrier and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on a undivided, two-way roadway approaching a three-legged intersection.  V1 departed the west side of the intersection and both front tires/wheels contacted the west curb. The front of V1 then contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was westbound on a 2 way, with middle turn lane, roadway. V2 was eastbound on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left then departed its lane to the left again and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. After contact, both vehicles rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing opposite their original travel directions.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) straight roadway. V2 and V3 were parked on private property off road. V1 departed the road to the right. V1 was traveling north on a three-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a three-lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V1 stopped for the traffic signal. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, three lane roadway, after making a left turn from a driveway. V2 was a trailer parked off the west road edge facing a south. As V1 entered the roadway, V1 lost control and departed the lane to the left, returned to the lane from the left, then departed the roadway to the right west road edge, where the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest under the trailer facing west. V2 came to rest facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane physically divided road in lane three. V2 was traveling north on a three lane physically divided road in lane three in front of V1. V2 began to slow for traffic ahead and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to rest on the west shoulder facing north. V2 came to rest in lane three facing east.

V1 was traveling south east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north west on the same roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line crossing paths with V2. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 attempted to avoid deer that entered the roadway, V1 departed the left roads edge and the front plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way, three lane roadway with a center two way left turning lane.  V2, V3, V4, and V5 were all parked in the eastbound parking lane.  V1 struck V2, V3, V4, and V5 with the front plane.  V2, V3, and V4 sustained impact damage to the left side planes.  V5 was struck in the rear plane.  V1 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane, undivided roadway in lane 1 when V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 traveled through a field, traversing a ditch where its rear bumper impacted the top surface of the ditch-line (Event 1). An Unknown plane of V1 contacted a traffic sign (Event 2) before entering onto a different, two-lane, undivided roadway and still traveling south. V1 departed the roadway to the left as its windshield header impacted a tree branch (Event 3). V1 continued down a steep grade into another ditch where its frontal plane impacted a cement culvert wall (Event 4). V1 came to final rest on its wheels facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided two lane highway in lane two, negotiating a left curve. For an unknown reason V1 traveled across the southbound lanes towards the right road edge, where the front of V1 impacted a guardrail. V1 traveled up and over the guardrail, and began to roll left nine quarter turns down the hill, before coming to rest on it's passenger side facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided three lane highway in lane two. V2 was traveling south on the same physically divided three lane highway in lane two, behind V1. V2 passed V1 and began to change lanes from lane three to lane two. The right side of V2 was impacted by V1 as V2 was changing lanes back to lane two. V2 began to loose control and traveled west across the southbound lanes, yawing in a clockwise manner; and the front of V2 contacted a guard rail. V1 the began to roll. V2 continued rolling on top of the guardrail and came to rest straddling the guardrail facing a northerly direction. V1 continued driving.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided highway in lane one. V2 was traveling north on a two lane divided highway in lane one, towing a trailer in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of the trailer of V2 then front of the trailer impacted the rear of V2. The trailer then became detached from V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest on the right shoulder facing north. V2 departed the left road edge into the median and its front plane contacted a guardrail face. The detached trailer also impacted the guardrail face. V2 came to rest in the median facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one, negotiating a curve. V1 was unable to navigate the curve and departed the east road edge and continued off the roadway down an embankment where the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 continued through the fence and the front of V1 impacted a fire hydrant. V1 continued through a field and the front of V1 impacted another fence. V1 continued through the fence where the front of V1 impacted a post from a gazebo and then impacted a building. V1 came to rest against the building facing a northeasterly direction.
V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in front of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane 1 facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided, two-lane, two-way road. V2 is legally parked facing north. Both vehicle's came to final rest near impact in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane roadway in the first travel lane. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left in an attempt to pass a non contacted vehicle. V1 then rolled two quarter turns, right side leading, before coming to final rest in the southbound lane, on its roof, facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the northern road edge. The front plane of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided traffic way approaching a four-legged intersection.
