V2 went into a counter clockwise yaw and departed the right where the front impacted an embankment. V2 came to final rest off the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling south on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve with a trailer. V1 crossed the left lane line contacting V2's left plane and trailer with the front plane of V1. V1 re-entered its original lane of travel and came to rest on the roadway. V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one of a one lane, one way roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the left of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane two on a two lane divided roadway approaching a three-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane three on a five lane roadway turning left at the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane roadway divided by a median, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane two of a six lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier, approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing east. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 departed its travel lane to the left to overtake V1. V1 began to make a left turn into a parking lot. The left of V1 impacted with the front of V2.  V1 came to final rest facing west in the westbound lanes. V2 came to final rest near its point of impact.

V1 was heading west on a four lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was heading east on the same roadway approaching the same intersection to continue straight. V1 began to turn left at the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to slide due to ice on the roadway and departed the right hand (east) side of the roadway. V1 then contacted a tree with its frontal plane and a tree branch with its right side plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve. V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway contacting a culvert with its frontal plane. V1 proceeded forward a short distance before contacting a guy wire with its frontal plane. V1 then began to rotate clockwise where it contacted a utility box with its left side plane. V1 then contacted a utility pole twice with its left side plane and came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a four lane, two-way roadway approaching a "T" type intersection. V1 crossed through the intersection and departed the roadway. V1's front plane contacted a wall. V1 came to final rest off the roadway against the wall.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one on a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. V1 then re-entered its travel lane and departed the right road edge in a clockwise rotation. V1 contacted a ditch then tripped and rolled left four quarter turns contacting a fence before coming to final rest on its wheels off the right road edge.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane roadway physically divided by a concrete barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed its original lane of travel to the right. The right of Vehicle 1 contacted the left of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest facing east on the right shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a light controlled  four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same light controlled intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right of Vehicle 2. The right side of Vehicle 2 contacted the left side of Vehicle 1 in a side slap. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east and Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing south.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling in the same lane, ahead of V1. V2 stopped for a crew clearing trees off of the right side of the road. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact, heading southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane residential roadway. V2 was legally parked on the northbound side of the roadway. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2 and came to rest near area of impact facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on lane 2 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a grass median. A deer entered the roadway from the right side of the roadway. V1 front plane contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest on the roadway and pulled off on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling West in lane one of four lane, two-way, physically divided roadway. V1 left its initial lane of travel to the left and then the roadway to the left driving down an embankment. V1 began rotating clockwise, V1's back plane contacted a downed tree. V1's left plane then contacted a standing tree. V1 came to final rest against both trees facing North.

V1 was traveling North in the opposite direction of the Southbound lanes, in lane two. For an unknown reason V1 traveled off the east road edge of the southbound lanes onto a dirt/grass median, towards a descending embankment, to another road. V1 became airborne, over the embankment and the undercarriage of V1 impacted a curb and the ground. V1 continued across the road and the wheels of V1 impacted another curb, and then the front of V1 impacted a chain linked fence. V1 came to rest on it's wheels, against the fence, on an ascending embankment facing a northwest direction.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided four lane road in lane one negotiating a right curve, at an intersection. For an unknown reason V1 traveled south off  the south road edge and the front wheels impacted a curb and then the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest partially on the curb and roadway facing a southerly direction.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south on a three-lane divided highway. V1 was in lane three and V2 was in lane two. V1 departed its lane to the right and its front end struck the back of V2 (event 1). V2 began to rotate clockwise and departed the road on the right, where it overturned (event 2). During the rollover, the right side of V2 contacted a fence (event 3). V1 continued traveling south until it overturned in the roadway (event 4). V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction on the roadside. V2 came to rest on its right side facing an easterly direction on the roadside.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane on the left and the front end of V1 contacted left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a northerly direction in the center of the road. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a southerly direction in lane 1.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane 4 on a 6 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. A non-collision vehicle changed lanes from the number 3 lane into the number 4 lane and came to a stop in front of V2. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both V1 and V2 came to rest in the number 4 lane facing north.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane 2 on a 4-lane divided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the right and continued off the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a guard rail face. V1 continued forward and came to rest on the shoulder facing southeast.

V1 was northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was westbound in the number 1 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise while V2 rotated clockwise where the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles continued on their trajectories. V1 came to rest facing north on the north part of the intersection. V2 came to rest facing a northerly direction on the north roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a one-way physically divided roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 2 was stopped in traffic ahead of vehicle 1 on the same roadway. The front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling south on a two lane, one-way roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 1's front end and vehicle 2's rear end made contact with each other while slowing in traffic. Both vehicles came to final rest in their original lanes.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position stopped at an intersection with the intention to turn left. V2 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest after impact facing north in the intersection. V2 came to rest facing east on the east side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight right hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to lose control and departed the right hand side of the roadway. V1 contacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward contacting the same roadside embankment with its frontal plane causing V1 to rotate in a clockwise direction. V1 then rolled five quarter turns with its left side leading before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to lose control and rotate in a clockwise direction before departing the left side of the travel lane and then the left side of the roadway. V1 contacted a tree with its left side plane and then began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction. V1 then contacted a tree with its right side plane and continued to rotate in a counter clockwise direction where it stopped on top of a roadside embankment. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, one way, undivided highway. V1 lost control and spun in a clockwise yaw. V1 departed the roadway and rolled. V1 came to final rest off the highway on its roof.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two lane, two way, undivided road. The left rear tire of V1 blew out causing the vehicle to begin a clockwise yaw and depart the right side of the roadway. V1 straightened out and then yawed clockwise again and rolled four quarter turns, left side leading. V1 came to rest on its wheels heading northeast.
V1 was traveling south on a one-lane exit ramp. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front plane contacted a pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane undivided left curved roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a plastic reflector marker.  Then the right plane contacted a utility pole and the front contacted a left curve arrow warning sign.  After V1 crossed a driveway entrance the right front tire contacted a concrete curb causing the vehicle to roll over to the left three quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on the right plane facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1's front plane contacted a tree and V1 rotated counter clockwise the front plane contacted another tree. V1 came to final rest near impact facing southwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling southeast in lane three of a seven lane, two way divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a one lane, non-physically divided highway exit ramp.  Vehicle 1 veered to the left departing the roadway returning back to the roadway from the left side.  The vehicle started to rotate clockwise as it returned to the road.  Vehicle 1 then crossed the roadway departing the roadway on the right.  As the vehicle was crossing and departing, the driver steered left and the vehicle began a counterclockwise yaw.  The wheels of Vehicle 1 tripped in the grass/dirt causing the vehicle to roll, right side leading, 4 quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels facing south perpendicular to the roadway.  The driver of Vehicle 1 was ejected during the roll.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 1. Vehicle 2 was stopped in traffic on the same 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 1. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west at impact. After impact, Vehicle 2 traveled through the intersection pulling over on the north sidewalk and parked facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) highway. Driver lost directional control of vehicle due to wet road conditions. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left, crossed lane three and departed to roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a plastic impact attenuator. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the eastbound lanes of travel, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 attempted to follow the road curving to the right. V1 departed the road to the right as the road curved right. V1 returned to the road in the middle of the curve. V1 departed the lane to the left, continued forward and departed the road to the left. The front of V1 impacted the embankment of a ditch. V1 came to rest facing north in the ditch.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, two way roadway divided by a grass median. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a guardrail end with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then rotated counter clockwise impacting the back side of the guardrail with an unknown plane. V1 then overturned right side leading four-quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels facing west.

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway. As V1 was negotiating a right curve in the roadway, the vehicle departed the roadway to the left and entered into a ditch. V1 continued traveling forward in the ditch, exited the ditch, and re-entered the roadway to the right where it began to rotate in a clockwise direction. The vehicle then contacted a brick/concrete column,a mailbox post, and a sign post with the left side plane. After these impacts, V1 continued traveling sideways and contacted a utility marker and a 2 utility poles with the left side plane. After contacting the utility pole, V1 then rotated sharply in a clockwise direction and an unknown object contacted the undercarriage. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 and V2 were both traveling south in lane three on a four lane, non-positively divided roadway. V2 had slowed due to a traffic signal ahead when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 began to lose control and departed the left hand lane line and then the left (southeast) side of the roadway. V1 departed the roadway and contacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then overturned with its right side leading six quarter turns before coming to final rest on the roadway on its roof.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two on a median divided trafficway, with two lanes in the same direction. V1 departed the left side of the roadway into a non-paved median striking a culvert with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward crossing over a paved cut through in the median. V1 began rotating in a clockwise direction and proceeded to enter into a left leading roll. V1 rolled eight quarter turns coming to final rest in the non-paved median.

V1 was traveling southwest on a four lane, two way, median divided trafficway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway and approaching a concrete bridge. As V1 was crossing over the bridge it began to slide on the roadway due to the icy road conditions and began rotating in a counter clockwise direction. V1 departed its initial travel lane crossing over the left hand lane line and then departed the left (southeast) side of the roadway. V1 continued forward crossing the paved median and across both northbound lanes before departing the roadway and striking the concrete bridge guardrail face with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest facing north on the shoulder of the northbound roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, turning right at an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a four-lane divided roadway, negotiating a left curve. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 continued traveling on the roadway, departed the roadway to the left, and struck a guardrail face with its front plane and then its left plane before coming to final rest on the roadway. V2 continued traveling on the roadway and departed the roadway to the left, leading with its left plane. V2's left plane contacted a guardrail end and then it's front plane contacted the guardrail face. V2 rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southwest in lane three of a six lane divided roadway negotiating a left curve with V2 ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane three of a seven-lane divided roadway, changing lanes to lane one. V2 was traveling west in lane one of the same roadway. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicle came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane two of a four lane roadway attempting to make a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane two of a four lane roadway stopped at the same intersection waiting to make a left turn. The left plane of V1's trailer contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicle came to rest at impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 then rotated counter clockwise exiting the roadway at the north east corner of the intersection coming to rest facing west. V2 came to at the south side of the intersection facing south.

V1 was traveling east, following a two way, four lane road. V2 was legally parked, facing east, on the right side shoulder of the same roadway, at a bus stop. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing north. V2 came to final rest at impact, facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a five lane divided roadway attempting to crossover a four way intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane four of a four lane divided roadway attempting to turn left at the same intersection. Within the intersection, the left of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, non-divided roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left, where its frontal plane impacted the left plane of V2. V1 continued in a northern direction, and came to final rest in its original lane of travel. V2 traveled in a southern direction, rotating counter clockwise. V2 departed the road to the right, where its right plane impacted an embankment. V2 then cross both lanes of travel continuing to rotate counter clockwise, coming to final rest off the east side of the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 began to rotate counter clockwise, when it rolled six quarter turns right side leading. V1 came to final rest on its roof in the roadway.

Vehicles 1, 2, and 3 were traveling north in lane three of a three lane, two way roadway physically divided by a concrete barrier. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 3. The front of Vehicle 2 then contacted the back of Vehicle 1. All Vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane, undivided roadway approaching a four legged intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east pulling a trailer with a boat in lane one of a three lane, divided trafficway-median strip without a positive barrier approaching a four legged intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the trailer on V2 rotated clockwise and contacted the back of V1. V2 departed the roadway on the right and contacted the front on a light pole. The boat departed the trailer and contacted the back of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest off the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane three of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane one of a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the right side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection facing northeast.

V1 traveling northbound on lane 3 of a 4 lane, two-way, divided by a grass median with a left turn lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling on lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously. V1 front plane contacted V2 left plane. V1 rotated clockwise while V2 rotated counter-clockwise causing a side slap event. V1 right rear tire contacted V2 left plane. V1 continued traveling forward off the roadway contacting a sign with the front plane then coming to final rest off the roadway in the grass median on the northside of the intersection. V2 stayed on the roadway also coming to final rest on the northside of the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, median divided, roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the left. V1 returned to their initial lane of travel, and then departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail face off the roadway. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right side of V1 was contacted by the  front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, undivided roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling westbound on the same four lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V1 attempted to turn left into a private drive. While turning across the westbound lanes, the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest partially in both westbound lanes facing north. V2 came to rest in lane one facing westbound.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a four-way intersection.  V2 was traveling west on the same road as V1 approaching the same intersection.  As V1 began to make a left turn at the intersection the front contacted the front of V2.  V1 rolled back to final rest facing north.  V2 came to final rest facing west/southwest in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the second southbound lane of a seven lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was making a left hand turn from the left northbound lane of the same roadway at the intersection with a two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 contacted the right side plane of vehicle 2, both vehicles rotated vehicle 1 clockwise, vehicle 2 counter clockwise. As a result vehicle 1's left side plane contacted the right side plane of vehicle 2. After contact vehicle 1 traveled contacting a concrete curb with it right side plane and continued its rotation contacting a guardrail end off the roadway coming to rest off the roadway. Vehicle 2 came to rest after contact with vehicle 1 on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast in the first travel lane of a three lane undivided two way roadway, and was entering the intersection with a four lane non divided two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was in the first travel lane of the four lane cross street and also entered the intersection. The frontal plane of vehicle 2 contacted the right side plane of vehicle 1, both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching a sign controlled 3-legged intersection. V1 was attempting to make a left turn and head south. V2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 came to final rest on the southbound shoulder facing south, V2 came to final rest further north on the eastbound shoulder facing east.

V1 was traveling east in lane 3 on a six-lane, two-way roadway approaching a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 2 on a two-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles began to turn left in the intersection and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing east. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing north.

V1 was attempting to merge traveling west on a four lane, physically divided roadway with a positive barrier. While merging V1 lost control and departed the left side roadway, V1's right plane contacted the curb, and the guardrail. V1 continued further west and departed the left lanes, and the left side roadway. V1 contacted the jersey barrier with it's front plane, before coming to final rest facing westbound in the center lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 3 on a six lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection within an interchange area. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection and interchange area. Within the intersection, V1 turned left as V2 traveled straight and the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 came to rest in the southeast corner of the intersection facing south. V2 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the eastbound road edge where its right side contacted a guardrail face. V1 came to rest against the guardrail facing east.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane rural roadway when a cargo ejected from a northbound vehicle struck V1 (event 1). V1 departed the right side of the road and its front struck a utility box (event 2) and a utility pole (event 3). V1 came to final rest in a grass field facing south.

V1 was traveling west bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a mail box. V1 continued in a western direction where it impacted a warning sign, a shrub/brush, a second sign post, and a tree before V1 rolled over, driver side leading. V1 rolled two quarter turns, impacting a third sign, before coming to final rest on its roof, off the right side of the roadway.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it traversed a ditch, impacting the ditch with its frontal plane. V1 continued in a north western direction, where it impacted a small tree with its frontal plane, where it came to final rest off the right side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling eastbound on a 2 lane roadway. V2 was stopped in the roadway. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. V1 then rolled over to the left 2 quarter turns and came to a rest on it's roof. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the southbound lane of a two lane, two way, roadway with a two way left turn lane. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in the left turn lane. V2 turned left and the frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. V1 came to rest on the west side of the roadway heading southwest. V2 came to rest in the turn lane heading north.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, making a left turn at a four leg intersection. V2 was following behind V1. V2 changed lanes to the eastbound lane to pass through the four leg intersection and to pass V1. As V1 turned left the frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. V1 came to rest on the southwest corner of the intersection heading southeast. V2 came to a controlled stop heading west, west of the intersection on the eastbound shoulder.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. V1's roadway was controlled by a stop sign. After stopping at the sign, V1 continued to travel in the mentioned intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. The impact caused V1 to rotate counterclockwise. While spinning, the back of V1 impacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway; V1 facing north and V2 facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane road with a curve to the right, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. In the intersection the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. The impact caused V1 to rotate counterclockwise.   The right side of V1 then impacted the left side of V2 twice. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway; V1 facing east and V2 facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane three of an undivided six lane roadway approaching a four legged intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane three of a six lane, divided trafficway without a positive barrier approaching a four legged intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise. V2 rotated counter-clockwise. The left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it contacted a construction barrel.  V1 began to rotate clockwise.  V1 tripped and rolled over seven quarter-turns to the left.  V1 came to rest off the road to the right, on its right plane, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane one of an intersecting two-lane, undivided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection, where the front of V1 contacted the side of V2.  V2 began to rotate clockwise and departed the road to the left.  The right of V2 contacted a sign post.  V2 came to rest off the road to the north, facing northeast.  V1 came to rest on the edge of the intersection, facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was heading north on the same roadway.  V1 departed the left lane and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  V1 continued off the eastern road edge and rolled, right side leading, 6 quarter turns. V1 came to final rest off the roadway. V2 departed the eastern road edge and rolled, right side leading, 2 quarter turns. V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way undivided dirt roadway. V1 hit some bumps in the road and lost control departing the right roads edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a cluster of trees uprooting them. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest facing south west.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The right of V1 contacted the curb followed by a tree. V1 came to rest on the roadway, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V2 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 began a counter clockwise rotation. V2 rotated away from V1 to the right where it came to final rest partially off road facing northwest.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left while traveling west on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the intersecting roadway facing west. V1 departed its lane to the right and its front plane impacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the road heading north. V2 came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection. The front plane of V2 impacted the left plane of V1, causing both vehicles to rotate counterclockwise. V1 came to rest in the intersection heading east and V2 came to rest in the intersection heading south east.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 4 of a 6 lane undivided roadway, attempting to turn left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound in lane 3 of a 6 lane undivided roadway, attempting to crossover the same intersection.  Within the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest within  the intersection.

V1 was traveling north in the second of two lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. The driver of V1 lost directional control of the vehicle. V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the road on the left side. The left side of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier on the left side. V1 crossed back through both lanes and departed the road on the right side. The front of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier on the right side.
