V1 drove up and over the curb and traveled west on the eastbound lanes.V1 then traveled back across the westbound lanes towards the north road edge, where V1 impacted another curb. V1 came to rest on the curb facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a two way not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 3 lane not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the southwest corner of the intersection. V2 continued forward as it rotated clockwise and departed the southbound edge of the roadway where it traveled down into a ditch and its right side contacted the side of the ditch. V2 came to rest in the ditch facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-way, not physically divided roadway, stopped  in lane number 1 at the stop sign. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two-way, not physically divided roadway, passing through the intersection in lane number 1.  Vehicle 1's front collided with vehicle 2's left side while in the intersection. After initial impact, vehicle 2 departed the roadway on the southwest corner and vehicle 2's front made contact with a tree and came to final rest after impact. Vehicle 1 came to fine rest facing southwest, blocking the eastbound lane.

V2 was traveling south in lane 4 of a 6 lane positively divided roadway. V1 was traveling south on the same roadway behind V2 in lane 4.   V1 made contact with the rear of V2.  V2 departed the roadway to the right and made contact with bushes. V1 traveled to the left and made contact with the cable barrier guardrail before coming to rest in the median. V2 came to rest off road to the east.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound in lane one on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection simultaneously, and the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was parked facing north on the east shoulder of a 2 lane undivided one-way roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided one-way roadway. V1 entered the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest facing northerly, between the number 1 lane and the east shoulder. V2 came to rest facing northwest between the number 1 and number 2 lanes.

V1 was traveling North in lane one of a 2 lane lane divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left side.  The front plane of V1 struck a culvert/embankment at the end of a depressed median before rolling 4 quarter turns.  V1 came to final rest on its top plane facing West in the depressed median.

V1, V2, V3, V4, V5, and V6 were all traveling north on a one way, under construction highway, in lane one. V1 was behind V2, V2 was in front of V1 and behind V3. V3 was in front of V2 and behind V4, V4 was in front of V3 and behind V5, V5 was in front of V4 and behind V6, and V6 was in front of V5. Due to heavy traffic, the front of V1 impacted the back trailer of V2, the momentum created a chain reaction, where the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V3 was pushed forward and the front of V3 impacted the back of V4, the front of V4 impacted the back of V5, and the front of V5 impacted the back of V6. All vehicles came to rest in lane one facing a westerly direction in the construction zone.

V1 was traveling north on a divided two lane traffic way in lane two approaching V2. V2 was stopped in lane two on a divided two lane traffic way behind V3. V3 was stopped in lane two on a divided two lane traffic way behind V4. V4 was stopped in lane two on a divided two lane traffic way in front of V3. V1 was unable to stop and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2 and V2 was then pushed forward where the front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V3 was pushed forward and the front of V3 impacted the back of V4. All vehicles came to rest in lane two facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane physically divided roadway in lane two negotiating a curve with lane one closed due to construction. V1 departed the left road edge where the front impacted a traffic barrel. V1 then returned to the roadway and across lane two where the front of V1 impacted a concrete barrier. V1 bounced off the concrete barrier and the front of V1impacted it again before coming to rest in lane two facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 6 lane roadway, with a continuous left lane in lane number 3 intending to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 6 lane roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's front made contact with each other in the intersection. After initial contact, vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and vehicle 2 rotated clockwise, and vehicle 1's rear made contact with vehicle 2's left side. Vehicle 1 came to rest in lane 1 facing northwest. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in lane number 2 facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 3 lane median divided intersection in lane number 2. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a 3 lane, two-way not physically divided roadway, approaching the intersection in lane 1. Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's left side made contact with each other in the intersection. After initial contact, vehicle 1's right and vehicle 2's left side side slapped each other. Vehicle 1 came to rest facing northeast on the side walk. Vehicle 2 came to rest facing northwest in lane number 1.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a three-lane roadway. V2 was also traveling east, but in lane 2. V2 passed V1 and changed lanes to lane 1, directly in front of V1. The driver of V1 applied numerous counter-steering inputs and ultimately steered left as the front, left bumper corner of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2 (Event 1). V1 departed the right side of the roadway as its frontal plane impacted a guardrail (Event 2).  V1 rotated clockwise as its left side plane impacted the guardrail (Event 3) in a secondary impact sequence.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The frontal plane of V1 struck a deer in the roadway. The deer then rotated and struck the left side of V1. V1 came to rest on the westbound roadside heading west.

V1 was traveling in a northeast direction on a two-lane, two-way road that curved down to the left. An animal entered the road and V1 departed the right side of the road to avoid it. The front right plane of V1contacted a guardrail end causing it to rotate clockwise. While rotating, the front and left planes of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 came to rest back in the road across the center line heading north.

V1 was approaching an intersection while traveling northeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway that curved to the right. V2 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 crossed through the intersection and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and the left plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing northeast.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Then the left of V1 contacted the right of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 rotated clockwise after last impact and rolled one quarter turn to the left. V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was exiting a private drive attempting to make a left turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 5 lane two-way non physically divided roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 3 was traveling east on a 5 lane two-way non physically divided roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 1's right side and vehicle 2's front made contact with each other. Vehicle 1 rotated slightly counterclockwise after this impact and traveled into lane two of eastbound travel. The front of V1 then contacted the left side of V3. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west in lane two of eastbound travel. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing west in lane one of westbound travel. Vehicle 3 came to final rest facing northeast in the center of the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 departed lane of travel and then departed the roadway to the left. V1 continued traveling forward off the roadway when the front plane of V1 contacted an overpass wall. V1 rotated 2/4 roll and came to final rest on V1's roof on the edge of roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of  a 3 lane, two-way, undivided roadway with a two-way left turn lane approaching a four-way light controlled intersection. V2 was stopped facing east in lane 1 on the same roadway as V1.  V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 and V2 both came to final rest in the roadway at the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, undivided (two-way traffic) roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling west on the same four lane, undivided (two-way traffic) roadway in lane one. V1 departed it's lane to the left into the westbound lanes. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V2 then traveled backward after impact with V1, the back of V2 impacted a concrete barrier on the roadway edge to the north. V2 continued traveling backward and to the south. V2 departed all lanes to the south and the back of V2 contacted the concrete barrier on the roadway edge to the south. V2 came to rest against the concrete barrier facing northbound. V1 departed the roadway to the left and contacted the concrete barrier on the roadway edge with it's front. V1 came to rest against the concrete barrier facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane two of a two lane divided interstate roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 went into a clockwise rotation and departed the left road edge. V1 tripped and rolled right four quarter turns. During the roll V1's front and rear planes contacted unknown objects. V1 came to final rest off the left road edge.

V1 and V2 were both traveling northeast in lane one of a four-lane divided roadway, with V2 ahead of V1. There was a non-contact vehicle between V1 and V2. V1 changed lanes to lane two to avoid the non-contact vehicle, and then merged back from lane two into lane one. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane as V1 merged back into the lane. V1's right plane then contacted V2's left plane. V1 and V2 both departed the roadway to the right and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling on a 2-lane roadway not physically divided,  V2 was parked when V1 came off coarse of its travel and departed the travel lane to the right, V1 impacted its front plane into V2 rear plane.

V1 was traveling westbound on a eight lane physically divided highway in lane three. V2 was traveling westbound on the same highway in lane four. While changing lanes, V2's right plane contacted V1's left plane, both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two-lane, two-way, snow covered road. V1 lost control, rotated counterclockwise and departed the left side of the road. The front plane of V1 impacted a tree where it came to rest heading north off of the left side of the road.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling westbound, in lane one, of a four lane roadway. V2 and V3 were both stopped in the roadway. V1's front contacted V2's back plane. V2 then moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the back plane of V3. All vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in a four lane, two-way roadway making a left turn into a parking lot. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. After initial impact, V1's right plane sideswiped V2's front plane. V1 came to final rest facing southeast in the roadway. V2 came to final rest further eastbound.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two of a five lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the roadway on the right side. The right side of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one of a one lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and its front contacted a mail box post.  V1 continued forward and traveled across an intersecting roadway where its front contacted a guard rail face. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest in lane four on a seven lane roadway approaching a four-legged intersection to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling southeast in lane two on a six lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was traveling South on a five-lane (with center two-way turn lane) two-way roadway in lane one. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front impacted a guardrail. V1 came to rest off the roadway against the guardrail

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane, two-way roadway, negotiating a right curve. A bear entered the roadway from the right side. V1 steered left and departed its lane and the roadway on the left side and V1 contacted a tree with its front plane. The vehicle came to final rest in front of the tree.

V1 was parked facing south on the right side of a two lane, two-way, non-divided roadway, and was partially in lane one of the roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane one on the same roadway, and was negotiating a right curve in the roadway. V2's front plane then contacted V1's back plane. V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway on the right side, and V2 came to final rest in the roadway, in lane one.

V1 was traveling north in the second of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling north in the same lane ahead V1. The front of V1 contacted the left back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the lane.

V1 was traveling southbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway that was straight then curved to the right. V1 departed lane of travel to the left, continued traveling forward, departed the roadway also to the left. V1 traveled off the roadway contacting a tree with the front plane, rotating clockwise contacting a second tree with the left plane.

V1 was traveling southbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front plane of V1 impacted a utility pole.  V1 came to final rest off the edge of roadway with V1's front plane contacting the utility pole.

V1 was traveling North on a two lane, one-way, roadway. V2 was legally parked unoccupied on the right side of the roadway. V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest in its initial lane of travel still contacting V2. V2's final rest was same as impact.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and the departed the roadway to the left. V1 traveled off the roadway and possibly went airborne briefly as it crossed a creek. The left plane of V1 contacted a tree and then the front plane contacted the ditch. It came to final rest in the ditch near the second impact.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane road. V1 departed the left curb edge and its front plane contacted the corner of a concrete wall. V1 came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway headed towards a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane non-physically divided roadway headed towards the same intersection. While passing through the intersection, V1's front plane contacted V2's right side plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Both Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling eastbound on a 4 lane physically divided trafficway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 began to slow for traffic ahead.  Vehicle 1's front plane made contact to the rear plane of V2.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 came to final rest facing east shortly after impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane divided roadway (two west and eastbound lanes separated by a jersey barrier). The driver of V1 attempted to change lanes to the right and over-steered, entering the north shoulder. The driver steered left and re-entered the west travel lanes and then steered right again. V1 ultimately traversed the westbound lanes and departed the right (north) side of the roadway. V1 initiated a clockwise yaw as it initiated a four (4) quarter-turn rollover sequence, coming to rest on its wheels and facing east.

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a three lane, positively divided roadway. As the vehicle approached a newly constructed intersection, V1 departed its lane on the right side. The vehicle then drove over a painted lane divider and a concrete island, continued traveling forward, and then contacted a curb of another roadway with its left front tire. The vehicle then departed the roadway on the right side and traveled down a slight embankment, where its undercarriage contacted a gully. V1 continued forward through the gully and came to final rest in a dirt and grassy area approximately 42 meters right of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east on a three-lane divided highway. V1 was in lane one and V2 was in lane three. V1 entered V2s path when V2s front end struck the left side of V1 (event 1). V1 departed the north side of highway where its back end struck a bridge barrier (event 2). V1 returned to the highway and its front end struck the left side of V2 (event 3). V1 traveled across the highway and struck the bridge barrier, on the south side of the road, with its front end (event 4).

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the northbound lane of a two lane undivided roadway, and encountered icy conditions. As such, vehicle 1 lost control and departed the roadway to the right and contacted a tree with its frontal plane, rotating post contact clockwise. During the rotation, vehicle 1 contacted a second tree with its left side plane and came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane, not physically divided two-way roadway in lane two. V2 was traveling westbound along the shoulder, V2 then crossed the westbound lanes attempting to make a left turn into a business parking lot. V1 front plane contacted V2 left plane. V1 came to final rest on roadway facing westbound. V2 came to final rest on roadway in the eastbound lanes.

V1 was traveling westbound on a divided two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on three-lane divided roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing west, V2 came to final rest on the west shoulder facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 5 lane median divided traffic way, approaching the  intersection in lane number 3. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 7 lane two-way traffic way in lane number 3. Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's left side made contact in the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing southwest in the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southwest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way non-physically divided roadway attempting to make a left turn at a 3-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two-lane, two-way non-physically divided roadway. V1 begins to make a left turn onto the intersecting roadway. While navigating the turn V1's frontal plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was south on an undivided three lane road in lane one, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling north on the same undivided three lane road in lane one, negotiating a left curve. For an unknown reason V1 traveled towards the north bound lanes, and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. After the crash both vehicles spun counter-clockwise, V1 came to rest within the two way left turn lane and the south bound lane facing a northeast direction. V2 came to rest on the east shoulder facing a southwest direction.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a undivided/two way two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. V1 departed the road into a parking area in a clockwise yaw. V1's front plane contacted a wall and rotated clockwise where the front of V1 impacted the wall a second time. V1 came to final rest against the wall.

V1 was traveling east in lane two on a four-lane roadway with a 2-way center left turn lane. V1 departed its lane to the right and then departed the roadway. V1's front plane contacted a culvert and the vehicle went briefly airborne. V1 then began to roll along its left axis. V1 completed 4 quarter turns with its roll being interrupted when its right side struck an overhanging part of the adjacent roadway. V1 came to final rest on its wheels, off the roadway. The driver was fully ejected from the vehicle and came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection with north and south lanes controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling westbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway near the northwest corner facing westbound.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, four lane road, with a slight curve to the left. As V1 was negotiating the curve, V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a stop sign. Continuing forward, the front of V1 impacted a tree and then a guy wire. The guy wire severed the right side doors from the vehicle. V1 continued forward, impacting another tree, fully ejecting the driver. V1's engine caught fire before coming to final rest against a tree, facing west.

V1 was stopped in traffic, traveling northwest on a two way, five lane road with a curve to the right.  V2 was traveling behind V1.  The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1.   Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 was following V2. V2 stopped to make a left turn. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V2 pulled ahead and to the right, V2 came to final rest in a driveway. V1 pulled to the right and came to final rest in a driveway off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left, steered right then began to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the left road edge while rotating clockwise as it traveled down a snow-covered embankment and its left side contacted 2 trees. V1 then rotated counter-clockwise and its right side contacted a tree and its windshield was contacted by a tree branch. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 and V2 were both northbound in lane two of a three lane divided road. V2 was stopped ahead of V1 at a three-legged intersection. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway, facing northwest, in their original lane of travel.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and the right plane of vehicle 1 contacted a utility pole. Vehicle 1 continued forward and the front plane of vehicle 1 contacted another utility pole. Vehicle 1 came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a five lane, physically undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection in lane three. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a five lane, physically undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was turning left, traveling east when the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2 within the intersection. Vehicle 1 came to final rest within the intersection facing east. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway in the northeast corner and came to final rest after the front plane contacted a fire hydrant.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling west in lane one of a three-lane roadway (three westbound lanes with a cable guardrail that separates the three eastbound lanes). The front of Vehicle 1 impacted the back of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the roadway facing west. Vehicle 2 came to final rest off the north roadside, facing north.

V1 was traveling in a northwestern direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it impacted a tree with its right plane. V1 continued in a northwestern direction down an embankment, where its frontal plane impacted a tree and tree branches fell on the top of V1. V1 came to final rest off the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a one lane entrance ramp negotiating a right curve. V1 went into a clockwise yaw and departed the right road edge. The left plane contacted a pole and V1 continued off road and the left and rear planes contacted an embankment. V1 came to final rest off the right road edge.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V2 rotated clockwise, departed the road and struck a tree with the right plane.  This impact caused V2 to rotate counterclockwise and the right plane struck a wooden fence twice.  V2 came to final rest off the road facing west.  After the initial impact V1 rotated counterclockwise. Cargo from the bed of V1 fell out and struck V1 on the top left windshield header.  V1 came to final rest in the road facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection, making a left turn to travel southbound. V2 was traveling eastbound, in the mentioned roadway in lane one, passing through the intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 came to final rest facing southeast in the roadway. After the initial impact, V2 rotated counter-clockwise impacting a curb at the southeast corner of the intersection. V1 came to final rest at point of impact with the curb.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling westbound, in lane 3 of a 3 lane roadway that was physically divided with a concrete barrier to the left. V2 and V3 were stopped. V1's front contacted V2 rear plane. V2's front plane then contacted V3's rear plane. All vehicles came to final rest within the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound, on a five lane roadway with two way left turn lane, V1 was in lane one and V2 was in lane two. V1 departed their lane to the left. V1's left side contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 1. Vehicle 1 departed its lane of travel, making contact with legally parked Vehicle 2 with its front plane.  Vehicle 2 was pushed forward making contact with its front plane to the rear plane of Vehicle 3 which was also legally parked. Vehicle 2 and 3 were at final rest facing south. Vehicle 1 rotated slightly counter clockwise coming to final rest facing southwest just after impact with Vehicle 2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position with the intent of making a left hand turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same 5 lane non-physically divided roadway passing through the intersection in the lane 1 position. The front plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2. V1 came to final rest facing east near the east middle portion of the intersection. V2 continued through the intersection coming to rest at the side of the road facing north.

V1 was stopped facing west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway at a three leg intersection waiting to turn left. V2 was following V1 in the same lane. The frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder heading west. V2 came to rest on the right shoulder, behind V1, facing west.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane, two way, trafficway divided by a grass median with a cable barrier. V1 departed the road to the left, returned to the road, and departed the right side of the road in a clockwise yaw. V1 proceeded down an embankment striking the ground with its left front corner, and rolled, left side leading, six quarter turns ejecting the driver. V1 Came to rest on its top, with the right side contacting a fence, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a traffic sign. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west against the sign.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 made a left turn at the intersection, and departed the roadway to the right. The right front wheel of V1 impacted a curb and V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 on the same roadway. In the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southwest. V2rotated counter-clockwise and the trailer in tow contacted the left side of V2. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to make a left turn onto a private drive. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of the same roadway negotiating a left curve approaching the private drive. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 as it turned into the driveway. V1 rotated clockwise and V2 continued forward and to its right. The vehicles then side slapped with V1's right plane contacting V2's right plane. Both vehicles came to rest on the private drive side by side.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane two of a four-lane divided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling in the same lane, ahead of V1. V3 was also traveling in the same lane, ahead of V2. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 continued forward after impact and V2's front plane contacted the back plane of V3. All vehicles came to final rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane roadway. V2 was parked on the right side of lane one of the same roadway ahead of V1. V2 was not occupied. V1 departed the travel lane to the right and its front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  V1 came to rest in the roadway near impact. V2 departed the right road edge and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way unmarked roadway passing through a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling west bound on a two lane, two-way roadway crossing over the mentioned intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest facing northwest in the intersection. V2 came to final rest facing northeast in the roadway.

V1 was merging westbound, into a three lane, two-way roadway in lane one traveling westbound. V2 was traveling westbound on a three lane, two-way roadway. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest further westbound in the roadway.

V1 was traveling in lane one of the eastbound lanes on a four lane trafficway divided by a cable barrier. V1 struck a deer with its frontal plane. The deer went airborne and came down on the top plane of V1.  V1 came to rest on the right shoulder heading east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane one of the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 began a U-turn and departed the roadway to the west.  The front of V1 contacted a ditch.  V1 came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a traffic circle.  V2 was traveling north in lane one on a two lane undivided roadway approaching the same traffic circle.  As V1 made a right turn into the circle the front plane contacted the right plane of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counterclockwise after the initial impact causing the left plane of V1 to contact the right plane of V2 in a side slap fashion. V1 came to final rest on the right shoulder facing north.  V2 came to final rest on the roadway in the circle facing west.

V1 was traveling in a western direction, on a tow lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 was negotiating a slight curve to the right, when a deer entered the road from the left. The animal impacted the left side of V1. V1, departed its lane of travel to the left, where it left the roadway, and impacted a guardrail with its frontal plane. The area in front of the guardrail was built up with ice from previous storms. V1 traveled over the guardrail, where it rolled, left side leading, down a steep ravine. V1 rolled 6 quarter turns, before coming to final rest on its roof, on a private road at the bottom of the ravine.

V1 was driving eastbound, in lane 1, of a 5 lane, non divided roadway with 2 way left turn lane. Another vehicle in the west bound lanes hit an animal. The animal then came across the lanes and V1's front contacted it. V1 then pulled off to the side of the roadway and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two (2) of an undivided five (5) lane roadway (two westbound lanes, two eastbound lanes with a common left/right center turn lane). V1 traversed the lanes lines and entered lane one (1) before departing the left side of the roadway initiating a clockwise yaw. V1's left side impacted an overhead traffic signal pole a pole and the driver was ejected. The vehicle rotated rapidly clockwise around the pole as the vehicle split into two pieces. The rear box came to rest in the center of the roadway while the front continued westerly, impacting a concrete electric box with its right side plane, before coming to rest, facing easterly.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway with a two way left turn lane. Both vehicles were in the intersection and the front plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2. V1 came to rest near the point of impact facing east. V2 came to rest south of the intersection in the center turn lane facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane two, on a four lane, two way trafficway divided by a grass median and cable barrier. V2 was traveling east in lane one on the same trafficway. As V1 was pulling into lane one the frontal plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2. V1 came to a controlled stop on the right shoulder heading east. V2 rotated counterclockwise and departed the left side of the road and came to rest in the grass median heading northwest.

Vehicles 2 and 3 were stopped in traffic at an intersection traveling east on a 3 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V2 was behind V3. V1 was also traveling east on the roadway behind V2. The front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2. Due to impact, V2's front then made contact with the rear of V3. Final rests for all vehicles are at impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 was legally parked on the road facing north. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 left the scene. Vehicle 2 was pushed over the curb coming to final rest facing northwest after contacting another parked vehicle.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 3-lane roadway approaching an intersection to make a right turn. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 3 lane roadway approaching the same intersection to continue straight. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 then departed roadway at the south west corner of the intersection contacting a curb with 2 of its wheels. V2 came to rest on a residential lawn. V1 came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection facing west.

Vehicle was traveling westbound on a six lane physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was also traveling west on the same 6 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway also in lane 1 in front of Vehicle 1 stopped at the intersection with the intent of turning right. The he front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicles 1 and 2 came to final rest at impact facing west on the eastern side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling west in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was redirected to the the north and departed the roadway on the right side. V2 rolled over from right to top and came to rest off the road on it's top. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 continued west and the right side of V1 contacted a guardrail on the north road edge. V1 came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was southbound in lane 6 of 6 on a physically divided roadway when V1 changed to lane 5. V1 then departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier.  V1 then contacted the barrier with the right side.  V1's left side then contacted the same concrete traffic barrier. V1 came to rest on the shoulder facing south.

V1, V2, and V3 were all eastbound on a 3 lane roadway.  V1 in the first lane, V2 in the 2nd lane and V3 in the 3rd lane.  V1 departed its lane to the left and contacted V2. V2 attempted to avoid the collision with V1 and departed its lane to the left and contacted V3.  All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the third of five lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway approaching an exit ramp. V1 departed the roadway in the gore and the front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight left hand curve in the roadway. A non-contacted vehicle was traveling on the roadway in front of V1. V1 in an attempt to pass the non-contact vehicle departed the right hand (north) side of the roadway. V1 continued along the edge of the embankment until it contacted a rock embankment/culvert with its frontal plane. Directly after the first impact a small tree contacted the right side mirror of V1. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway. Roads were slippery due to icy wintery road conditions. Driver lost directional control and V1 started to rotate counter clockwise. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left and departed the roadway onto the raised median. The right side of V1 impacted a light pole on the median. V1 rotated clockwise around the light pole and came to rest at the light pole, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) right curved road. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left, crossed all lanes of travel and departed the roadway to its left. The left front wheel of V1 impacted a raised curb. The front of V1 impacted a low wall located on the median. V1 came to rest at the wall, facing southwest.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing southeast.
V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a deer with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the right side of the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road approaching a T-intersection. V1 was negotiating a curve to the left on a two-lane, two-way road while traveling west, passing through the same intersection. As V1 turned left at the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest at the point of impact. V2 came to rest west of the intersection.

V1 was traveling south in lane five of a six-lane, two way, positively divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the left side of V1 contacted a concrete barrier.  V1 crossed all travel lanes to the right and departed the roadway to the right.  The front of V1 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 came to final rest on the west shoulder facing southwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a four-lane divided highway. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane 4 of the same road, slowing for traffic. V1 changed lanes to the left, crossing into lane 4. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 departed the road to the left, and the front plane of V2 contacted the concrete median. V2 came to rest on the shoulder to the left. V1 came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling westbound passing a four way intersection on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way roadway. V1's front plane contacted V2 left plane. After initial impact V2 went into a counter clockwise rotation, departed the roadway on the left side. V2 right side contacted the curb, V2 continued further south off-road where it struck two poles with it's back plane before coming to final rest off road. V1 came to final rest off road facing south in a ditch.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 3 on a five-lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway exiting a business drive. V1 began to turn left into the parking lot. V2 began to turn left onto the road. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane transition roadway in lane one. As V1 approached the transition, V1 departed the left road edge and continued straight where the front of V1 impacted a Guardrail end. V1 came to rest stratelling the median and lane one facing north.

V1 was traveling west on a non-physically divided three lane trafficway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a physically divided two lane trafficway in lane two approaching the same intersection, preparing to make a left turn. As V2 attempted a left turn, V1 entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 then spun clockwise and came to rest on the right shoulder of the westbound lanes facing a easterly direction. V2 came to rest on the the right shoulder of northbound lane facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided two lane highway in lane one, behind V2. V2 was traveling south on the same physically divided two lane highway in lane one, in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward and came to rest on it's wheels of the right shoulder facing a southeast direction. V1 also came to rest on the right shoulder, facing a southeast direction.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling north on the same two lane divided roadway in lane two. V1 crossed its lane line to the right and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest partially in the number two lane facing west. V2 counter-clockwise and came to rest partially in the number two lane facing west

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 5-lane divided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a concrete jersey barrier. V1 came to rest on the paved shoulder facing west.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane to the right and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 was redirected left where it departed the left road edge into the dirt median and its front plane contacted a metal guardrail face. V1 continued forward and its left side contacted the guardrail face. V1 was redirected right and it re-entered the roadway, departed the right road edge, traveled down a shallow embankment and its front plane contacted a barb wire fence. V1 came to rest on the roadside facing west. V2 drove a distance and came to a stop on the right shoulder facing west.

V1 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane roadway. V2 was traveling north in the #1 lane of a 3 lane roadway. Both vehicles entered an intersection. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and traveled north. The front of V1 impacted a center median curb. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted a reflector. V1 came to rest facing north in the #3 lane of the southbound lanes. V2 after impact with V1 rotated counter clockwise and traveled west and came to rest facing west on the west side of the intersection.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a slight left hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the eastern side of the roadway, and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left while traveling east on two-lane, two-way road with a positive incline. V1 departed the right road edge and the right side of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest on the roadside facing north.

V1 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. A tree north of the roadway broke and fell over into the roadway. The tree fell on top of V1 where the top of V1 impacted the tree. V1 came to rest facing west in the #1 lane.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling north in lane five on a five lane, non positively divided roadway. V2 and V3 both slowed down for slower traffic ahead when V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. As a result of this contact, V2 was pushed forward and it's front plane contacted V3's rear plane. All three vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V2 was in the third travel lane of a three lane one way roadway, traveling East, stopped at a red traffic signal. V1 was traveling East, in lane 2 of the same roadway as V2, as V1 approached a non contact vehicle in lane 2, V1 swerved into the third travel lane to pass the non contact vehicle, V1 contacted its left side plane with the right side plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 came to rest on the roadway while vehicle 1 left the scene and continued traveling.

Vehicle 2 was stopped at a traffic light within the westbound left turn lane of a one way off ramp at the intersection of a five lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling in the second of three northbound lanes of the intersecting roadway. Vehicle 2 was contacted on its left plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 1 when turning left. Vehicle 2 came to final rest within the roadway intersection. Vehicle 1 continued traveling post impact northbound to an unknown location.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a one-way, two-lane roadway in lane one approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling northbound on a one-way, two-lane roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northeast, V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the right side roadway, V1 continues south and strikes a utility pole with its front plane.  V1 drove onto a snow bank. The snow bank caused V1 to become airborne, and initiated a left side leading rollover.  The left side of V1 then impacted a second utility pole.  V1 then continued its rollover onto the roadway, where it came to final rest facing southeast on its roof.

V1 was traveling westbound a four lane, two-way passing through a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a four lane, two-way roadway, attempting to make a left turn at the mentioned T-shaped intersection. V1's front plane contacted V2's right plane.  V1came to final rest in the middle of the intersection after impact. V2, after the initial impact with V1, rotated counterclockwise and departed the road at the northwest corner of the intersection. The front plane impacted a wooden utility pole where it came to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane two on a four lane, non-divided roadway, approaching a stop sign controlled intersection, intending to turn left.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane two of the intersecting three lane, painted median divided roadway, passing through the intersection.  Within the intersection the the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise then rolled over onto its right side and came to rest in the intersection, on the north side, facing west.  V2 came to rest within the intersection, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 2 lane roadway and approaching the intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane roadway and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, V1's front contacted the right side of V2.Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling Northbound on a 2 lane roadway, separated by a curb, and approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left and approaching an intersection. V3 was traveling westbound on a 2 lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the right and approaching an intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 then spun around clockwise. V3's front contacted V2's left side. V2 and V3 came to rest on the shoulders of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two way, two lane intersecting roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1. V1 continued in a southwest direction exiting the roadway and struck a small tree with the front plane before coming to final rest off the roadway. V2 came to final rest along the road edge at the southwest corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front plane contacted a ditch then the right plane contacted a tree before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two way, four lane undivided roadway in lane 2. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway in lane 1. Vehicle 1 departed the original lane of travel to the left. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing northeast and Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a three lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was stopped at the intersection facing east in lane one of the same three lane divided roadway. The driver of V1 voluntarily exited the vehicle after experiencing brake failure. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and its left side contacted the right side of V2. V1 continued forward and re-entered the roadway on the left side. V1 departed the roadway again where its left front, right front and right rear wheels contacted a curb surrounding an island. V1 continued forward after departing the island and its right front wheel contacted another curb. V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted a light pole. V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted a steel fuel pump guard. V1 rotated and its front contacted a fuel pump. V1 came to rest near the fuel pump facing southeast. V2 came to rest at its point of impact facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a five lane, two-way, physically undivided roadway in lane three approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a five lane, two-way, physically undivided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2 within the intersection. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was leaving a parked position traveling east bound in lane one of an undivided two lane roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling east bound in lane one of an undivided two lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 departed the roadway on the right side and contacted the front on a snow pile. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing east bound. V2 came to rest off the roadway facing east bound.

V1 was traveling in a north eastern direction, on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway with a negative grade. V1 was negotiating a curve to the left. The roadway at the time was ice covered. V1 left the roadway to the right, where it impacted a line of brush, a barbed wire fence, and a tree, before coming to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional road way with a slight curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a tree, causing V1 to rotate clockwise around the tree. V1 traveled across both lanes, and come to final rest on the north side of the roadway facing west bound.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a ditch with its frontal plane. V1 then rotated counterclockwise striking a fence post with its right side plane. V1 continued south striking a fence post with its frontal plane and then a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest near the point of impact with the tree, after rotating clockwise, heading southwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane two on a divided trafficway not divided by a positive barrier approaching an intersection to turn left. Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane one on a divided trafficway not divided by a positive barrier approaching an intersection. V1 turned left and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing west. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged sign controlled intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway at the southeast corner of the intersection. The left side of Vehicle 2 contacted a tree before coming to final rest facing west. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the east leg of the intersection facing southeast.

Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane two of a five lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane three of a five lane, undivided roadway, turning left at an intersection. V1 turned left and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing south. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling in lane one of a four lane undivided roadway. A non-contact vehicle was traveling in lane two on the same roadway. The non-contact vehicle attempted changed lanes to the right. V1 steered to the right. The right front wheel impacted the curb. Continuing on its trajectory, the front of V1 contacted a landscaping rock. V1 came to final rest in a ditch near the second impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was stopped facing north on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  V1 came to rest near impact, still facing northeast.  Vehicle #2 came to rest partially on the shoulder, still facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in the channelized left turn lane of a divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the same trafficway in lane two.  V1 began to turn left at intersection.  The right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest still in the intersection, facing west.  V2 began to rotate clockwise and came to rest still in the intersection, facing southeast.

V1 was traveling northwest following a two way, six lane road, in the second lane of travel, approaching a four way intersection. V1 attempted to turn right at the mentioned intersection, departing the roadway on the left. The front of V1 impacted a curb, and two signs before catching fire. V1 came to final rest off the roadway, facing northwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two way roadway. While negotiating a left curve going downhill, V1 departed the roadway on right side and struck three trees of varying sizes with the front plane before coming to final rest off of roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two-lane, two-way road approaching a T-intersection. V1 drifted over the left lane line and then departed the end of the road. The front of V1 impacted a tree causing it to rotate clockwise where it's front plane hit another tree. V1 came to rest off of the side of the road heading west.

V1 was traveling east in the first of one lane on a one-way highway on ramp.  V2 was traveling east in the same lane ahead of V1.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles departed the road on the right side. The front of V2 contacted a tree. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail end.  Both Vehicles came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a 3 lane physically divided roadway in lane 3. V1 departed the roadway to the left where, in a sideswiping manner, the left front fender/wheel contacted a concrete traffic barrier and simultaneously the left rear fender/wheel contacted the concrete traffic barrier. V1 began a clockwise rotation and the left back bumper corner contacted the concrete traffic barrier resulting in a rapid counterclockwise rotation. During the counterclockwise yaw, the front of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier, rotating off coming to rest within the roadway facing east.

V1 was eastbound on a 4 lane roadway approaching a 4 way intersection in lane 4. V2 was westbound on a 4 lane roadway in the 3rd lane, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane roadway, with a curve to the right. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a wooden bridge railing. V1 continued forward where it rolled right, 4-quarter turns, down a steep embankment before coming to final rest in a stream, on its wheels, facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road. V2 was traveling south on the same two way, two lane road. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 continued forward coming to final rest on the east side of the road facing north. V2 was pushed backwards by the impact and rotated clockwise before coming to final rest on the west side of the road facing north.
V1 was heading south in lane three of a physically divided interstate. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a barrier. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west on a wet four-lane divided highway. V1 was in lane four and V2 was in lane one. V1 entered lane one where its front end contacted the left side of V2 (event 1). V1 departed the north side of the road and its front contacted a concrete wall (event 2). V1 rotated clockwise and the left side struck a guardrail (event 3). V1 crossed all four lanes and its right side struck a concrete barrier (event 4). V1 came to final rest on the south side shoulder facing southeast. V2 came to final rest in the road facing east.

V1 was traveling west, leaving a business parking lot with the intention to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two of a four lane divided (no positive barrier) road, approaching an intersection. V3 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane undivided road (two-way traffic) and turned left the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left front corner of V1. V1 rotated counter clockwise and moved north into lane three of the north leg of the intersection. There it came to rest in lane three, facing north. After the impact with V1, V2 rotated counter clockwise and moved towards the southbound lanes of the north leg of the intersection. The left side of V2 impacted the front of V3 in a sideswipe impact. V2 continued and drove across the raised median. V2 came to rest in the left turn lane of the southbound lanes, north leg of the intersection, facing northwest. V3 came to rest within the intersection, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway (west) and then returned to the roadway before losing control of the vehicle. V1 then departed the left hand lane line and continued forward departing the left hand side of the roadway (east) striking a brush pile with its frontal plane. V1 then struck an unknown object with both its left side and right side planes. V1 continued forward coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling north a two lane undivided roadway in lane one behind V1. V1 slowed and pulled onto the northbound shoulder to get in better position to make a U-turn. As V1 began to make a U-turn, the left front side of V1 impacted the front right of V2. This caused both vehicle to bounce off each other and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the southbound lane facing a northerly direction. V2 came to rest in a driveway facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway. V2 was legally parked on the eastbound side of the roadway. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest on the roadway facing east. V2 came to rest at impact location.

V1 was traveling west in lane two of a four lane physically divided highway. V2 was stopped with traffic also in lane two. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise then rolled onto its left side and came to rest facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, four lane, median divided roadway in the second travel lane of the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left side of the travel lane, and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling North West in lane 3 of a 5 lane divided roadway approaching a traffic controlled tree leg intersection.  V2 was traveling on the same roadway, stopped ahead of V1.  V3 was traveling SE of the same roadway, stopped for the southbound traffic signal.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  V1 continued through the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V3.  All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 3 lane median divided roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left and its front plane contacted a pole. V1 came to rest in the area of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a two way roadway approaching a three leg intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same two way roadway. While V1 attempted a left turn, the right of V1 impact the front of V2. V1 continued to the southern leg of the intersection and came to final rest in the roadway facing south. V2 came to final rest shortly after impact facing east.

V1 was traveling north in the third of four lanes on a right curved, divided, two-way roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south in the first of four lanes on a left curved, divided, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. While in the intersection, V1 departed the lane on the left side and departed the intersection into the oncoming lanes. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise and came rest in the roadway. After the initial impact, V2 rotated counterclockwise and departed the west side of the road. The back of V2 contacted a pole and came to rest off the road to the west.

V1 was traveling east on a undivided two lane road in lane one, behind V2. V2 was traveling east on the same undivided two lane road in lane one, in front of V1. V2 began to slow down, and attempted to make a U turn. V1 traveled on the westbound lanes to overtake V2. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 continued off the north road edge and the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest on it's wheels in the agricultural field, facing a northeast direction. V2 spun clockwise and came to rest on it's wheels in the north dirt shoulder, facing north.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a four lane left curved roadway divided by a grass median.  V2 was traveling west in lane two of the same roadway.  V1 moved to lane two and partially off the left road edge. The front of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  Both vehicles traveled across both west bound lanes and off the north road edge.  V1 yawed left and struck a utility box with the left plane which caused the vehicle to rollover to the left and strike a utility pole with the top plane.
