Vehicle 1 than lost control and crossed lanes 1 and 2 and made contact with the concrete barrier on the southside of the road. After impact 2 vehicle went back onto the roadway and vehicle left side made contact with vehicle 3's front and vehicle 4 front in lane number 3.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. V1 traveled into the northbound lane and the left side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 then lost control and departed the east road edge while rotating clockwise. After V2 departed the roadway, V2 fell into a ditch and rolled left one quarter turn and came to rest on its driver side facing an easterly direction. V1 came to rest in the southbound lane facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane road. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. Continuing forward, V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a sign and then a utility pole. The impact with the pole caused V1 to rotate clockwise and move west. V1 came to rest facing east in a private yard near the pole impact.

V1 was traveling southwest following a two way, three lane roadway, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling southeast following a two way, three lane roadway, approaching the same four way intersection. Both vehicles entered the mentioned intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. After impact, V1 rotated counterclockwise before coming to final rest in the intersection facing east. After impact, V2 rotated counterclockwise, departing the roadway to the right. The right side of V2 impacted a pole before coming to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east in the first of two lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the second lane on the same road. V1 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 departed the location without stopping.  V2 departed the road on the left side and rolled, left side leading, 4 quarter turns and came to rest off the road.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was following V1 on the same roadway. V2 attempted to pass V1 as V1 attempted to pass a vehicle traveling in front of it. The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2 causing damage. V1 lost control and departed the left side of the roadway impacting a tree with the left side plane causing damage. V1 then impacted a tree with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the road at the second point of impact facing southwest. V2 came to final rest in the eastbound lane facing west.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was southbound on the same roadway approaching V1. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left impacting the front plane of V2 with the front plane of V1. V1 then rotated counter clockwise departing the south side of the road coming to final rest off the road facing southwest. V2 departed the north side of the road coming to final rest facing southwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south in southbound lane one of the same roadway.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing north. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and its right side contacted a snowbank on the edge of the southwest corner and came to rest facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two-lane neighborhood street. Vehicle 2 was legally parked on that same street facing west. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. V1 continued forward and its right side struck the left side of V2. All vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were both traveling east on a two-lane, one-way highway entrance ramp in the same lane. Vehicle 2 was stopped in traffic ahead of vehicle 1. The front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south stopped at a yield sign at an intersection on a one-lane divided roadway. V1 was crossing through a four leg intersection from the right turn lane, to continue south. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided road, passing through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V2 struck the left side plane of V1. V1 came to rest heading southwest in the eastbound lane just west of the intersection. V2 came to rest heading west, just west of the intersection, on the eastbound shoulder.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and then departed the roadway to the left. V1 impacted an embankment with its frontal plane and rotated counterclockwise. V1 rolled two quarter turns, right side leading, and contacted a fence with the back plane during the roll.  V1 came to rest facing east, on its top plane.

V1 was traveling north east in the #1 lane of a 2 lane divided trafficway. A non collision vehicle changed lanes from the #2 lane into the #1 lane near V1. V1 steered right and then left and lost control. V1 rotated counter clockwise while traveling north east. V1 departed the roadway and the right front tire of V1 impacted the center median curb. V1 traveled onto the center median and the right side impacted a tree. V1 continued north east where the right rear tire impacted the center median curb. V1 traveled across the center median while rotating counter clockwise. V1 came to rest facing north between the #1 and #2 lanes of the southwest bound lanes.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 1 lane painted median divided roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the lane to the left and entered the northbound lane. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the roadway to the right and came to rest in a field facing westerly. After impact, V2 steered left and departed its lane where it came to rest facing north west blocking the #1 southbound lane.

V1 was traveling north west in the #3 lane of a 4 lane roadway. V2 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. Both vehicles entered an intersection. The left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 continued north west into the south east lanes of traffic. V1 came to rest facing west in the #4 lane of the south east bound lanes. V2 continued through the intersection and came to rest in the #1 lane facing north.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection while towing a trailer. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, approaching the intersection. V1 began to turn left through the intersection. The right side of V1's trailer impacted the front of V2. V1's trailer became detached and came to rest in the eastbound lanes facing northerly. V1 came to rest in the westbound lanes facing northwesterly. V2 began to rotate clockwise and came to rest facing westerly in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a one lane unpaved dirt road. V1 was unable to navigate the roadway and began to reverse back down the roadway. V1 lost control and hit an embankment which caused V1 to roll left 3 quarter turns, then one quarter turn back onto its roof. V1 came to rest on its roof facing north.

V1 was driving west on a five-lane non-physically divided trafficway in lane two approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two-lane non-physically divided roadway stopped at an intersection, waiting to turn left. As V1 entered the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest in the middle of the intersection facing south. V2 came to rest in the middle of the intersection facing southwest.

V1 traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road when it made a left turn onto a two-lane, two-way side road. V2 and another vehicle were parked on the side road facing north. V1 departed the road to the right and its front plane impacted the rear plane of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the road. V2 was pushed forward and its front plane impacted the rear of the vehicle parked in front of it. V2 came to rest near its second impact. The other parked vehicle traveled off of the left side of the road where it came to rest.

V1 was traveling north on a snow-covered, two-lane, two-way road attempting a left turn onto a side street. V2 was traveling east on a snow-covered, two-lane, two-way road attempting to to turn right at a T-intersection. After making the right turn, V2 was traveling south when V1 crossed over the left lane line. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 and both vehicles came to rest in the road at the point of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane divided highway in lane 2. V1 entered an area of the road that curved left and added a merging on-ramp lane. V1 departed the road to the left. The right plane of V1 contacted a guard rail face. V1 mounted the guard rail and continued SW. The front plane of V1 contacted first one, then a second breakaway post. V1 dismounted the guard rail to the right. The front plane of V1 contacted a fence. V1 came to rest off road to the north.

V1 was traveling north west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south east on the same roadway. The front left tire of V1 fell off of V1. The undercarriage of V1 contacted the ground and came to final rest on the roadway. The tire from V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V2 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 caught fire. V1 pulled into a parking lot and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane three, on a three lane, non-positively divided roadway, turning left at an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane two, on the same roadway, passing through the intersection. V1's right side plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left hand (north) shoulder and contacted V1 on its left side plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east, negotiating a left curve, in lane one of a two lane not physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway right where the rollover event initiated. V1 came to rest off  the roadway on its side plane, unknown number of quarter turns.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the end of a T-intersection.  The front of V1 contacted a tree.  V1 came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right hand (south) side of the roadway contacting a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal plane. V1 continued to travel down the cable barrier guardrail contacting four posts before it came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, undivided (two way traffic) roadway in lane one. V1 lost control due to icy conditions, and departed the roadway to the right. V1 was rotating clockwise and the front of V1 impacted a fence post. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and impacted two fence posts with it's left side. V1 came to rest against the fence posts facing northwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V1 lost control due to icy conditions and departed the roadway to the left. V1 then impacted a metal pipe fence with it's front. V1 then impacted the same fence with it's left side. V1 came to rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a three lane, non-positively divided roadway. As the vehicle was negotiating a left curve in the roadway, the vehicle departed the roadway on the right side. V1 then contacted a signpost and a mailbox post with its front plane. The vehicle then crossed over a private driveway and continued forward across a grass embankment for approximately 65 meters. V1 then struck a tree with its front plane and began to rotate in a counterclockwise direction contacting another tree with its right side plane. The vehicle then struck another a tree with its right side plane and began a right side leading rollover. V1 rolled over two-quarter turn onto it's right side, slid backwards on its's right side down an embankment, and came to final rest at the base of the embankment on its top.

V1 & V2 were both traveling north in lane two on a six lane, non positively divided roadway. V2 slowed down due to other traffic and V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to final rest half way in lane two and lane three. V2 came to final rest in lane two.

V1 was traveling eastbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, not physically divided, two-way roadway negating a curve. V1 departed lane of travel to the left, departed roadway to the left and continued traveling forward off the roadway. V1 contacted small shrubs with the front plane, drove over a block retention wall contacting a post with the front plane and a cable utility box with the left plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway with the right plane against a tree.

V1 was traveling northeast on lane 1 of a 3 lane, two-way, not physically divided with a left turn lane roadway approaching an "X" intersection. V2 was traveling north on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 enter the intersection simultaneously. V1 right plane contacted V2 front plane. V2 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the roadway on the northeast corner and struck a post with the front plane.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane, undivided roadway. A deer contacted the left of V1, then the deer contacted the left again. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way roadway after making a right turn. V2 was traveling southeast stopped at intersection waiting for the traffic light. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 came to final rest at point of impact on roadway facing northbound. V2 came to final rest at point of impact facing southbound.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way unmarked roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left side, V1's front plane then struck a utility pole. V1 came to final rest off roadway after impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four-lane roadway, V1 was traveling behind V2 in lane two. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing westbound.

V1 was traveling southeast, in lane 3, of a 6 lane roadway with 2 way turn lane. V2 was traveling on the same roadway, Northwest bound, in lane 1. V1 turned left. V1's right side was contacted by V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane 3 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection intending to turn left. V2 was traveling southeast in lane 2 on a 5-lane roadway approaching the same intersection intending to continue straight. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the southeast corner of the intersection where its left side plane contacted a stop sign post. V1 then came to rest facing west. V2 rotated clockwise as it continued forward where it came to rest off the roadway facing south.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling westbound on 6 lane physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection. Vehicle 1 was attempting to make a right had turn at the intersection. The unknown plane of V1 made contact with the right plane of V2. V2 came to final rest facing west just after impact. V1 fled the scene.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 3 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on the same 3 lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in unknown lane 2 position approaching the same intersection. V1 departed lane of travel left side passed through the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 continued south and the right side of V1 made contact with the left side rear passenger side of V2. V1 came to rest still facing south. V2 came to rest still facing north after impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane two position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on the same four lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane two position.  As the two physically were approaching each other from opposite directions Vehicle 1 began to rotate clockwise.  The left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  The impact cause Vehicle 1 to rotate back clockwise and Vehicle 2 began to rotate counter clockwise.  The left plane of Vehicle again made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east just after impact.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing west just after impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a three-lane divided highway. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane 1 of the same highway. Vehicle #3 was traveling south in lane 3 of the same highway. V1 partially departed its lane to the left. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 departed the road to the right. V1 crossed over the road, and began slowing to come to rest on the left shoulder. The front plane of V3 contacted the back plane of V1. V3 rotated counter clockwise and departed the road to the left. The front plane of V1 contacted an embankment on the median. V1 came to rest on the shoulder to the east. V2 came to rest off-road to the west. V3 came to rest in the median to the east.

V1 was heading north on a four lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was heading south on the same roadway. Both vehicles entered into the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane one of a three-lane divided roadway with a positive barrier. V2 was stopped for traffic ahead. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, physically undivided roadway in lane one approaching a three legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a four lane, physically undivided roadway in lane two approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was turning right, crossed the center line and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a not-physically divided two-way roadway approaching a T-intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound, in a two lane, unmarked roadway making a right turn. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V1 came to final rest further south in the roadway. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, one-way roadway entering a highway entrance ramp. V1 departed the roadway to the left, where V1's front contacted a concrete barrier. V1 then departed the roadway to the right. V1's front contacted V2, a piece of construction equipment, before coming to final rest off of the roadway and catching fire.

V1 was traveling southwest following a two way, two lane road with a curve to the left. As V1 was negotiating the curve, it departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a sign. Continuing forward, the front of V1 impacted an embankment. V1 came to final rest on the side of the road, facing south.

V1 was traveling east in lane three of a two way, four lane divided roadway attempting to crossover an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one of a tow lane divided roadway attempting to turn  left at the same intersection. While V2 was negotiating a turn to the left in the intersection, the right plane of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 began to rotate clockwise and the right of V1 contacted the right of V2. V1 continued through the intersection while rotating clockwise and crossed through a island on the east leg of the intersection, impacting a stop sign with its left plane. V1 came to final rest in the east leg of the intersection facing southwest. V2 came to final rest in the middle of the intersection facing southwest.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling southbound on a five lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, which is a right turn lane.  Vehicle 2 came to a stop and the front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing south at impact.  Vehicle 2 fled the scene.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a five lane non-physically divided roadway intending to turn left from lane 3.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a five lane non-physically divided roadway intending to pass through the intersection in lane 2.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing southwest near the center of the intersection.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southeast near the southeast portion of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed its travel lane crossing over the left lane line. V1 departed the western road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree and continued on. V1 contacted a second tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway following V2. V2 was stopped in the roadway attempting to make a left hand turn. V3 was traveling south on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. Then the left plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 crossed the left lane line, crossing paths with V3. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the front plane of V3. V2 came to final rest on the roadway. V3 began in a clockwise yaw departing the western roads edge. V3 rolled 1 quarter turn, coming to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two of a five lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane one of a three lane roadway approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing northeast. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two way, four lane, non-physically divided roadway in lane two. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a two way, four lane, non-physically divided roadway in lane two. Vehicle 1 lost control and departed the original lane of travel on the left. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing northwest; Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing southwest.

V1, V2 and V3 were east bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V3 had stopped in the lane of travel to make a left hand turn into a driveway. V2 stopped behind V3. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane. V2's frontal plane then impacted V3's rear plane. V2 then departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted a guard rail. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact. V2 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway next to the guardrail. V3 came to a controlled rest on the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were both traveling north in lane two on a three-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-leg intersection with a traffic light. Vehicle 1 was stopped ahead of vehicle 2. The front end of vehicle 2 contacted the back plane of vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway facing north before the intersection.

V1, V2 and V3 were all eastbound on a six-lane, one-way, roadway. V1 was traveling in lane three behind V2 and V3. V2 was stopped in lane two and V3 was stopped in lane three. V1 departed its lane to the right and its front struck the rear of V3 (event 1). V1 continued forward when its right side swiped the left side of V2 (event 2). V1s right side struck V2s left side again (event 3) before it came to final rest on the road.  V2 and V3 also came to final rest on the road facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane divided (with positive barrier) highway. V2 was traveling in lane two of the same highway. V1 changed lanes into lane two. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 continued to drive and did not stop. V2 departed the roadway to the south where its front end struck a concrete traffic barrier.  V2 re-entered the road, crossed all lanes of traffic and departed the road to the north. The front of V2 impacted the face of a guard rail. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the north shoulder of the highway, facing north.

V1 was southbound on a one lane private drive approaching an intersection. V2 was eastbound on a 3 lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After impact, both vehicles spun clockwise before coming to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the second of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling north in the first of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the road, north of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a single lane exit ramp. V2 was traveling north in the same lane ahead of V1. V1 lost traction and began to rotate clockwise. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The front of V2 contacted the concrete traffic barrier on the left road edge. The left side of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane road. The roadway was ice covered at the time of the crash. V1 lost control and departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole before coming to final rest on the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane divided roadway, in the number two lane. A non-contact vehicle was traveling north bound on the same road in the number one lane. As V1 was negotiating a curve to the right, the non-contact vehicle entered V1's lane of travel. V1 departed the roadway to the left. V1 returned to the roadway, rotated counter clockwise, departed the roadway a second time to the left. V1's frontal plane impacted a cable barrier guardrail. V1 returned to the roadway, crossed both lanes of travel, departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a guardrail face. V1 came to rest on the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two of a five lane roadway with a two-way left turn lane not divided by a positive barrier. V1 departed the lane on the right side and departed the roadway on the right side and contacted the front on a tree. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, rural roadway, approaching a three leg Y intersection. V1 went straight, proceeding across the grass island in the center of the Y intersection. V1 crossed over the intersecting road, continued east, where it struck a barbed wire fence with its front. V1 continued traveling east where it became airborne and struck a tree with its front plane. V1 then struck the ground with its front plane as it landed. V1 then struck a tree with its top and rolled, left side leading, five quarter turns, and came to final rest heading west, on its left side.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, five lane, guardrail divided roadway. V1 began to swerve on the roadway before departing the left hand (south) side of the roadway and contacting a cable barrier guardrail with its frontal and left side planes. V1 continued forward a short distance before coming to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 attempted to merge to the right. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. After the initial impact, V1 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the right where its rear plane contacted a building before coming to rest. V2 came to rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were heading west on a two lane undivided roadway. V2 began to brake to attempt to avoid collision with object in roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane four of a four-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane three of the same trafficway.  V1 began to turn left at intersection. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rolled over two quarter-turns to the left and came to rest on its roof facing southeast on the edge of intersection.  V2 came to rest still facing north on the edge of the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane two of a four lane traffic way, divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane three of a four lane traffic way, divided by a positive barrier. V1 departed the lane on the left side. The back of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and rolled on the left side two quarter turns and contacted a concrete traffic barrier. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast. V2 came to rest on its roof facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in a channelized left turn lane.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane three of a three-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier. V1 began left turn at intersection. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise, and right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 3. Vehicle 2 was also traveling east on the same roadway in lane 3 in front of V1, stopped in traffic. The front of V2 contacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest at impact still facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast on a 2 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection to make a left hand turn upon stop. Vehicle 2 was traveling southeast on a 5 lane lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position passing through the same intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection the front plane of V1 made contact with the right plane of V2. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise coming to final rest facing east near the point of contact. Vehicle 2 passed through the intersection coming to final rest facing east shortly after impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a 4 lane lane physically median divided trafficway in the lane 2 position approaching a roundabout.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a 2 lane non physically divided roadway traveling in the lane 2 position approaching the same roundabout with the intent to pass through.  Both vehicles 1 and 2 entered at the same time.  The left plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2.  V1 was deflected to the east. V2 came to final rest shortly after impact and came to final rest facing northeast at the southeast region of the roundabout.

V1 made a left turn out of a driveway onto a four lane, two way roadway. While traveling east, V1 departed the roadway to the right and struck a utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest in the roadway facing south.

Traveling eastbound in lane 1 of a 2-lane, 2-way roadway, V1 attempted a passing maneuver around eastbound V3. V2 was traveling westbound in lane 1 of the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V2 was deflected off the right side of the roadway, coming to rest. V1 was diverted right, departing the roadway. V3 avoided the event between V1 and V2 by departing the roadway to the right, however, off the roadway to the right, the front left of V3 contacted the right side of V1 resulting in V1 rolling over left side leading and coming to rest on its roof.  V3 came to rest off the roadway shortly after impact with V1.

V1 was traveling southbound, in lane two, on a five lane roadway with a two way left turn lane. V2 was traveling northbound, in lane two, of the same roadway. V1 began to hydroplane. V1 departed its lane to the left. V1 then departed the center lane to the left. V1's front contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling in lane three,eastbound, of a three lane physically divided roadway. V2 was parked on the left shoulder of the same roadway. V1 departed it's lane line to the left. Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane one of a one way roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane two of a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a 5 lane roadway not divided by a positive barrier approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling south in the sixth of six lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V1 was traveling east in the first of four lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway attempting to turn left into a private drive. V2 was traveling east in the second lane of the same road. V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling in the opposite direction of V1, on the same two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 was traveling west on a 5 lane (with middle turn lane) two-way roadway in lane two.. V2 was eastbound on the same roadway in the 1st lane. V1 was traveling northeast in lane three of a five-lane divided roadway, negotiating a curve, and passing through an intersection. V1 and V2 were both traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane divided roadway with a positive barrier negotiating a right curve. V1 was ahead of V2. V2's front plane contacted V1's rear plane . Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, passing through a light controlled intersection. V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to cross over an intersection. V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, two-way unmarked roadway. V2 was parked in the southbound side of the same roadway facing northbound. V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway stopped in the roadway attempting to make a left hand turn into a private driveway. V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating right hand curve. A moose entered the roadway from the southern road edge. V1 was traveling North on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front impacted two trees before coming to rest off the roadway to the right.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  V1 departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a ditch.  V1 came to rest off the road to the right, facing north.

V1 was stopped traveling east in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway and departed the roadway to the right contacting a mailbox with its frontal plane. Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane three of a three lane roadway, divided not by a physical barrier. V1 departed the road on the left side. The front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east in an unknown lane of a 5 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching a four-way light controlled intersection. V1 was traveling north, on a 2-lane roadway and approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling east, on a 4 lane, two-way roadway in lane 2. Within the intersection, V1's front contacted V2's left side. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of five lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway ahead in lane 3. V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right (north) shoulder. V1 was traveling westbound on a three-lane, two-way roadway attempting a left turn into a private business. V2 was traveling eastbound on the mentioned roadway. V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 contacted a cable barrier guardrail with its front and right side planes. V1 then began to rotate in a clockwise direction where it rolled one quarter turn with its left side leading. V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two of a four-lane roadway approaching an intersecting street. V2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 was traveling westbound on a four lane roadway, in lane four approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway, in lane two approaching the same intersection. Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane two of a two lane, divided trafficway without a positive barrier. V1 departed the roadway on the left side and contacted the front on a guard rail. Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a three lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier with a two-way left turn lane. V1 came to rest on the left side in a private drive facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound from an alley with the intent to turn right (south) into the intersecting roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 1.  As Vehicle 1 entered into the roadway, the front plane made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 2 continued through the intersection coming to final rest facing south near the edge of the roadway.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing southeast shortly after impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position with the intent of making a left hand turn at the intersection. Both vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2.  Vehicle1 came to final rest shortly after impact facing roughly west.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest at impact facing south.

V2 traveled southwest where it came to rest facing a westerly direction,partly on the median curb and lane two. V3 came to rest at the beginning of the intersection within lane two facing a westerly direction. V4 came to rest at the beginning of the intersection facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a undivided two lane road in lane one negotiating a left turn. For an unknown reason V1 departed the right road edge and the front of V1 impacted a sign. V1 then traveled southeast, down an embankment into a agricultural field, where V1 rolled left side leading six quarter turns, before coming to rest on it's roof facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the right. V2 was traveling on the same road traveling west. V1 departed its lane to the left and its front plane impacted the front plane of V2. Both vehicles rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the road, heading in their original direction of travel.

V1 was heading north on a divided roadway with one northbound lane. V2 was heading south on a three-lane, two-way road with one lane heading south. V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 2-lane roadway. V2 was also traveling in lane 1 of the same roadway when the front end of V1 contacted the rear end of V2. V1 was straddling the west road edge line and facing south at final rest. V2 came to rest on the west shoulder and was also facing south.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 2 way non divided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and then departed the left side of the road. The front front plane of V1 then struck a wall and continued south with its front plane striking a garbage can and a portable basketball hoop. V1 pushed the garbage can and basketball hoop south into V2. V1 front plane struck the front plane of V2. V2 was pushed south approximately 1 meter before coming to rest against the left side curb. V1 came to rest facing south after traveling approximately 1 meter.

V1 was traveling north when it entered an off ramp that was curved to the right. V1 departed the left side aof the roadway and traveled down an embankment prior to its left side plane impacting a tree (Events 1 & 2). V1 continued in a forward trajectory as its right side plane impacted another tree (Event 3) and its front right bumper corner impacted a 4th tree (Event 4). V1 rotated counterclockwise as its right side plane impacted another tree (Event 5) before coming to rest facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, five lane roadway, in the second travel lane, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling east following a two way, six lane trafficway, in the second lane, approaching the same four way intersection. As V1 was passing through the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. The impact caused V2 to rotate clockwise. Continuing forward, the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway, both facing southeast.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a pole with its right side plane, and then the ground with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest off the roadway heading north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 2-lane, undivided trafficway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling south in an intersecting 2-lane, undivided trafficway. Both vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise, V2 rotated clockwise and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  The goose-neck trailer V1 was towing became unattached and contacted the left plane of V1.  V1 departed the roadway near the southwest corner of the intersection.  The left of V1 contacted a sign.  V1 came to rest near this impact, facing west.  V2 also departed the roadway near the southwest corner of the intersection.  The left of V2 contacted a sign post, a utility box and a pole in succession.  V2 then rotated counter-clockwise and right of V1 contacted another utility box.  V2 came to rest near this impact, facing east.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left while traveling westbound, in lane two, of a three lane roadway. V1 departed its lane and then all eastbound lanes. V1 began to yaw counterclockwise. V1's front contacted an embankment before coming to a final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane four of a four lane roadway, divided without a physical barrier, turning left at an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane one of a three lane roadway, divided without a physical barrier, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing west. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling east, in lane one of a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1. V1 rotated in a clockwise direction striking the right side of V2 again with its left side plane. V1 came to a final rest partially off of the roadway. V2 rotated in a counter clockwise direction crossing through the non-paved median of the roadway and came to a final rest on the westbound roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane two of a two-lane divided highway. V1 departed the roadway to the left entering a grass median. V1's front plane and right side contacted a cable barrier. V1 continued traveling forward through the cable barrier and coming to final rest facing north on the westbound roadway.

V1 was traveling South in lane 2 of a 4, two-way, not physically divided roadway with both left and right turn lanes approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling West in lane 2 of 4, on a two-way not physically divided roadway with both left and right turn lanes approaching the same intersection. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection simultaneously, V1's front plane struck V2's right plane. V1 then rotated clockwise striking V2's right side with V1's left side. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 3 lane on a two-way, not physically divided roadway with a left turn lane approaching a sign controlled 3-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 both entered the intersection at the same time. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 and V2 both came to final rest in the intersection.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two lane, undivided roadway. V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one. V1 lost control and began to yaw in a clockwise rotation. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a tree. V1 rotated clockwise and the front of V1 impacted an iron fence. V1 then rotated clockwise and impacted another tree with its left side. V1 traveled north while rotating clockwise and the back of V1 then impacted a smaller tree. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and came to rest in the grass right of the roadway facing southeast.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling ahead of V1, V2 stopped for traffic ahead. The front of V1 then impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane one facing eastbound.

Vehicle 1 traveling northbound from a business parking lot attempting to enter into a 5 lane roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  As V1 entered into the roadway the left front plane made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest facing east in lane 1 of the roadway.  Vehicle 2 deflected to the north and came to final rest in lane 2 of the same roadway facing east.  Both vehicles came to final rest just east of the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way, 2 lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two way, 2 lane, undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, V1 was turning left. V1's left side contacted V2's front. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling south and cresting a hill on a two lane, two way, roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road and struck a fence with its frontal plane. V1 continued southwest through the fence and struck a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway heading south.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, four lane, divided trafficway. V1 departed the left side of the road striking a cable barrier with its frontal plane. As V1 struck the barrier it rotated counterclockwise and rolled one quarter turn right side leading, before coming back onto its wheels. V1 came to rest partially on the left shoulder of the road, on its wheels, heading northwest.

V1 was following V2, in lane one of the westbound lanes, on a two way, four lane, divided trafficway. The front plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest in their original travel lane heading west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection in a residential area. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection turning left and departed the roadway on the right side. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a tree and came to final rest facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane two on a three lane roadway, physically divided by a concrete barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the same direction, on the same roadway, in lane two behind V1. Vehicle began to change lanes to the left when it rotated counter-clockwise, departed the left road edge and its front plane contacted a concrete barrier.  Vehicle 2 continued to rotate counter-clockwise, entered the roadway and its left side was contacted by the front of V1. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and its left side contacted the left side of V1.  Vehicle 2 then departed the left road edge again where its back plane contacted the concrete barrier. V2 came to rest on the road facing east. V1 continued forward and came to rest on the road facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane roadway approaching a light controlled intersection. V1 entered the intersection where it crossed over 4 lanes of travel before departing the north quadrant of the roadway. V1 Impacted a raised curb with its front tires, then contacted a guardrail with its frontal plane. V1s left rear tire then contacted the raised curb. V1 started a counterclockwise yaw while traveling through the guardrail. V1 impacted a light pole with its right front, then contacted a small tree with its left rear. V1 then contacted a rectangular pole with its left rear before coming to rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both traveling northeast on a two lane one way roadway in the lane 1 position. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest shortly after impact facing northeast on the right shoulder of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position negotiating a curve to the right. V2 was traveling north west on the same two lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position negotiating a curve to the left. The front left of V1 contacted the front left of V2. Due to impact V1 yawed in a counter-clockwise rotation approximately 50 degrees departing roadway right side coming to rest straddling the edge of the roadway facing north east. V2 also departed roadway left side coming to rest still facing north west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position attempting to make a left hand turn from the lane two position. Vehicle 2 was traveling westbound on a three lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position passing through the intersection. Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection. The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing northeast at the northern portion of the intersection. Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise coming to final rest at impact facing northwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the roadway on the left impacting a guywire with its frontal plane. The front and left side of V1 impacted three trees before reentering the roadway. V1 crossed the roadway and came to final rest in its original travel lane facing west.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge. The undercarriage of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 continued off the roadway and its frontal plane contacted a bush. V1 came to final rest up against a pile of used tires off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left travel lane and departed the western road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a 2 trees.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest still on the roadway, facing east.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway coming upon a right curve. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 traveled through a yard before impacting a barn with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 traveled through the wall of the barn doing damage to the front, left, right, and top sides of V1. V1 came to final rest in the barn facing southeast.
V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the west side of the road facing south.

V1 was descending a hill while traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left. V1 failed to negotiate the curve and departed the right side of the road where its right plane impacted a sign. As V1 continued, its front plane impacted a tree, causing it to rotate clockwise and roll one quarter turn, left side leading where it came to rest off of the right side of the road heading east.

V1 was traveling west in lane three on a divided road with three lanes going west and three lanes going east while approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped while traveling east in lane three on a divided road with three lanes going east and three lanes going west while approaching the same intersection. V1 turned left at the intersection and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. Both vehicles rotated clockwise, coming to rest in the intersection. V1 came to rest heading west and V2 came to rest heading south.

V1 was driving south on a non-physically divided two lane road. V1 departed the roadway on the right hand side. While departing the roadway V1's front plane contacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway. The right front tire contacted a large rock in the road. V1 came to rest in the eastbound lane facing east.

V1 was northbound on a 3 lane roadway in lane 1. V2 was legally parked on the right shoulder. V1 departed it lane to the right and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the second of three lanes on a divided, two-way roadway approaching an intersection with a private drive. V2 was traveling south in the third of three lanes on the same road attempting to turn left at the intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After the initial impact, both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was passing through an intersection while traveling south in lane three of a six lane divided roadway with four lanes heading south and two lanes heading north. As V1 passed through the intersection to make a left turn, it departed the road to the right, impacting a curb with its right front wheel. V1 continued to travel through a parking lot where it impacted a sign pole with its front plane. V1 came to rest against the sign pole in the parking lot.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the road impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then continued northeast traveling through a field impacting another ditch with the frontal plane coming to final rest at the point of impact facing northeast.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling into a ditch impacting the frontal plane causing damage. After the initial impact, the undercarriage impacted the ditch. V1 then continued southeast coming back onto the road coming to final rest facing southeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast in lane one of an intersecting, two-lane, one-way roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and the left of V1 contacted the right of V2.  V1 came to rest facing southeast on the edge of the intersection.  V2 came to rest facing east on the edge of the intersection.

V1 was traveling in a southeasterly direction on a designated north/south not physically divided (two-way) trafficway in lane 1 (of two lanes) when it departed the road on the right. V1's right front wheel/tire contacted a curb, followed by its left front wheel/tire. V1 continued in a southeasterly direction where its front end contacted two fences. V1 then traversed a wash (dropping approximately 20 feet) and its front end contacted the southern wall. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction in the wash.

V1 was traveling from west to south (making a left turn) through an intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway in lane 3 (of five lanes). V2 was traveling east through the same intersection from a two-way, not physically divided trafficway in lane 1 (of five lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a southwesterly direction in the intersection. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing a southeasterly direction in the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling westward but in different lanes of a six lane highway (three up and three down). The PAR stated that the operator of V2 (according to witnesses) was traveling at a high rate of speed and weaving in and out of traffic. V2 departed their travel lane to the left and continued to cross the middle lane.  The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1.  V2 continued forward and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  V1 was then displaced left and the left side of V1 impacted a concrete traffic barrier.  Both vehicles came to rest facing northwest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a non-physically divided one way roadway exiting an off ramp, negotiating a left curve. V1 drifted off the right road edge then back towards the roadway. V1 traveled across the southbound on road, and off the west road edge and the front of V1 impacted an embankment. V1 continued to travel off road and the front of V1 contacted a concrete bridge support wing. V1 then rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the same concrete bridge wing. V1 then traveled back down the embankment towards the roadway and the front of V1 contacted the asphalt roadway. V1 then came to rest in the southbound lane, facing in a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. For unknown reasons, V1 traveled off the west road edge and impacted a fence. V1 continued through the fence and across a large field until the front of V1 impacted another fence. V1 continued through that fence and then airborne over and across a large ravine where the front of V1 impacted the other side of the ravine. V1 came to rest in a field just past the ravine facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling west on a 2 lane, 2 way undivided roadway.  V2 was stopped facing west on the same 2 lane 2 way undivided roadway ahead of V1 waiting to turn left.  The front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in the third lane on a six lane, two-way undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was facing north on the same roadway, stopped ahead of vehicle 1. V2 entered the intersection when the front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection facing north.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one, stopped at a stop sign waiting to make a right turn. V2 was traveling north on a four lane non-physically divided roadway in lane two approaching an intersection. As V1 entered the roadway and began to merge from lane one into lane two, the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest in lane two of the southbound lanes facing south. V2 came to rest in lane two of the southbound lanes just north of V1 facing north.

V1 was traveling north on an undivided two-way road in lane one, behind V2 and a Non Contact Vehicle. V2 was traveling north on the same undivided two-lane road in lane one, in front of a Non Contact Vehicle and V1. V2 began to slow down to turn left towards the west shoulder; V1 began to overtake the Non Contact Vehicle in the southbound lane. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 as V2 attempted a left turn. Both vehicles came to rest on the west shoulder facing a northwest direction.

V1 was traveling south on a six lane non-physically divided roadway in lane two, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a non-physically divided five lane road in lane three, approaching an intersection to turn left. As V2 was making a left turn, the front of left front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 came to rest south off the intersection facing a southwest direction. V2 spun counter-clockwise and came to rest within the intersection facing a westerly direction.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane of a 3 lane one way road. V2 was parked on the east shoulder facing north. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to rest partially in the #1 lane facing north. V2 came to rest on the east shoulder facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling east in lane 1 on a 2 lane undivided roadway. V3 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 began to slow down due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and entered the westbound lane where the right side of V2 was impacted by the front of V3. V2 continued to rotate counter-clockwise where the right side of V2 impacted the left side of V3. After the impact with V2, V1 traveled to the left and came to rest on the north shoulder facing east. After the impact with V3, V2 came to rest facing south blocking the westbound lane. After the impact with V2, V3 departed the road to the right and came to rest off the road facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane two-way roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front plane contacted a utility pole. Vehicle 1 continued forward and the front plane contacted a tree before coming to final rest off the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway approaching the peak of a hill crest. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway as V1 negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway exiting the peak of a hill crest. V1 began to depart the left hand lane line and in an attempt to avoid colliding with V2, V1 began to re-enter its initial lane of travel. V2 recognizing oncoming V1 attempted to turn left into the northbound lane. The frontal plane of V1 then contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 proceeded to push V2 slightly off of the eastern shoulder where V2 then contacted a guardrail face with its left side plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway while V2 came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 began to lose control due to the road conditions and departed the left hand lane line and then departed the left side (east) of the roadway. V1 contacted a tree with its frontal plane where it came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the eastern road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to rest off the roadway.

Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle #1 was  traveling west in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the roadway facing west. V2 came to rest in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling east on a unmarked two lane roadway attempting to turn left approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a four lane with a two-way left turn lane approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling east in lane three or a four lane, one way roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one of a four lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in the northbound lanes of a two lane divided highway in lane two. V2 was traveling north on a two lane divided highway in lane two. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 and both vehicles spun counter clockwise where the right of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to rest on the west shoulder facing south. V2 came to rest on the west shoulder facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a six lane, two-way physically divided roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 1 blew a tire and loss control of the vehicle. Vehicle 1's front made contact with a impact attenuator, and rotated counterclockwise and came to final rest facing east and caught on fire.

Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling west in lane 1, on a 5 lane divided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing west. V2 rotated  clockwise, departed the right road edge and the left side contacted a light pole. V2 came to rest off the roadway facing north.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast in lane one of a two-lane divided roadway with a positive barrier.  V1 began to yaw clockwise.  V1 departed its lane and then the roadway to the left.  The leftt of V1 contacted a cable barrier guardrail.  V1 came to rest facing northeast in the median.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was parked on the opposite side of the same roadway, facing north. V1 departed it's lane on the left side and it's front plane struck V2's front plane. V1 continued traveling forward and pushed V2 rearward over a sidewalk and into a brick wall. V1 then began to rotate in a counter clockwise direction and began a right side leading rollover. V1 then rolled 2 quarter turns, partially departed the roadway, and contacted a fence with it's left side plane. The vehicle rolled 2 more quarter turns, returned to the roadway, and came to final rest on it's wheels in lane one, facing north. V2 came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the west and the front plane contacted a utility pole.  The final rest was against the pole.

V1 was traveling north on a one lane exit ramp approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to cross over the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 came to rest west of the intersection in lane one facing west. V1 came to rest facing north.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane, undivided, roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on three lane, undivided, roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway, stopped at a stop sign. V2 was traveling behind V1. V1's back plane was struck by V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest at near impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, negotiating a slight left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and its front plane contacted a fire hydrant, which broke off from the base. V1 continued off the roadway and its front plane contacted a culvert drain. V1 continued across a driveway and came to final rest off the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling north on a private drive and made a right turn onto a two lane roadway. V1 traveling a short distance and attempted a left turn onto an other private drive. V2 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the private drive. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. Both vehicles came to rest at impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a four lane divided trafficway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left then the left road edge and it front plane contacted a guardrail. V1 reentered the roadway and crossed both lanes and the front plane contacted a bridge. V1 came to rest in the roadway near impact two.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-way lane, in lane number 1 intending to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 6 lane, two-way not physically divided roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 3 was traveling west on the same roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 4 was traveling west on the same roadway in lane number 1. Vehicle 1's front and vehicle 2's rear end made contact with each other in lane number 4. After initial impact, vehicle 1 switched lanes and vehicle 1's right side made contact with vehicle 3's front, vehicle 1 continued forward and made contact with vehicle 4's front. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing east in lane number 1. Vehicle 2 came to final rest in their original lane. Vehicle 3 came to final rest facing west in lane number 2. Vehicle 4 came to rest in their original lane facing west.

V1 was traveling east in lane three on a three lane, non-positively divided roadway, and was negotiating a right curve in the roadway. A deer  entered the road from the median side of the roadway, and V1 contacted the deer with its front plane. After the initial impact, the deer was launched into the air and the vehicle contacted the deer a second time with its top plane. V1 came to final rest in its original travel lane east of the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a physically divided two lane highway in lane one in the area of an on ramp. For an unknown reason V1 lost control and traveled across and into the exit lane channel area. V1 then traveled southeast and departed the east road edge, where the front of V1 impacted a concrete median. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the right side impacted the same concrete median. After the second impact V1 rotated counterclockwise and began to roll left four quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels, facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling eastbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 departed lane of travel to the right for an unknown reason. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane while V2 was legally parked along the edge of roadway. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, divided roadway, approaching a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two lane, one way roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and rolled over two quarter turns to the right. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound, in lane two, of a four lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound, in lane two, of a four lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound, on a two lane roadway, while negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 then contacted a fence with an unknown plane. V1 came to rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way median divided interchange negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right hand (west) side of the roadway, and V1 contacted the deer in the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching a sign controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection as V1. V2 entered the intersection and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the frontal plane of V1. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 slowed for a vehicle in front that was turning left.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the rear plane of Vehicle 2.  Both vehicles came to final rest facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane undivided roadway crossing thru the intersection with a four lane undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was contacted on its right side side by the frontal plane of vehicle 2 which was northbound and also entering the intersection. After initial contact vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and contacted the left side plane of vehicle 2 as it rotated clockwise. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the second of three southbound lanes of a three lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed its travel lane crossed over the third travel lane and contacted a concrete traffic divider with its frontal plane. After initial contact vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and contacted the concrete barrier with its left side plane. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the hard shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, physically divided trafficway in lane two attempting to change lanes to lane one. V2 was traveling westbound in the same roadway, in lane one. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. After the initial impact with V1, V2 spun around and rolled over right side leading 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest off roadway on its roof.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane, two-way roadway in lane one. V2 and V3 were traveling eastbound on the same roadway in lane one ahead of V1. V2 was slowing down in traffic. V3 was stopped in traffic. V1 front plane contacted V2's back plane, after initial impact V2 was pushed into V3, V2's front plane contacted V3's back plane. V1, V2 and V3 came to final rest in roadway at point of impact facing eastbound.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling northwest on the same roadway. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 then rotated counter clockwise and came to rest off the roadway. V2 was pushed back and rolled to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, with  a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, then returned to the roadway crossing over it and departing the left side of the roadway, in a counterclockwise yaw. V1 then over corrected and entered a clockwise yaw. V1 rolled, left side leading, five quarter turns. During the roll sequence V1 struck the top portion of a fence that does not appear to have impacted the roll sequence. V1 came to rest on its left side heading east.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1, of a 3 lane roadway with a two-way turn lane. V1 was approaching an intersecting roadway. V1 continued straight through and left the roadway to the left. V1 turned over onto its left side and slid down an embankment. V1 then entered another roadway, still on its left side. V1's back plane then contacted a concrete barrier before coming to final rest, partially on the roadway.

V1 was travelling north and V2 was stopped facing north in the third of three lanes on a positively divided, two-way road. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. After impact V1 departed the roadway to the left and came to rest off the roadway and V2 departed the roadway to the right and came to rest off the roadway.

Vehicles 1, 2, and 3 were traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 and 3 were in lane 2 and Vehicle 2 was in lane 1. Vehicle 1 was behind Vehicle 3.  Vehicle 3 stopped due to traffic. V2 merged into lane 2  behind V3 then slowed. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Then the front of V2 contacted the back of V3. V1 departed the right road edge and came to rest facing east. V2 and V3 came to rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left. A bicyclist was also traveling west on the right shoulder. V1 departed the right side of the road and its front plane impacted the bicyclist. V1 came to rest on the right side of the road heading west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling in the same direction behind V1 on the same two lane, two way roadway. V2 had come to a stop in the roadway and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest shortly after impact in the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane roadway in the westbound lane approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a two way, two lane intersecting roadway in the southbound lane.  V3 was stopped at the intersection in the eastbound lane of the same roadway V1 was traveling.  V2 struck V1 on the right side with the front plane at the intersection.  V1 rotated clockwise and struck V3 with the left side plane.  V3 sustained damage to the front plane.  V1 continued in a southwest direction partially off the roadway and struck a stop sign post anchored by a cement block, with it's back plane, on the southwest corner.  V1 came to final rest partially off the roadway facing north.  V2 and V3 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling in a north western direction on a two lane, non-divided roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left, where its frontal plane impacted a guardrail twice, before coming to final rest on the left side of the roadway.
