V1 was traveling on a two lane, non-divided roadway. A non-contact vehicle was traveling on the same roadway in front of V1. The non-contact vehicle braked, causing V1 to brake, and veer right to avoid impact. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it's frontal plane impacted a culvert. V1 came to final rest in the culvert on the right side of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle 2 was legally parked on the south side of lane one facing east. V1 departed the roadway on the right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 departed the roadway on the right. The front of V2 contacted a pole. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing southeast. V2 came to rest partially off the roadway facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in the first of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the the front of V1 contacted a concrete bridge. The impact caused V1 to rotate vertically and the top of V1 then struck the underside of the bridge in two locations. V1 rolled backward down the embankment to final rest off the road.

V1 was northbound on a 2 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was westbound on a 2 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the first of four lanes on a positively divided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was redirected off the right side of the road. The right side of V2 contacted the concrete traffic barrier. Both vehicles then came to rest in the road. V2 at final rest had a major fire.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a 2 lane physically median divided roadway in the lane one position. Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on 3 lane physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position. Both vehicles entered into the intersection at the same time. The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west at the northern center section of the intersection. Vehicle 2 began to rotate clockwise after contact and came to final rest facing south/east at the north eastern section of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching a 4 way intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching the same 4 way intersection.  Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time.  The front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and Vehicle 2 rotated counter clockwise.  At this point the left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the right plane of Vehicle 2.   Both vehicles came to final rest facing southeast at the southeast corner of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching an intersection with the intention to pass through. V2 was traveling on a 5 lane, two-way, median divided roadway in lane 1 position approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 continued through the intersection and departed roadway left side coming to rest on a landscaped mound facing northeast. V2 came to rest at the north east corner of the intersection facing north west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. V1 returned to the roadway on the right side. V1 departed the lane on the left side and the roadway on the left side. The left side of V1 contacted a pole. V1 rolled right side leading ten quarter turns and came to rest on it's roof, off the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a five lane, two-way physically undivided roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right and the front of Vehicle 1 contacted a pole. Vehicle 1 came to final rest against the pole facing southwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west and turning left at a five lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane two of a five lane roadway, not divided by a positive barrier. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and impacted the left rear wheel on a curb. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing north. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane three on a four lane roadway, physically divided by a concrete barrier. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane four. Vehicle 1 departed the original lane of travel to the left. The left plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the right of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 then departed the roadway contacting a Jersey barrier with its front left rim, followed by its left rear rim before coming to rest facing north. Vehicle 2 also came to final rest facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling south bound on a four lane, physically divided roadway, with two lanes south bound and two lanes north bound divided by a cable barrier guard rail. V2 was in the lead traveling in the number two lane, when the vehicles entered a snow squall. V2 slowed down for the change in road conditions. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane. V2 rotated counter clockwise, where it impacted V1's left plane. V2 departed the roadway to the left, where it impacted a cable barrier guard rail. V1 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway facing south. V2 came to final rest on the left side of the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling in a northeastern direction, on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway, with a slight curve to the left. The roadway was bordered on both side by high rock cut walls. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted the rock cut wall. V1 rotated clockwise, coming to final rest on the right side of the road facing south.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, three lane road in the second lane of travel, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling southwest following a two way, two lane road, approaching the same four way intersection. In the middle of the mentioned intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 and V2 rotated counter clockwise and the left side of V1 impacted the left side of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south following a two way, two-lane road. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. V1 then departed the roadway on the left. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole. The impact caused the pole to snap in half. V1 continued forward, skidding longitudinally before impacting another utility pole with its frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise, impacting a guy wire, a fence and then another guy wire before coming to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 entered onto the roadway from a private drive to make a right turn. V2 was heading east on a two lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west, in lane 2, of a divided roadway with a non-protected median. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The right side of V1 contacted a bridge wall. V1 the re-entered that roadway. V1 continued and departed the roadway to the left again. V1 then tripped over to the right and came to final rest on its wheels within the median.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane two of a six lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in the same lane approaching the same intersection. After the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest north of the intersection facing north.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a three lane divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was parked on the right shoulder of the same roadway. Vehicle 3 was traveling in lane three on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right, steered left and its right side contacted the back of V2. Debris from this event landed in lane 3 and the left tires of V3 contacted the debris. V1 came to rest on the right shoulder facing southwest. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the roadway facing southwest. V3 came to rest on the left shoulder facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right.  The right side mirror of V1 contacted a mailbox.  V1 continued forward and the front of V1 contacted a fence.  V1 continued forward and the right plane of V1 contacted a tree.  The front of V1 then contacted another tree.  V1 came to rest near this impact, off road to the west, facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west, on a median divided roadway, with three lanes in the same direction. V1 began to slide on the roadway due to the road conditions and began rotating in a counter clockwise direction. V1 departed the right hand (north) side of the roadway striking an embankment with its back plane and striking an unknown object with its left side plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane undivided roadway, approaching a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling east, on a median divided roadway, with four lanes in the same direction, approaching the same intersection as V1. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1. Both V1 and V2 continued forward departing the right hand (southeast) side of the roadway and came to a final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane two on a three lane, two-way roadway and was turning left to go west on a five lane, non-divided, roadway with a two way left turn lane. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 on the five lane roadway. As V1 was turning left, its front plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane undivided (two-way traffic) left curve roadway. V2 was ahead of V1 and legally parked at the west curb of the street. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to rest at impact, facing south.
V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the east side of the road facing north.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was northbound followed by V3 on a the same roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left impacting the frontal plane of V2 with its frontal plane causing damage. Upon impact debris flew back impacting the frontal plane of V3 causing damage. V1 continued southward coming to final rest on the east side of the road facing south. V2 and V3 continued northward coming to final rest on the east side of the road facing north.

V1 was traveling up a slight incline that curved right while traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road where it impacted a mailbox post and rock with its front plane. V1 continued over a driveway then into a grass yard where its right front end plane impacted a tree and its top contacted tree branches. V1 then impacted another with its front plane. Finally, the front of V1 impacted a large tree where it came to rest facing southeast against the tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway.  Vehicles #2 was parked facing south on the west side of the same roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  The impact pushed V2 forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of another parked vehicle.  V1 and V2 came to rest near impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of a two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and departed the road to the left. The back of V1 contacted a rock embedded in the ditch (event 1). V1 continued to rotate counterclockwise and the front contacted a bush (event 2) and the back contacted a barbed wire fence (event 3) passing through it. V1 came to rest off road to the east.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 struck a cow that was in the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest in its original travel lane, heading south, near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling in a southwesterly direction on a north/south designated, physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier), in lane 3 (of three lanes) and was approaching V2, which was disabled partially in lane 3 facing a northeasterly direction. In lane 3, the front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2. After impact V2 moved rearward and rotated counterclockwise and the rear of V2 contacted a pedestrian that was standing behind the vehicle. V2 came to rest facing west straddling the road edge and lane three. V1 rotated counterclockwise and traveled south and came to rest on its wheels facing east straddling lane two and lane three of southbound travel.

V1 was traveling south on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane one (of two lanes) and was approaching a tractor trailer in the same lane. V2 was traveling in the same direction, on the same trafficway, in lane two ahead of the tractor trailer. V1 changed into lane two to pass the tractor trailer, and began to return to lane one when the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest on their wheels facing a southerly direction on the right shoulder.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four-lane, two-way roadway attempting left turn at an intersection to head southbound. V2 was traveling eastbound on the mentioned roadway approaching the intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing west, V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane 1 on a 2 lane undivided roadway with parking lanes on both sides. V3 was legally parked on the north shoulder facing east. V2 began to slow down to eventually make a u-turn and park. V1 attempted to pass V2 on the left. The right side mirror of V1 impacted the left side mirror of V2. V1 continued forward and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 departed the roadway to the left where the front of V1 impacted the front of V3. Then the back of V3 was pushed into the front of a legally parked vehicle. V1 came to rest on the south shoulder facing south west. V2 came to rest in lane 1 facing west. V3 came to rest on the south shoulder facing east.

V1 was traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left. V1 steered back and entered back into its lane before departing the road to the right. V1 steered left going down into a ditch where V1 rolled over leading right. V1 rolled over through a barbed wire fence. V1 came to rest of the road on its wheels facing south west.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing southerly in the intersection. V2 then rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the south where the left side of V2 impacted a pole. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing easterly on the southwest corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 came to rest facing northwest against the fence.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 1 lane  divided roadway  in lane number 1 intending to turn left at a intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on a 4 lane median divided roadway approaching the same intersection in lane 4. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing east.  V2 rotated clockwise  and came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 5  on a 8 lane roadway  approaching an intersection intending to turn left. . V2 was traveling south in lane number 1,on a 7 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 front made contact with V2 front in the intersection. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest facing southwest in the intersection.  V2 departed the southwest corner of the intersection and made contact with a fiber optic junction box  and came to final rest after impact facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided road in lane one, negotiating a right curve. V1 was unable to negotiate the curve and crossed over the east bound lane and departed the south road edge. After departing the road, the front of V1 impacted a mail box. V1 continued and the front of V1 impacted a pole, then a utility box, then another pole. V1 began to spin counter-clockwise and the first pole that V1 impacted, landed on the top of V1. V1 came to rest off of the roadway facing a southeasterly direction.

V1 was traveling northwest on a undivided three lane road in lane two approaching an intersection, preparing to turn left. V2 was traveling southeast on a undivided two way road in lane one approaching the intersection. As V1 entered the intersection to make a left turn, V2 passed through the intersection where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 spun counter-clockwise and came to rest within the intersection facing a westerly direction. V2 came to rest within the intersection facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 noticed an animal on the western roadside causing V1 to turn the wheel. V1 departed the left hand lane line and then the left side of the roadway. V1 then contacted a tree with its frontal plane. V1 proceeded forward contacting an embankment with its left side followed by an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then contacted a snowbank with its right plane before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching a four way intersection.  V2 was traveling south on the intersecting five lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching the same intersection. V2 moved to lane two to pass a non contact vehicle. As both vehicles passed through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right plane of V1.  V1 then overturned to the left and rolled three quarter turns coming to final rest on the right plane in the intersection facing northwest. V2 came to final rest in the intersection near the point of impact facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west in a channelized right turn lane approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest on a four lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection and began to turn left. V2 entered the same intersection to continue straight. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, divided, roadway. V1 departed their initial lane of travel to the left, and then departed the roadway to the left. Off the roadway, the front of V1 contacted a concrete barrier. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a lane 1, one-way, on-ramp. The front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway near point of impact.

V1 was traveling east on a undivided two lane road in lane one, negotiating a curve. For and unknown reason V1 drove off the right road edge, where the right side of V1 impacted a pole. V1 spun in an clockwise manner towards an embankment, and rolled left six quarter impacting bushes and the ground, before coming to rest on its roof, facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A non-contact vehicle was traveling northwest on the same roadway as V1. In an attempt to avoid a collision with the non-contact vehicle V1 moved towards the right edge of the roadway. V1 lost control and contacted two trees with its right side plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A dog was standing in the roadway and in an attempt to avoid hitting the dog, V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway. V1 continued forward off of the roadway and down an embankment before contacting a tree with the right side plane of the vehicle. V1 continued forward striking two additional trees with its left side plane and came to a final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was leaving his driveway, backing on to a two lane, two way undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling northbound on the two lane, two way undivided roadway.  The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two lane, divided roadway in lane one. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the shoulder to the right of lane one.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a three lane, non divided, two way roadway. As V1 approached the back of another vehicle traveling in the same direction, V1 departed its lane on the left side to go around the other vehicle. When V1 returned back into lane one, V1 lost control and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 then traveled up an embankment, rotated, and contacted several trees. V1 then rolled over and ejected the driver into the southbound ditch. V1 came to final rest in the roadway, on its wheels, facing east.

V1 was traveling south on a four lane, divided, roadway, in lane 1. V2 was traveling south on a four lane, divided, roadway approaching an intersection in lane 2. V1 made a lane change to the left, and at the intersection the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway. V2 proceeded across the intersection to the south east corner, and the right of V2 contacted a curb. V2 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 4-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 3 on the same roadway. As V1 changed lanes to the left, the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the left shoulder and contacted a concrete barrier with its right side. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and contacted the concrete barrier again with its right side. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing south. V2 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the left shoulder and contacted the concrete barrier with its front plane. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise then tripped and rolled right 6-quarter turns and came to rest on the roadway on its top facing southeast.

V1 and V2 were both traveling on the same one lane highway ramp. V2 was ahead of V1 when it slowed for traffic on the freeway and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicle came to rest in the lane.

V1 was backing up facing north. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The left of V1 contacted a fire hydrant (event 1). The right of V1 contacted the building steps (event 2) and the corner (event 3). V1 came to final rest near the last point of impact.

V1 was traveling east in lane two,on a two way, four lane, trafficway divided by a cable barrier. V1 departed the left travel lane to keep from striking an animal in the roadway. As V1 swerved left the left front tire blew out. V1 departed the left side of the road, crossing over an Authorized Vehicle Only gravel crossover lane, and struck a sign post with its frontal plane. The sign post broke off and the sign struck the top plane of V1. V1 came to rest east of the sign, heading northeast, on the north (left) side of the cable barrier.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left then traveled off the left side of the road impacting a ditch with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 continued over a culvert traveling into another ditch impacting it with the undercarriage causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the second point of impact facing north.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway following V2. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear of the farm implement being pulled by V2. Upon impact V1 rotated clockwise and overturned left side leading two quarter turns coming to final rest on its roof in the southbound lane facing east. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane No.2 of an undivided five lane roadway. Vehicle 1 moved to the left into lane No. 3 (designated left turn lane and initiated a left turn at a three-leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane No. 1 approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 initiated a left turn sequence as the front of Vehicle 2 (motorcycle) impacted the front corner region of Vehicle 1 (Event 1). The motorcyclist was ejected over the hood region and impacted the front windshield glazing of V1 (Event 2) before falling to the ground. V1 came to final rest facing south in the eastbound, lane No. 1. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on its side facing south in eastbound lane No. 1.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway. V1 departed the curb edge to the right and its left front tire contacted the curb. V1 entered a grass yard and its left side contacted a fire hydrant. V1 continued forward and its front contacted a wood utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise where the left contacted a non-fixed metal sign. V1 continued to rotate clockwise across two driveways. The back of V1 contacted a shrubbery and another wood pole. V1 continued to rotate clockwise as it entered the road where its right rear wheel contacted the ground and came to rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling in a north eastern direction on a two lane roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 left the road to the left, where it entered a ditch, and rolled driver side leading. V1 completed two quarter turns coming to final rest on its roof partially on the south west side lane.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway, when a deer entered its path of travel. V1's frontal plane impacted the animal. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in an unknown lane of a five-lane, divided roadway. V2 was also traveling northwest in lane 5 of the same roadway when the front plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2 (Event 1). V1 departed the left side of the roadway and its left quarter panel contacted the concrete barrier (Event 2) before coming to rest in between lanes 2 and 3 and facing east. V2 rotated counter-clockwise as its frontal plane also impacted the jersey barrier (Event 3) on the left side of the roadway. V2 traversed all five lanes as its back plane impacted the concrete barrier (Event 4) before coming to rest in lane 1 and facing west.

V1 was traveling north in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V1 departed the lane on the left side then departed the road on the left side. The front of V1 contacted the ground and rotated counterclockwise. The right side of V1 contacted the ground and V1 came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling west in the same lane ahead of V1. Traffic in the roadway slowed and V2 braked and departed the right side of the roadway. V1 also departed the right side of the roadway. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a six lane, two-way road approaching the same intersection. V1 took a right turn at the intersection and merged to lane two. V2 traveled straight through the intersection where it's front plane impacted the left side of V1. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway heading east.

V1 was traveling south on an unmarked, two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road where its front plane impacted a small tree and a large tree. V1 came to rest against the second tree off of the right side of the road heading south.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southwest in lane two of a lane five-lane roadway. V2 was stopped ahead of V1. V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest near the impact.

V1 was northbound in lane 2 of a 3 lane not physically divided roadway, stopped in traffic for a traffic controlled intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound in the same lane on the same roadway.  The front of V2 contacted the back of V1.  V1 then experienced an unknown event to the frontal plane.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a one way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided curved left roadway.  V1 departed the right road edge, then started a counterclockwise yaw. The front contacted the guardrail end.  V1 continued sliding with the right side leading and the right plane contacted a wire fence. V1 rolled over with the right side leading 4 quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels facing southwest off the road.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane three of a five-lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one of a four-lane roadway, approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted a left turn and the right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 departed the roadway and came to final rest off the roadway, facing east. V2 departed the roadway and came to final rest off the roadway, facing east.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane one of the same roadway, attempting a left turn. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and began to overtake V2. V2 attempted to turn left and the right plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest at impact.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane four of a seven lane divided trafficway attempting to make a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane two attempting to pass through the same intersection. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. V2 came to rest near impact in the intersection. V1 departed its right road edge and the front plane contacted a sign.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve approaching an intersection. Just as V1 passed over the intersection it departed the right road edge. V1's front plane contacted a railroad track. As V1 moved forward to final rest the RF wheel contacted the the railroad track.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound approaching a round about on a two lane divided roadway. Vehicle 1 entered into the round about and contacted its frontal plane with the right side plane of vehicle 2, which was traveling through the round about. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 8 lane divided highway, in the fourth travel lane. Vehicle 2 was stopped in that same lane and was contacted on the back plane by the right plane of vehicle 1, which was changing lanes into the fifth eastbound travel lane. Both vehicle came to rest on the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane three of a four lane roadway with V2 behind V3. V3 was traveling south in the same lane behind V2.. V2 slowed and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 moved forward and to its left and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3 in lane four of southbound travel. V1, V2, and V3 came to rest on the roadway facing south.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest in lane one on a two lane roadway physically divided by a concrete barrier. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side. The front of Vehicle 1 contacted a guardrail face and came to final rest on the right shoulder facing northwest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane one of an undivided, five lane roadway with a two-way turning lane. V1 departed the roadway on the right.  The right front wheel, lower front plane, and left front wheel of V1 impacted a curb.   The left plane of V1 contacted a mailbox. V1 continued forward and contacted the undercarriage on the ground twice. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a four lane roadway. V2 was parked in a parking lot on the southbound side of the road facing east. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The left side of V1 contacted a pole. The back portion of V1 separated and continued across a parking lot, coming to final rest independently of the front portion. After contacting the pole, V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The front portion of V1 came to final rest facing south. V2 came to final rest facing east.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, two-way roadway passing through a T-shaped intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, unmarked roadway. V2 was entering the intersection, attempting a left turn to head southbound. V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. After the initial impact V1 continued northbound and the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2. V1 came to final rest further north in the westbound lane, V2 came to final rest facing northbound.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a four-way intersection with north and south lanes controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling northbound approaching the mentioned intersection. In the middle of the intersection the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V2 came to final rest in the roadway facing south. V1 came to final rest in the roadway facing northwest.

V1 was traveling east on a divided roadway with five lanes traveling in the east direction. V1 was traveling in lane four approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling west on a divided roadway with four lanes traveling in the west direction. V1 made a left turn to head north where the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1 in the middle of the intersection. V1 came to final rest near the northwest quadrant facing east. V2 came to final rest towards the southwest quadrant facing west.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, unmarked roadway entering a four four-way intersection, controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two-way roadway approaching the mentioned intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 and V2 came to final rest facing northeast in roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left at the intersection as V2 traveled straight and the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing south. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing southwest.
V1 was traveling Northbound on a 1 lane access road, that was under construction. V1's front plane contacted a beam that was suspended over the roadway. V1 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided dirt road. A deer entered the road and V1 swerved to the right to avoid the deer. V1 departed the northern roads edge and contacted a snow bank with its right plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way. undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 lost control and crossed the left lane line and departed the left road edge. V1 re-entered the road, crossed over the road and departed the right road edge into a ditch. V1 rolled two quarter turns and came to final rest off the roadway on its roof.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a four lane median divided roadway in an unknown lane position traveling through an intersection. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway right side and the north west corner of the intersection. Vehicle 1 made contact with a curb with all four of its wheels and tires. V1 then traveled into a landscaped rock bed area making contact with the front, V1 then contacted with its left side a large rock and then a bush with its front and became airborne. The right plane, top plane and front plane made contact simultaneously with a branch system of a tree. Vehicle 1 then came back to ground making contact with the undercarriage. Vehicle 1 then traveled across a private parking lot. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 which was unoccupied and legally parked finally coming to rest facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching an intersection.  Vehicle two was traveling westbound on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position approaching the same intersection.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time.  The right front plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise.  The right rear plane of V1 made contact with the left rear plane of V2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west at the western side of the intersection.  V2 came to final rest facing west on the shoulder of the road just west of the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1 position. V1 then departed roadway left side in to a private drive. The front right of V1 contacted a large empty dumpster causing the dumpster to roll. V1 then continued north west into a neighboring private drive making contact with a pole and then a wall simultaneously, coming to final rest after impact #2 facing north west.

V1 was traveling east on a 7 lane, two- way, median divided roadway in lane 2 position approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling in front of V1 in the same lane of travel also going east stopped at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. Final rests for both V1 and V2 was at impact facing east.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 was passing through a T intersection, attempting to make a left hand turn. V2 was east bound on the same roadway, passing through the same intersection. V1's right plane impacted V2's frontal plane. This caused V1 to rotate clockwise, where V1 impacted V2's left plane twice. V1 came to final rest in the east bound lane, facing west. V2 traveled off the right side of the roadway, entered a parking lot, where it struck V3 with its right plane. V2 then impacted a soda machine, before coming to final rest in the parking lot. V3 was parked and unoccupied at the time of crash. It came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 was east bound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. The roadway had a slight curve to the left, and a positive grade. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted a large tree. V1 came to final rest in the east bound lane of travel, facing south.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a curb with its right front wheel, then striking a pole with its front plane. V1 came to rest near the point of impact heading north.

V1 was heading west in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a concrete retaining wall. V1 came to final rest facing west near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway when it departed the right side of the roadway. The front of V1 made contact with a fence (event 1) and a concrete parking block (event 2) before crashing into a building with the front end (event 3). V1 came to final rest against the building.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a non-physically divided two lane roadway. Both vehicles were traveling in lane one. A pedestrian entered the roadway, causing V2 to abruptly stop in the road. V1 did not have enough time to break and V1's front plane contacted V2's rear plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound negotiating a curve right on 4 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound negotiating a curve left on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position.  As the two vehicles approached each other from opposite direction the left plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2.  Each vehicle came to final rest shortly after impact in their initial direction of travel.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west and Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing east.

V1 was stopped on a 2 way undivided roadway waiting to turn left (south) at an intersection.  V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 2 way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection, the front plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2.  V1 rotated counterclockwise as V2 rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west in lane three of a three-lane divided roadway, behind V2 and V3.  V2 encountered traffic and slowed down. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  V2 was displaced forward and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non-physically divided roadway in lane one, negotiating a left curve. V1 was unable to navigate the curve and departed the east road edge and continued along the road edge before re-entering the roadway. V1 traveled across both lanes while rotating in a counterclockwise rotation and departed the west road edge where V1 began to rollover right side leading. During its roll, the right side of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence and the undercarriage impacted a tree. V1 completed six quarter turns before coming to rest on its roof facing a southerly direction up an embankment.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was legally parked on the west curb line. The front of V1 impacted the rear V2. V1 came to rest in lane one facing south. V2 came to rest along the west curb line facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway in lane one. A vehicle towing a trailer was traveling in the opposite direction. The trailer disconnected from the vehicle and continued into V1's lane of travel where the front of V1 impacted the trailer. V1 came to rest on the north shoulder facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a undivided two lane two way roadway negotiating a curve to its right. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 traveled to its left and into the southbound travel lane. After the impact V2 came to rest on the right shoulder facing a southerly direction. After the impact V1 fled the scene and the final rest is unknown.

V1 was traveling southwest on a median divided trafficway approaching an intersection controlled by traffic signals. V2 was traveling northeast, on the same trafficway as V1 and was attempting a left hand turn. At the intersection, the left side plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of V2. Both vehicles came to a final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 3 on a 3-lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane 1 on a 2-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and as V1 turned left, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southwest. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was southbound on a 5 lane roadway, in lane 2, approaching a 4 legged intersection. V2 was stopped on the same roadway at the same intersection. V3 was westbound on a 4 lane divided roadway in the #2 lane, approaching the same intersection. As V1 approached the intersection V1 departed its lane to the left and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After impact, V1 continued to travel and within the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V3. All vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was east bound on a 6 lane divided roadway in lane 4 approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was south bound on a 5 lane divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After initial impact the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in a side-slap motion, both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in lane 5 on a 8 lane roadway approaching an intersection intending to turn left. V2 was traveling south in lane number 3, on a 7 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to turn to its left and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest facing north in the intersection. V2 came to final rest facing southwest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 on a three lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail end. The damaged guardrail then contacted the left side of V1. The right of V1 contacted a line of shrubberies then the front contacted a signpost. The undercarriage of V1 contacted a shrub. V1 continued forward where its front contacted a tree. V1 came to rest near the tree facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 5-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 5-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 began to turn left at the intersection as V2 was passing through and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the intersection facing west. V2 rotated clockwise as it continued forward and its front plane contacted the left side of V3. V2 came to rest near V3 facing northwest. V3 came to rest in its lane facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane 3 on a seven-lane road with a two-way left turn lane. Vehicle #2 was traveling east, leaving a parking lot, approaching the same road. V2 entered the road, turning left. The front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. Both vehicles came to rest on the road.

V1 was traveling east pulling out of a private driveway in an attempt to make a left hand turn to head northbound. V2 was traveling south on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway approaching the same private driveway that V1 was exiting. The left side plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left (east) and in an attempt to avoid the animal in the roadway, V1 departed the right side of the roadway. V1 contacted a utility pole with its frontal plane, and then began to rotate in a clockwise direction. V1 rolled one quarter turn with its left side leading before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1, Vehicle #2, Vehicle #3, and Vehicle #4 were traveling north in lane six of a six lane roadway, divided by a positive barrier. The front of V1 contacted the Back of V2. The front of V2 contacted the back of V3. The front of V3 contacted the back of V4. V1, V2, V3, and V4 came to rest on the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane one on a three lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane one on a three lane, two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection facing southwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane, divided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane, undivided two way traffic frontage road in lane one. V1 attempted to merge onto the frontage road and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest partially in lane two of the frontage road facing west. V2 came to rest in lane two facing northwest.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right hand side (west) of the roadway, and V1 contacted the animal in the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 began to lose control and slide on the snow covered roadway. V1 departed the left side of its travel lane and then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 then contacted an embankment with an unknown plane and rolled one quarter turn with its left side leading. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane divided roadway approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The right of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a left-turn only lane approaching a four-way intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in lane three of a three lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. Vehicle 1's front struck vehicle 2's left side. Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest in the intersection facing west. Vehicle 2 continued forward and came to final rest in lane number 1 facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, grass median divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a five lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 proceeded off the roadway the southeast corner of the intersection in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 continued off the roadway and the front contacted a building. V1 came to final rest in the building.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position. Vehicle 2 had stopped in the left hand turn lane of the 3 lane roadway. Vehicle 2 began to back up, turning the vehicle into the private access driveway. As Vehicle 2 crossed lane 1, the front plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the left plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 was pushed westward off the north side of the road striking the curb edge. The vehicle continued westward striking a landscaping bush with its rear plane. The Vehicle 2 was facing southeast at final rest. Vehicle 1 hopped the curb with its rear wheels coming to final rest facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 3 position attempting to make a left hand turn into a business access.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on the same 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  As Vehicle 1 was turning left in front of a non-contact vehicle which had stopped in traffic, the right plane of V1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 spun counter-clockwise and came to final rest facing southeast in the business access entrance.  Vehicle 2 rotated slightly clockwise also coming to final rest facing southeast in the same business access.

V1 was traveling south in the second of four lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, intersection attempting to turn left. V1 departed the road on the southeast corner and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 rotated counterclockwise and the right side of V1 contacted a wood fence. V1 came to rest off the road.

V1 was traveling west in the first of three lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south in the second of five lanes on undivided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. After the initial impact, both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a four legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling northeast in the second of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After the initial impact, both came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane two of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) straight roadway, passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane two of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) straight roadway, approaching an intersection. V3 was traveling south in lane one of a four lane undivided (two-way traffic) straight roadway, approaching an intersection. After V1 passed through the intersection, it departed it's lane of travel to the left. V1 crossed partially into lane four before the driver steered back to the right in order to get back into the original lane of travel. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the road to its left. V1 came to rest partially off the road and partially in lane four, facing south. After the impact with V1, V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest in its lane of travel, facing south. V3 attempted to avoid being hit by V1 during its post-crash movement and steered to the right.
