V1 was traveling south in lane one of a four lane divided roadway, approaching an intersecting street. V2 was traveling east on that intersecting street. V1 turned right at the intersection and departed the roadway to the south. V1s left front wheel struck a raised curb (event 1) and partially drove off the road. V1 re-entered the roadway, driving west in the eastbound lane. The front of V1 struck the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the eastbound lane, facing west. V2 came to rest partially in both lanes, facing northeast.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane road with a curve to the right. V2 was traveling in front of V1 on the same two way, two lane road. V2 stopped in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one on a five lane, non divided, two way roadway. V2 was exiting a parking lot driveway to travel northeast on the same roadway. At the intersection of the parking lot driveway, V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. After impact, V1 departed the roadway on the right side and came to final rest partially on the driveway and partially in the parking lot. V2 came to final rest in lane three of the roadway, facing northeast.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane one of a two-lane, divided roadway without a positive barrier.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.  V1 came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road up an incline. V1 departed the road to the left side where its front plane impacted a tree. V1 rotated counterclockwise then rolled right one quarter turn. The rollover was interrupted when the top plane of V1 impacted another tree. V1 rolled back one quarter turn toward the left, landing back on its wheels. V1 came to rest facing west with its right wheels off of the road.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was legally parked off the roadway right, facing east.  V1's front contacted V2's left plane. Then V1 continued East, departing the roadway left where the front plane contacted a chain link fence. V1 continued forward where it contacted a shrub with it's front plane, and then contacted a residential home with it's front plane. V1 came to final rest facing east on the front lawn of the residential house.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane divided highway in lane three. While changing lanes, V1 lost control and traveled across the number two and number one lane and departed the east road edge where the front left of V1 impacted a post. V1 continued up an embankment where the front of V1 impact a shrub. V1 then began to roll left four quarter turns up and then down the embankment where the left side of V1 impacted a pole. V1 came to rest on its wheels up against the pole facing a northeasterly direction.

V1 was traveling west in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northeast in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 traveled northwesterly coming to rest facing west on the northwest shoulder. V2, after the impact with V1, rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing westerly in the intersection.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were all traveling south west in the #1 lane of a 5 lane one way freeway off ramp. V5 was traveling south west in the #2 lane of a 5 lane one way freeway off ramp. V6 was traveling south west in the #3 lane of a 5 lane one way freeway off ramp. V3, V4, V5, V6 were all stopped at an intersection. V2 began slowing behind V3. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 steered right and departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a bridge barrier wall. V1 steered back left and entered back into the roadway where the front of V1 impacted the back of V3. V3 was pushed forward and the front of V3 impacted the back of V4. V1 continued traveling to the left departing its lane. V3 rotated and departed its lane to the left where the front of V1 impacted the right side of V3. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V5. V5 rotated clockwise and traveled to the left where the left side of V5 impacted the right side of V6. V1, after impacting V5, continued into the intersection wh

V1 was traveling east on a two way, four lane, median divided roadway in lane two negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 traveled into lane one of eastbound traffic and then back across both lanes of eastbound traffic. V1 then departed the left (north) side of the roadway. V1 contacted a guardrail face with its left side plane. V1 continued forward and southeast and crossed both lanes of eastbound traffic, coming to rest in the right shoulder of the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling south in the first of two lanes on a divided, two-way trafficway. V2 was traveling south in the same lane ahead of V1. V3 was traveling south in the same lane behind V1. V2 stopped for road conditions and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The front of V3 then contacted the back of V1. All three vehicles came to rest in the lane near their respective points of impact.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound, in lane two, of a three lane roadway. V2 was stopped for traffic when V1's front contacted V2's back plane. Both vehicles came to rest within the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway in lane 1 approaching a three-leg intersection. V2 was traveling south on a five-lane, undivided roadway in lane 2 and approaching the same intersection. V1 had stopped at a stop sign and proceeded into the intersection, turning left when the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 (Event1). V1 rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 collided with the right side of V2 in a secondary sideslap (Event 2) . V2 traversed the northbound lanes where the front of V2 impacted the ground/embankment (Event 3) and then the front impacted a bush (Event 4). V1 came to rest facing south straddling lane 2 and the north bound designated left turn lane. V2 came to rest off the left roadside in  a group of decorative bushes and facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two lane, divided roadway, and was turning right at an intersection to travel north on a four lane, divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in lane three on a six lane, divided roadway, and had crossed into lane 2 prior to entering an intersection. At the intersection, V1's left side plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one on a two-way driveway, in a parking lot, approaching an intersection to turn left to go west onto a three lane driveway to exit the parking lot. V2 was traveling northeast in lane one on a three lane, two way driveway, to enter the parking lot. At the intersection of these driveways, V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. Both vehicles came to final rest in the drive lane of the parking lot.

V1 was traveling westbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a 4-way intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same 4-way intersection.  V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. V1's front plane contacted V2's unknown plane. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway on the side of the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a four lane, two way, median divided roadway. V1 was trailing V2 in the same lane and at a higher rate of speed. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 came to final rest in the unpaved median off the left hand (west) side of the roadway. V2 came to a final rest in a private drive off the right hand (east) side of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two of a five-lane, divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane three of an intersecting six-lane, undivided roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V2 rotated clockwise and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest facing northwest on the periphery of the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane two of a three-lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane one of an intersecting two-lane, undivided roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near the southwest corner of the intersection facing southwest.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were traveling in the fourth southbound lane of five lanes of a median divided roadway. Vehicle 2 stopped in its travel lane for a traffic signal and was contacted on the back plane by the frontal plane of vehicle 1. Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way, two lane attempting a left turn to travel eastbound from a business entrance. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the business entrance. In the westbound lane the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left (west) side of the roadway. V1 contacted the animal in the roadway with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a two-lane divided roadway without a positive barrier. Vehicle #1 was disabled in the median. V2 departed the roadway to the left and entered the median. The front of V2 contacted the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to rest near impact, facing east.

V1 was traveling south in lane No. 1 of an undivided one-way road. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the roadway and facing south. V1 veered to the right as its frontal plane impacted the rear plane of the parked vehicle. V1 rotated clockwise coming to rest on the roadway facing north-west. V2 came to final rest on the edge of the pavement facing south.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane roadway approaching a right curve. V2 was traveling northwest on the same roadway exiting the left curve. V2 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Due to impact forces, V2 was split at the B-Pillar. The front half was redirected to the left where it came to final rest in a driveway. The back half of V2 was redirected to the right. The left of V1 impacted the right of V2. V2, continuing on its path, departed the roadway to the right where it came to final rest in between two driveways. V2 also was redirected to the right where it came to final rest near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway. V2 was traveling north directly in front of V1. V2 was slowing to turn left into a business drive. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 continued forward and came to rest on the roadway facing north. V2 continued forward, departed the right road edge and came to rest in a grass area facing northeast.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its travel lane to the left and then departed the left side of the roadway. V1 went off the edge of a large concrete culvert striking the far side of the culvert with its wheels and undercarriage (event 1). V1 then struck the ground with its frontal plane (event 2). Upon striking the ground V1 rotated clockwise. V1 then struck several trees with its left side (events 3-6). V1 came to final rest off the roadway heading west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided dirt and gravel roadway. A deer entered the road from the right road edge, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the deer. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling west directly in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to rest in lane one facing west.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left hand side of the roadway (north) and in an attempt to avoid the collision with the deer V1 departed the right hand side of the roadway. V1 drove off of the roadway a short distance before contacting a bush, a tree stump, and two trees with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a 4 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2, towing a trailer, was stopped in the same lane in front of V1. V1 front made contact with the back of V2's trailer. Both vehicles came to final rest in the area of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road that curved downhill and to the left. V1 departed the right side of the road where its front plane impacted a guardrail, sign post, two small trees and one large tree with its front plane. V1 came to rest off of the right side of the road against the large tree and guardrail.

V1 was stopped in traffic heading south on a three lane, two way roadway, with a two way center turn lane. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway behind V1. The frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. V1 came to rest near the point of impact in its original travel lane heading south. V2 came to rest near the point of impact partially on the shoulder and partially in its original travel lane, heading southwest.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane divided highway in lane two. V1 lost control and moved into lane one then back into lane two and then departed the left road edge. V1 continued off of the roadway where the front of V1 impacted a jersey barrier. V1 then bounced off of the barrier and began to roll right side leading 4 quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its wheels in an embankment facing a northeasterly direction.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane one on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. V2 had come to a stop due to cargo in the roadway that had fallen off of another, non-contact, vehicle. V1's front plane then contacted V2's rear plane. V2 came to final rest with its RF tire off the roadway to the right, while the rest of the vehicle remained in lane one. V1 came to final rest in lane one, on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, two way, non divided roadway, and was negotiating a right curve . V2 was traveling west in lane one on the same roadway, and was negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 departed it's lane on the left side and it's front plane contacted V2's left side plane. After impact, V1 returned to it's lane and departed the roadway on the right side, where it came to final rest. V2 rotated in a counter-clockwise direction after impact, and departed the roadway on the right side. V2 then came to final rest with it's left front tire still on the roadway, and the rest of the vehicle off the roadway.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling southeast on a two way, two lane undivided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 came to a full stop in the roadway. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with the rear plane of V2. V2 continued forward and its frontal plane made contact with the rear plane of V3. V3 continued forward and its frontal plane made contact with the rear plane of V4. V1, V2, V3, and V4 came to a final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 began to lose control and departed the left hand lane line and then the left (southeast) side of the roadway. V1 returned to the roadway, crossed over the left lane line and departed the right side of the roadway. V1 rotated clockwise and tripped onto its left side contacting a tree with its roof before falling back onto its wheels at final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane two of a three lane, two way undivided roadway approaching a four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in lane two of a three lane, two way roadway with median approaching the same intersection turning left. Within the intersection, the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest within the intersection facing northwest.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two way, six lane divided trafficway with a positive barrier in the grass median dividing the northbound and southbound lanes.  V3 was parked on the left shoulder, of the southbound lanes.  V1 exited the roadway left and struck a cable barrier with the front plane.  V1 reentered the roadway and crossed all three southbound lanes in a southwest direction off the roadway right and struck a concrete barrier overpass support with the front plane.  V1 reentered the roadway and was struck on the back plane by V2.  V2 sustained damage to the front plane from the impact.  V2 continued off the roadway left striking V3 in the back plane with V2's front plane.  V1, V2, and V3 all came to final rest on the inner berm.  V2 engulfed in flames.

V1 and V2 were traveling east in lane one on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. V3 was traveling west in lane one, on a two lane non-positively divided roadway. V1's front plane then contacted V2's back plane. After this contact, V1 departed its lane on the left side, crossed over lane two, and departed the roadway on the left side. V1 then traveled over a grass median, lane two of the westbound lane, and entered lane 1 of the west bound lane. V1's front plane then contacted V3's front plane. V1 and V3 came to final rest in the westbound travel lanes, and V2 came to rest on the right shoulder of the eastbound lanes.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a two lane, two-way, non-divided roadway, when the vehicle departed its lane and the road on the left side. V1 contacted a culvert with its front plane, continued traveling forward, and contacted a mailbox post with its front plane. The vehicle began a left side leading roll and rolled over two quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on its roof, and was located off of the road on the left side.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in the same lane on a two lane bidirectional roadway. V2 was ahead of V1. V2 slowed to turn left into a private drive. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane. V1 came to final rest east of impact, in the middle of the roadway. V2 came to final rest on it's left side east of V1, also in the middle of the roadway.

V1 was traveling in an eastern direction on a two lane, physically divided roadway, approaching a large bridge. V1 was towing a trailer at the time. The trailer started to sway causing V1 to depart the roadway to the right, where its frontal plane impacted the side of the bridge. V1 continued to rotate clockwise, coming to final rest in the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a 2-lane roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2. Both vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane driveway. V2 was traveling east following a two way, two lane, intersecting roadway. V1 attempted to turn left at the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway, V1 facing north and V2 facing east.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane two on a 2- lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two on a 3-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and as V1 turned left, its right side contacted the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise as V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing east. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing west.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked facing west on the same roadway.  V1's frontal contacted the rear plane of V2. V2 came to final rest on the roadway. V1 crossed both travel lanes and came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane one of a two lane roadway attempting to make a left turn at an intersection. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of the same roadway attempting to pass through the same intersection. V3 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two lane roadway stopped at the same intersection waiting for the signal to change. V1's front plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise and its front plane contacted V3's front plane both vehicles came to rest at impact. V2 came to rest near impact in the intersection.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The frontal plane of V1 struck a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the north side of the road facing west.

V1 was traveling North on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw crossing over a ditch and impacting a tree with the rear plane causing damage. V1 rotated counter clockwise upon impact coming to final rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 on the same roadway behind V1. V1 began to turn right into a private driveway and the right side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the right road edge and came to rest partially in a grass yard facing northeast. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing southwest.

V1 and V2 were both traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, undivided trafficway.  V2 slowed for another vehicle.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest near impact, still facing east.

V1 was traveling in lane two of a two-lane divided roadway with a positive barrier. V1 departed the highway to the left, prior to the start of the barrier. V1 went down an embankment. The front of V1 contacted the ground. V1 rolled end over end coming to rest on its roof on a different roadway.

Vehicle 1 traveling Northbound Lane 1 on a 5-Lane roadway attempting to make a left turn. Vehicle 2 traveling southbound in Lane 1 on a 5-Lane roadway came into contact with its front plane into Vehicle 1 right plane. Both Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 impacted and came to rest in Southbound Lane #1 facing southwest.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided traffic way in lane one. For unknown reasons, V1 crossed over the southbound lane and off the west road edge where the front of V1 impacted a utility trailer. V1 continued under the utility trailer until the front of V1 impacted a metal support on the trailer. V1 came to rest under the trailer facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane divided roadway in lane three, negotiating a curve on a wet roadway in the rain. V1 lost control and departed the east road edge and the front of V1 impacted a concrete barrier. V1 bounced off the barrier and the left side of V1 impacted the concrete barrier before coming to rest in the center median facing a southerly direction.

V1 was traveling west on an undivided four lane road in lane two, waiting to turn left. V2 was traveling on a physically divided two-lane road in lane two, approaching the intersection. As V1 attempted a left turn, the left side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 spun counter-clockwise and came to rest within the intersection facing a southwest direction. V2 came to rest within the intersection facing a northerly direction.

V1 was traveling southbound on an interstate off-ramp in the number 1 lane of a 1 lane one way roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V2 and V3 were traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane one way interstate on-ramp, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the roadway to the left and entered the northbound on-ramp where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Debris flew off from this impact and the debris impacted the back of V3. V1 came to rest facing southeasterly on the right shoulder of the on-ramp. V2 came to rest facing northeast in the number 1 lane of the on-ramp, west of V1. V3 came to rest facing northeasterly in the number 1 lane of the on-ramp.

V1 was traveling southerly in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were traveling westerly in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway, preparing to turn left at an intersection. All vehicles entered the intersection. V1, V2, and V3 were then traveling southerly on the south side of the intersection in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. This collision pushed V2 forward and to the right where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3. V2 then departed the roadway to the right where the front of V2 impacted a curb. V2 continued southerly off the roadway where the front of V2 impacted an electrical tower. V2 continued forward where the front of V2 impacted the ground. V1, after the impact with V2, rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing northerly in the number 1 southbound lane. V2 came to rest off the west roadway up against the ground, facing southerly, V3 came to rest facing south in the number 1

Vehicle 1 was traveling north approaching an intersection on a 4 lane, two way undivided roadway in lane number 3. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 3 was stopped facing west on an intersecting six lane, two way undivided roadway. In the intersection Vehicle 1 attempted to make a right turn and vehicle 1's right side made contact with vehicle 2's front. After initial contact vehicle 2 continued forward and made contact with the front of vehicle 3. All vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 4 lane median divided roadway in lane number 2. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway in lane 1. Vehicle 2 attempted to change lanes and the right side of vehicle 1 contacted the left of vehicle 2. Both vehicles came to final rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way gravel roadway approaching aa sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling west on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 left  plane was contacted by V2 front plane.  V1 continued forward contacting the guardrail with unknown plane. V1 then drove away from the scene. V2 came to final rest on the southwest corner of the intersection.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way, undivided roadway when a deer entered the roadway from the north.  The front plane of V1 struck the deer and V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and began to skid on the wet ground. V1's front plane contacted tree 1, then tree 2. V1's right plane contacted a barbed wire fence, and then the front plane again contacted a tree, uprooting the tree. Then it's front plane contacted another tree before coming to final rest off the roadway near the final impact.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching an intersection to turn right. V2 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. Both came to final rest on the roadway near impact.

V1 was traveling north on a private drive attempting to make a left turn onto a two lane roadway. V2 was traveling northwest in lane one of a two lane roadway approaching the private drive. V1's right plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 then departed the left roadway and the front plane contacted a ditch were it came to final rest. V2 came to final rest near impact.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane, undivided roadway in lane one. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. V2 stopped in the roadway to turn left into a private drive. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 departed the right road edge where its front contacted a tree and its top contacted overhanging tree limbs. V1 came to rest under the tree facing northwest. V2 rotated counter clockwise and departed the roadway to the left, coming to rest in the private drive facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling in the second of three southbound travel lanes on a six lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle 1 encountered standing water and lost control departing its travel lane to the left and entered into the third travel lane. Vehicle 2 contacted its frontal plane with the left side plane of vehicle 1. Vehicle 3 then contacted its frontal plane with the back plane of vehicle 2. All vehicles came to rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was at a stop sign making a right turn traveling in the eastbound lane of a two lane median divided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a sign with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 reentered the roadway and continued to travel eastbound and encountered a left hand curve. Vehicle 1 contacted the concrete curbing with its frontal plane as it departed the roadway and continued travelling. Vehicle 1 contacted shrubbery with its frontal plane and came to rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in the first of two lanes on an undivided, two-way roadway entering a stop sign controlled, three-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling west in the third of four lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2. After the initial impact, both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the second of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering a light controlled, four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling west in the fourth of five lanes on a divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection as V1 attempting to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. After the initial impact, both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound on a two lane, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, non-physically divided roadway in the lane 1 position.  Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered the intersection at the same time.  The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing Southeast in the intersection.  Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing Southeast just after impact in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 4 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 2, approaching an intersection. V2, V3, V4 were also traveling east on the same roadway in lane 2, stopped at the traffic light, with V2 in front of V1, V3 in front of V2, and V4 in front of V3. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.  The front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.  The front of V3 contacted the rear of V4.  All vehicles came to rest in same lane of travel, facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, business driveway access in lane 1, approaching an intersecting roadway. V2 was traveling east on a 5 lane, two way, non-physically divided roadway in lane 1, approaching the intersecting business driveway. As V1 entered the intersection the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 came to rest facing southeast and V2 came to rest also facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, two-way, divided roadway. V1 departed travel lane to the right, continuing forward exiting the roadway to the right. V1's front plane contacted an embankment, V1 then rotated clockwise  and contacted the embankment again with its left rear before coming to rest facing west off the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching a 4-way intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on lane 1 of a 2 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1's left plane contacted V2's front plane. V1 rotated counter-clockwise exiting the roadway on the southside of the intersection in the grass median. V2 continued exiting the roadway on the north side of the intersection, contacting an utility marker with V2's front plane, coming to final rest in the grass median.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane three of a three lane trafficway, not divided by a positive barrier. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane two of  a four lane trafficway, not divided by a positive barrier. V1 departed the lane and roadway on the left side. V1 entered the southbound travel lanes on the left side and departed the lane twice on the left side. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 spun clockwise and contacted the right side on the guard rail. The front of V2 then contacted the guard rail. V1 came to rest on the roadway facing west. V2 came to rest on the roadway facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling Northbound on a 4 lane Non-Physically divided roadway in the lane 2 position. Vehicle 1 was turning left from a 3 lane Non-Physically divided, one way roadway in the lane 2 position. Both Vehicles 1 and 2 entered into the the intersection at the same time. The right plane of Vehicle 1 made contact with the front plane of Vehicle 2. The impact cause Vehicle 1 to rotate clockwise coming to final rest facing east in the middle of the intersection. Vehicle 2 also rotated clockwise coming to final rest facing west in the middle of the intersection.

V1 was negotiating a slight left curve, traveling South East on a 2 way undivided roadway in lane 1.  V1 departed the right side of the roadway, over corrected and began rotating counterclockwise.  V1 was skidding with its right plane leading.  The right side tires tripped up in the soft gravel/dirt causing the vehicle to roll right.  V1 completed 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its top plane.  V1 was facing South East at final rest.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right road edge, and the frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane No. 2 of an undivided, five-lane roadway and approaching a four leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in lane No. 2 of an undivided four-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 initiated a left turn at the intersection as the front plane of Vehicle 2 impacted the right side of Vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and came to rest facing west. Vehicle 2 rotated slightly counterclockwise and came to rest facing east.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south in lane two of a three lane, divided trafficway without a positive barrier.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north in the channelized left turn lane of the same trafficway.  V2 began to turn left at an intersection. V2 came to a stop within the intersection where the front of V1 contacted the right of V2. Both vehicle came to rest within the intersection.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on an exit ramp.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north on an intersecting roadway.  V1 began to turn left at the intersection and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane, one way roadway, approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 as both vehicles proceeded straight. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling South on a 3 lane intersection divided traffic way with a median strip that had no positive barrier, while V2 was traveling in a 3 lane intersection that was not physically divided with 2 way left turn lanes. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 as it was turning left.  The vehicles then rotated and the right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest facing Northeast on the intersection. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest facing Southeast on the intersection.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a two lane one way traffic way. V2 was in front of V1.  A vehicle ahead of V2 was stopped for a pedestrian in the roadway and V2 was decelerating. The front of V1 contacted back of V2. V1 and V2 came to rest near impact.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane 1 on a non-physically divided five lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway right where the frontal plane contacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest just off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane contacted the terminal end of a guardrail. V1 continued off the roadway down a slope where it rolled over four quarter turns. During the rollover the back plane contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest on its wheels, off the roadway, facing west.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound on a two lane roadway. Both vehicle entered an intersection and V1's front plane contacted V2's left plane. V2 continued southwest, departed the road to the right where its left front wheel contacted the curb. V2 then struck a sign pole with its left plane, and a fence with its front plane. V1 came to final rest on the road. V2 came to final rest off the road to the west.

V2 was traveling westbound approaching an intersection on a three-lane, divided roadway in lane two. V1 was stopped in traffic heading westbound on the same roadway and lane. The front plane of V2 contacted the back plane of V1. After impact V2 continued northbound where it departed the roadway on the northern traffic island. The left front tire of V2 contacted a curb before continuing off the roadway where the right plane struck a crosswalk pole. V1 came to final rest in the roadway near point of impact facing north west. V2 came to final rest off the roadway facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed it's travel lane to the left, then left side roadway. V1 struck a fallen tree with its front plane and then continued north off the road impacting a second tree with its front. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane roadway while negotiating a curve to the left. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 steered left and re-entered the roadway.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise as it crossed the lane line to the left. The right side of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise, departed the westbound road edge and came to rest on the dirt roadside facing southwest. V2 rotated clockwise as it departed the westbound road edge and came to rest on the dirt roadside facing east. The driver of V1 was ejected during the crash sequence.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway in the southbound lane. V2 was traveling east on an intersecting two lane, two way roadway in the eastbound lane. The front end of V2 impacted the right side of V1 in the intersection. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest in the northbound lane of the southern leg of the intersection. V2 came to rest in the eastbound lane of the eastern leg of the intersection.

V1 was heading south on a three lane divided trafficway with a cable barrier in the grassy median. V1 was traveling in the first southbound lane. V2 was traveling south in the same lane behind V1. In lane one, the front end of V2 impacted the back end of V1. V1 exited the roadway into the median and came to final rest facing south. V2 exited the roadway and struck the cable barrier and overturned (one quarter turn, leading right) before coming to final rest in median.

V1 and V2 were traveling in a eastern direction on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 had stopped in the lane of travel in order to make a left turn across oncoming traffic. V2's frontal plane impacted V1's rear plane. Both vehicles came to rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane divided roadway in lane two, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a three lane undivided roadway in lane two, approaching an intersection. As V1 and V2 both crossed through the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left of V2. V1 came to rest in the intersection facing south. V2 came to rest in the intersection facing northeast.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 on a 3-lane roadway. V1 attempted to make a right turn onto an intersecting roadway and departed the left road edge where its left front wheel contacted a curb. V1 continued forward and its front plane contacted a brick wall and metal fence combination. V1 came to rest against the wall facing northeast.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a three lane, undivided roadway, approaching an intersection. Before the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on an undivided two lane road, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the south road edge and the front of V1 impacted a ditch. V1 continued traveling east off the road edge and the front of V1 impacted a tree/bush. As V1 continued traveling East the front of V1 was impacted by the same tree/bush. V1 came to rest on its wheels facing a easterly direction.

V1 was traveling south on a undivided two lane road, in lane one. negotiating a right turn. For an unknown reason V1 traveled on the northbound lanes and off the east road edge, and the front of V1 impacted a tire wall. V1 came to rest off the roadway facing a southeast direction.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a three lane, one way roadway, in the lane 1 position.  Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a three lane, non-physically divided roadway, in the lane 1 position.  Both vehicles entered into an intersection at the same time.  The right plane of V1 made contact with front plane of V2.  V1 rotated counter clockwise and V2 rotated clockwise creating a side slap impact.  Damage was sustained on the right plane of V1 and the left plane of V2.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the southwest corner of the intersection facing roughly southwest.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane 2 on a 2-lane divided, two-way roadway entering a four-legged intersection attempting to turn left. V2 was traveling southwest in lane 3 on a 4-lane divided, two-way roadway entering the same intersection.  Within the intersection, the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2. After the initial impact, Vehicle 1 rotated counterclockwise and then rolled forward to final rest within the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the road on the left. V1 was traveling west in a not physically divided trafficway (with two way left turn lane) in lane 1 (of three lanes) and making a left turn into a driveway. V2 came to rest on its wheels facing east in lane 1.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a three lane divided (no positive barrier) roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve in the roadway. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve in the roadway. V1 departed the left hand side of the roadway.
